#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:105
#, no-c-format
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr "Uvod"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:106
#, no-c-format
msgid "Yet Another Diff Frontend?"
msgstr "Še eno začelje Diffa?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:107
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Several graphical diff tools exist. Why choose &kdiff3;? Let me say, why I "
"wrote it."
msgstr ""
"Obstaja več grafičnih orodij za razlikovanje. Zakaj izbrati &kdiff3;? Naj "
"povem, zakaj sem ga napisal."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:109
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kdiff3; started because I had to do a difficult merge. Merging is necessary "
"when several people work on the same files in a project. A merge can be "
"somewhat automated, when the merge-tool not only has the new modified files "
"(called \"branches\"), but also the original file (called \"base\"). The "
"merge tool will automatically choose any modification that was only done in "
"one branch. When several contributors change the same lines, then the merge "
"tool detects a conflict which must be solved manually."
msgstr ""
"&kdiff3; se je začel, ker sem moral opraviti težko zlivanje. Zlivanje je "
"potrebno, kadar več ljudi dela na istih datotekah v projektu. Zlivanje je "
"lahko nekoliko avtomatizirano, ko ima orodje za spajanje ne le nove "
"spremenjene datoteke (imenovane \"veje\"), temveč tudi izvirno datoteko "
"(imenovano \"osnova\"). Orodje za zlivanje bo samodejno izbralo vse "
"spremembe, ki so bile izvedene samo v eni veji. Ko več sodelujočih spremeni "
"iste vrstice, potem orodje za spajanje zazna konflikt, ki ga je treba rešiti "
"ročno."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:116
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The merge then was difficult because one contributor had changed many things "
"and corrected the indentation in many places. Another contributor also had "
"changed much text in the same file, which resulted in several merge "
"conflicts."
msgstr ""
"Zlivanje je bilo takrat težko, ker je en sodelujoči spremenil marsikaj in "
"popravil zamik na mnogih mestih. Drugi sodelavec je prav tako spremenil "
"veliko besedila v isti datoteki, kar je povzročilo več sporov pri zlivanju."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:120
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The tool I used then, only showed the changed lines, but not what had "
"changed within these lines. And there was no information about where only "
"the indentation was changed. The merge was a little nightmare."
msgstr ""
"Orodje, ki sem ga takrat uporabil, je pokazalo samo spremenjene vrstice, ne "
"pa tudi tega, kar se je spremenilo v teh vrsticah. In ni bilo nobenih "
"informacij o tem, kje je bila spremenjen le zamik. Zlivanje je bilo majhna "
"nočna mora."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:124
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"So this was the start. The first version could show differences within a "
"line and showed white space differences. Later many other features were "
"added to increase the usefulness."
msgstr ""
"To je bil torej začetek. Prva različica je lahko pokazala razlike znotraj "
"vrstice in je pokazala razlike v praznem prostoru. Kasneje so bile dodane "
"številne druge funkcije za povečanje uporabnosti."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:127
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For example if you want to compare some text quickly, then you can copy it "
"to the clipboard and paste it into either diff window."
msgstr ""
"Na primer, če želite hitro primerjati nekaj besedila, ga lahko kopirate v "
"odložišče in prilepite v katero koli okno diff."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:130
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A feature that required a big effort was the folder comparison and merge "
"facility, which turned the program almost into a full file browser."
msgstr ""
"Funkcija, ki je zahtevala veliko truda, je primerjava in zlivanje map, ki je "
"program spremenila skoraj v popoln brskalnik datotek."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:133
#, no-c-format
msgid "I hope &kdiff3; works for you too. Have fun!"
msgstr "Upam, da &kdiff3; deluje tudi za vas. Uživajte!"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:135
#, no-c-format
msgid "Joachim Eibl (2003)"
msgstr "Joachim Eibl (2003)"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:140
#, no-c-format
msgid "Screenshots and Features"
msgstr "Posnetki zaslona in zmožnosti"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:141
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This screenshot shows the difference between two text files (using an early "
"version of &kdiff3;):"
msgstr ""
"Ta posnetek zaslona prikazuje razliko med dvema besedilnima datotekama (z "
"uporabo zgodnje različice &kdiff3;):"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:146
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"3-way-merging is fully supported. This is useful if two people change code "
"independently. The original file (the base) is used to help &kdiff3; to "
"automatically select the correct changes. The merge-editor below the diff-"
"windows allows you to solve conflicts, while showing you the output you will "
"get. You can even edit the output. This screenshot shows three input files "
"being merged:"
msgstr ""
"3-smerno zlivanje je v celoti podprto. To je uporabno, če dve osebi "
"neodvisno spreminjata kodo. Izvirna datoteka (osnova) se uporablja za pomoč "
"&kdiff3; za samodejno izbiro pravilnih sprememb. Urejevalnik zlivanja pod "
"oknidiff vam omogoča reševanje sporov, hkrati pa vam prikazuje rezultat, ki "
"ga boste dobili. Izpis lahko celo urejate. Ta posnetek zaslona prikazuje "
"zlivanje treh vhodnih datotek:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:159
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kdiff3; also helps you to compare and merge complete folders. This "
"screenshot shows &kdiff3; during a folder merge:"
msgstr ""
"&kdiff3; pomaga tudi pri primerjavi in zlivanju celotnih map. Ta posnetek "
"zaslona prikazuje &kdiff3; med zlivanjem map:"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:168
#, no-c-format
msgid "More Features"
msgstr "Več zmožnosti"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:169
#, no-c-format
msgid "Line-By-Line And Char-By-Char Diff-Viewer"
msgstr "Pregledovalnik razlik vrstica po vrstici in znak po znaku"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:170
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"By using the possibilities of a graphical color display &kdiff3; shows "
"exactly what the difference is. When you have to do many code-reviews, you "
"will like this."
msgstr ""
"Z uporabo možnosti grafičnega barvnega prikaza &kdiff3; točno pokaže v čem "
"je razlika. Ko boste morali opraviti veliko pregledov kode, vam bo to všeč."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:178
#, no-c-format
msgid "See White-Space Differences At One Glance"
msgstr "Oglejte si razlike v belem prostoru v enem samem pogledu"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:179
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Spaces and tabs that differ appear visibly. When lines differ only in the "
"amount of white space this can be seen at one look in the summary column on "
"the left side. (No more worries when people change the indentation.)"
msgstr ""
"Presledki in zavihki, ki se razlikujejo, so vidni. Ko se vrstice razlikujejo "
"le po količini praznega prostora, je to mogoče videti v enem samem pogledu v "
"stolpcu s povzetkom na levi strani. (Nič več skrbi, ko ljudje spremenijo "
"zamik.)"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:188
#, no-c-format
msgid "Triple-Diff"
msgstr "Trojni dif"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:189
#, no-c-format
msgid "Analyze three files and see where they differ."
msgstr "Analizirajte tri datoteke in ugotovite, kje se razlikujejo."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:190
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The left/middle/right windows are named <guilabel>A</guilabel>/<guilabel>B</"
"guilabel>/<guilabel>C</guilabel> and have the blue/green/magenta color "
"respectively."
msgstr ""
"Levo/srednje/desno okno se imenuje <guilabel>A</guilabel>/<guilabel>B</"
"guilabel>/<guilabel>C</guilabel> in ima barvo modro/zeleno/magenta."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:192
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If one file is the same and one file is different on a line then the color "
"shows which file is different. The red color means that both other files are "
"different."
msgstr ""
"Če je ena datoteka v vrstici enaka in ena drugačna, potem barva prikazuje, "
"katera datoteka je drugačna. Rdeča barva pomeni, da sta obe drugi datoteki "
"različni."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:202
#, no-c-format
msgid "Comfortable Merge Of Two Or Three Input Files"
msgstr "Udobno zlivanje dveh ali treh vhodnih datotek"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:203
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kdiff3; can be used to merge two or three input files and automatically "
"merges as much as possible. The result is presented in an editable window "
"where most conflicts can be solved with a single mouseclick: Select the "
"respective <guibutton>...</guibutton> buttons at the <guilabel>A</guilabel>/ "
"<guilabel>B</guilabel>/<guilabel>C</guilabel> windows to select the source "
"that should be used. You can also select more than one source. Since this "
"output window is an editor even conflicts which need further corrections can "
"be solved here without requiring another tool."
msgstr ""
"&kdiff3; se lahko uporablja za združevanje dveh ali treh vhodnih datotek in "
"samodejno zlije čim več. Rezultat je predstavljen v oknu, ki ga je mogoče "
"urejati, kjer je večino konfliktov mogoče rešiti z enim samim klikom miške: "
"izberite ustrezne gumbe <guibutton>...</guibutton> pri <guilabel>A</"
"guilabel>/ <guilabel>B</guilabel>/<guilabel>C</guilabel> za izbiro vira, ki "
"naj bo uporabljen. Izberete lahko tudi več kot en vir. Ker je to izhodno "
"okno urejevalnik, lahko tudi konflikte, ki potrebujejo nadaljnje popravke, "
"rešite tukaj, ne da bi potrebovali drugo orodje."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:214
#, no-c-format
msgid "And ..."
msgstr "in ..."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:216
#, no-c-format
msgid "Fast navigation via buttons."
msgstr "Hitra navigacija prek gumbov."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:217
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A mouse-click into a summary column sync's all windows to show the same "
"position."
msgstr ""
"Klik z miško na stolpec s povzetkom sinhronizira vsa okna, da prikažejo isti "
"položaj."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:218
#, no-c-format
msgid "Select and copy from any window and paste into the merge result window."
msgstr ""
"Izberite in kopirajte iz katerega koli okna ter prilepite v okno z rezultati "
"zlivanja."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:219
#, no-c-format
msgid "Overview column that shows where the changes and conflicts are."
msgstr "Pregledni stolpec, ki prikazuje, kje so spremembe in koflikti."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:220
#, no-c-format
msgid "The colors are adjustable to your specific preferences."
msgstr "Barve so prilagodljive vašim preferencam."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:221
#, no-c-format
msgid "Adjustable Tab size."
msgstr "Nastavljiva velikost zavihka."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:222
#, no-c-format
msgid "Option to insert spaces instead of tabs."
msgstr "Možnost vstavljanja presledkov namesto tabulatorjev."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:223
#, no-c-format
msgid "Open files comfortably via dialog or specify files on the command line."
msgstr ""
"Udobno odprite datoteke prek pogovornega okna ali jih določite v ukazni "
"vrstici."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:224
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Search for strings in all text windows with <menuchoice><guimenu>Edit</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Find</guimenuitem></menuchoice> (<keycombo>&Ctrl;"
"<keycap>F</keycap></keycombo>) and <menuchoice><guimenu>Edit</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Find Next</guimenuitem></menuchoice> (<keycap>F3</"
"keycap>) menu items."
msgstr ""
"Poiščite nize v vseh besedilnih oknih z <menuchoice><guimenu>Uredi</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Najdi</guimenuitem></menuchoice> (<keycombo>&Ctrl;"
"<keycap>F</keycap></keycombo>) in <menuchoice><guimenu>Uredi</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Najdi naslednje</guimenuitem></menuchoice> (<keycap>F3</"
"keycap>) menijske elemente."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:225
#, no-c-format
msgid "Show the line numbers for each line."
msgstr "Pokaže številke vrstic za vsako vrstico."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:226
#, no-c-format
msgid "Paste clipboard or drag text into a diff input window."
msgstr "Prilepi odložišče ali povleče besedilo v okno vnosa razlike."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:227
#, no-c-format
msgid "Network transparency via KIO."
msgstr "Preglednost omrežja prek KIO."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:228
#, no-c-format
msgid "Can be used as diff-viewer from the &kdevelop; 3."
msgstr "Lahko se uporablja kot pregledovalnik razlik iz &kdevelop; 3."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:229
#, no-c-format
msgid "Word-wrap for long lines."
msgstr "Prelom besed za dolge vrstice."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:230
#, no-c-format
msgid "Support for Unicode, UTF-8 and other codecs."
msgstr "Podpora za Unicode, UTF-8 in druge kodeke."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:231
#, no-c-format
msgid "Support for right to left languages."
msgstr "Podpora za jezike od desne proti levi."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:232 index.docbook:1181
#, no-c-format
msgid "<para>...</para>"
msgstr "<para>...</para>"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:238
#, no-c-format
msgid "File Comparison And Merge"
msgstr "Primerjava in zlivanje datotek"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:240
#, no-c-format
msgid "Command-Line Options"
msgstr "Možnosti ukazne vrstice"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:242
#, no-c-format
msgid "Comparing 2 files:"
msgstr "Primerjava dveh datotek:"

#. Tag: screen
#: index.docbook:243
#, no-c-format
msgid "<command>kdiff3</command> <replaceable>file1 file2</replaceable>"
msgstr ""
"<command>kdiff3</command> <replaceable>datoteka1 datoteka2</replaceable>"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:246
#, no-c-format
msgid "Merging 2 files:"
msgstr "Zlivanje 2 datotek:"

#. Tag: screen
#: index.docbook:247
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<command>kdiff3</command> <replaceable>file1 file2</replaceable> -m\n"
"   <command>kdiff3</command> <replaceable>file1 file2</replaceable> -o "
"<replaceable>outputfile</replaceable>"
msgstr ""
"<command>kdiff3</command> <replaceable>datoteka1 datoteka2</replaceable> -m\n"
"   <command>kdiff3</command> <replaceable>datoteka1 datoteka2</replaceable> -"
"o <replaceable>izhodnadatoteka</replaceable>"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:250
#, no-c-format
msgid "Comparing 3 files:"
msgstr "Primerjava 3 datotek:"

#. Tag: screen
#: index.docbook:251
#, no-c-format
msgid "<command>kdiff3</command> <replaceable>file1 file2 file3</replaceable>"
msgstr ""
"<command>kdiff3</command> <replaceable>datoteka1 datoteka2 datoteka3</"
"replaceable>"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:254
#, no-c-format
msgid "Merging 3 files:"
msgstr "Zlivanje 3 datotek:"

#. Tag: screen
#: index.docbook:255
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<command>kdiff3</command> <replaceable>file1 file2 file3</replaceable> -m\n"
"   <command>kdiff3</command> <replaceable>file1 file2 file3</replaceable> -o "
"<replaceable>outputfile</replaceable>"
msgstr ""
"<command>kdiff3</command> <replaceable>datoteka1 datoteka2 datoteka3</"
"replaceable> -m\n"
"<command>kdiff3</command> <replaceable>datoteka1 datoteka2 datoteka3</"
"replaceable> -o <replaceable>izhodnadatoteka</replaceable>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:256
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Note that <replaceable>file1</replaceable> will be treated as base of "
"<replaceable>file2</replaceable> and <replaceable>file3</replaceable>."
msgstr ""
"Upoštevajte, da bo <replaceable>datoteka1</replaceable> obravnavana kot "
"osnova <replaceable>datoteka2</replaceable> in <replaceable>datoteka3</"
"replaceable>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:263
#, no-c-format
msgid "Special case: Files with the same name"
msgstr "Poseben primer: datoteke z enakim imenom"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:264
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If all files have the same name but are in different folders, you can reduce "
"typework by specifying the filename only for the first file, &eg;:"
msgstr ""
"Če imajo vse datoteke enako ime, vendar so v različnih mapah, lahko "
"zmanjšate tipkanje tako, da določite ime datoteke samo za prvo datoteko, "
"&eg;:"

#. Tag: screen
#: index.docbook:268
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<command>kdiff3</command> <replaceable>folder1/filename folder2 folder3</"
"replaceable>"
msgstr ""
"<command>kdiff3</command> <replaceable>mapa1/imedatoteke mapa2 mapa3</"
"replaceable>"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:271
#, no-c-format
msgid "Commandline for starting a folder comparison or merge:"
msgstr "Ukazna vrstica za začetek primerjave ali zlivanje map:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:272
#, no-c-format
msgid "This is very similar, but now it's about folders."
msgstr "To je zelo podobno, vendar gre zdaj za mape."

#. Tag: screen
#: index.docbook:273
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<command>kdiff3</command> <replaceable>folder1 folder2</replaceable>\n"
"   <command>kdiff3</command> <replaceable>folder1 folder2</replaceable> -o "
"<replaceable>destdir</replaceable>\n"
"   <command>kdiff3</command> <replaceable>folder1 folder2 folder3</"
"replaceable>\n"
"   <command>kdiff3</command> <replaceable>folder1 folder2 folder3</"
"replaceable> -o <replaceable>destdir</replaceable>"
msgstr ""
"<command>kdiff3</command> <replaceable>folder1 folder2</replaceable>\n"
"   <command>kdiff3</command> <replaceable>folder1 folder2</replaceable> -o "
"<replaceable>destdir</replaceable>\n"
"   <command>kdiff3</command> <replaceable>folder1 folder2 folder3</"
"replaceable>\n"
"   <command>kdiff3</command> <replaceable>folder1 folder2 folder3</"
"replaceable> -o <replaceable>destdir</replaceable>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:274
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For folder comparison and merge you can continue to read <link linkend="
"\"dirmerge\">here</link>."
msgstr ""
"Za primerjavo in združevanje map lahko nadaljujete z branjem <link linkend="
"\"dirmerge\">tukaj</link>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:277
#, no-c-format
msgid "Other command line options"
msgstr "Druge možnosti ukazne vrstice"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:278
#, no-c-format
msgid "To see all available command line options type"
msgstr "Če želite videti vse razpoložljive možnosti ukazne vrstice, vnesite"

#. Tag: screen
#: index.docbook:279
#, no-c-format
msgid "<command>kdiff3</command> --help"
msgstr "<command>kdiff3</command> --help"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:280
#, no-c-format
msgid "Example output:"
msgstr "Primer izhoda:"

#. Tag: screen
#: index.docbook:281
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Options:\n"
"  -m, --merge               Merge the input.\n"
"  -b, --base file           Explicit base file. For compatibility with "
"certain tools.\n"
"  -o, --output file         Output file. Implies -m. E.g.: -o newfile.txt\n"
"  --out file                Output file, again. (For compatibility with "
"certain tools.)\n"
"  --noauto                  Ignore --auto and always show GUI.\n"
"  --auto                    No GUI if all conflicts are auto-solvable. "
"(Needs -o file)\n"
"  --L1 alias1               Visible name replacement for input file 1 "
"(base).\n"
"  --L2 alias2               Visible name replacement for input file 2.\n"
"  --L3 alias3               Visible name replacement for input file 3.\n"
"  -L, --fname alias         Alternative visible name replacement. Supply "
"this once for every input.\n"
"  --cs string               Override a config setting. Use once for every "
"setting. E.g.: --cs \"AutoAdvance=1\"\n"
"  --confighelp              Show list of config settings and current "
"values.\n"
"  --config file             Use a different config file."
msgstr ""
"Options:\n"
"  -m, --merge               Zlij input.\n"
"  -b, --base file           Eksplicitna datoteka osnova. Zaradi združjivosti "
"z določenimi orodji.\n"
"  -o, --output file         Output datoteka. Pomeni -m. Npr.: -o newfile."
"txt\n"
"  --out file                Spet output datoteka. (Zaradi združjivosti z "
"določenimi orodji.)\n"
"  --noauto                  Prezri --auto in vedno pokaži uporabniški "
"vmesnik.\n"
"  --auto                    Brez grafičnega vmesnika, če so vsi konflikti "
"samodejno rešljivi. (Potrebuje -o datoteka)\n"
"  --L1 alias1               Vidna zamenjava imena za vhodno datoteko 1 "
"(osnova).\n"
"  --L2 alias2               Vidna zamenjava imena za vhodno datoteko 2.\n"
"  --L3 alias3               Vidna zamenjava imena za vhodno datoteko 3.\n"
"  -L, --fname alias         Alternativna vidna zamenjava imena. Ena omemba "
"za vsak input.\n"
"  --cs string               Preglasi nastavitev config. Uporaba enkratno za "
"vsako nastavitev. npr.: --cs \"AutoAdvance=1\"\n"
"  --confighelp              Prikaži seznam nastavitev konfiguracije in "
"trenutne vrednosti.\n"
"  --config file             Uporabi drugo datoteko config."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:282
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The option <option>--cs</option> allows you to adjust a configuration value "
"that is otherwise only adjustable via the configure dialogs. But be aware "
"that when &kdiff3; then terminates the changed value will be stored along "
"with the other settings. With <option>--confighelp</option> you can find out "
"the names of the available items and current values."
msgstr ""
"Možnost <option>--cs</option> vam omogoča prilagoditev konfiguracijske "
"vrednosti, ki je sicer nastavljiva samo prek konfiguracijskih pogovornih "
"oken. Vendar se zavedajte, da ko se &kdiff3; nato prekine, bo spremenjena "
"vrednost  shranjena skupaj z drugimi nastavitvami. Z <option>--confighelp</"
"option> lahko izveste imena razpoložljivih elementov in trenutne vrednosti."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:285
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Via <option>--config</option> you can specify a different config file. When "
"you often use &kdiff3; with completely different setups this allows you to "
"easily switch between them."
msgstr ""
"Z <option>--config</option> lahko določite drugo konfiguracijsko datoteko. "
"Ko pogosto uporabljate &kdiff3; s popolnoma različnimi nastavitvami vam to "
"omogoča enostavno preklapljanje med njimi."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:288
#, no-c-format
msgid "Ignorable command line options"
msgstr "Zanemarljive možnosti ukazne vrstice"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:289
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Many people want to use &kdiff3; with some version control system. But when "
"that version control system calls &kdiff3; using command line parameters "
"that &kdiff3; doesn't recognise, then &kdiff3; terminates with an error. The "
"<guilabel>Integration</guilabel> item in the settings dialog allow to "
"specify command line parameters that should be ignored by &kdiff3;. They "
"will appear in the usage help like in this example:"
msgstr ""
"Veliko ljudi želi uporabljati &kdiff3; z nekim sistemom za nadzor različic. "
"Ko pa sistem za nadzor različic pokliče &kdiff3; z uporabo parametrov ukazne "
"vrstice, ki &kdiff3; ne prepozna, se potem &kdiff3; zaključi z napako. "
"Element <guilabel>Integracija</guilabel> v pogovornem oknu z nastavitvami "
"omogoča podajanje parametrov ukazne vrstice, ki naj jih &kdiff3; prezre. "
"Prikazali se bodo v pomoči za uporabo, kot v tem primeru:"

#. Tag: screen
#: index.docbook:292
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"--<replaceable>foo</replaceable>                     Ignored. (User defined.)"
msgstr "--<replaceable>foo</replaceable> Prezrto. (Uporabnik definiran.)"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:294
#, no-c-format
msgid "Command line options to ignore:"
msgstr "Možnosti ukazne vrstice, ki jih je treba prezreti:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:294
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A list of options, separated via semicolon ';'. When one of these options "
"appears on the commandline, then &kdiff3; will ignore it and run without "
"reporting an error. (Default is \"<literal>u;query;html;abort</literal>\")."
msgstr ""
"Seznam možnosti, ločenih s podpičjem ';'. Ko se ena od teh možnosti prikaže "
"v ukazni vrstici, potem ga bo &kdiff3; prezrl in zagnal brez poročanja o "
"napaki. (Privzeto je \"<literal>u;query;html;abort</literal>\")."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:299
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When this isn't enough, then it is recommended to write a shell script that "
"does the option translation."
msgstr ""
"Ko to ni dovolj, je priporočljivo napisati skript lupine, ki prevede to "
"možnost."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:304
#, no-c-format
msgid "Open-Dialog"
msgstr "Odpri pogovorno okno"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:305
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Since many input files must be selectable, the program has a special open "
"dialog:"
msgstr ""
"Ker mora biti možno izbirati veliko vhodnih datotek, ima program posebno "
"pogovorno okno za odpiranje:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:311
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The open dialog allows you to edit the filenames by hand, selecting a file "
"via the file-browser via the <guibutton>File...</guibutton> button or allows "
"you to choose recent files from the drop-down lists. If you open the dialog "
"again, then the current names still remain there. The third input file is "
"not required. If the entry for <guilabel>C</guilabel> remains empty, then "
"only a two file diff analysis will be done."
msgstr ""
"Pogovorno okno za odpiranje vam omogoča ročno urejanje imen datotek, izbiro "
"datoteke v brskalniku datotek prek gumba <guibutton>Datoteka...</guibutton> "
"ali vam omogoča izbiro nedavnih datotek s spustnih seznamov. Če znova "
"odprete pogovorno okno, bodo trenutna imena še vedno tam. Tretja vhodna "
"datoteka ni potrebna. Če vnos za <guilabel>C</guilabel> ostane prazen, bo "
"opravljena le analiza razlike v dveh datotekah."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:318
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can also select a folder via the <guibutton>Folder...</guibutton> "
"button. If for <guilabel>A</guilabel> a folder is specified then a folder-"
"comparison /merge starts. If <guilabel>A</guilabel> specifies a file but "
"<guilabel>B</guilabel>, <guilabel>C</guilabel> or the output specify a "
"folder, then &kdiff3; uses the filename from <guilabel>A</guilabel> in the "
"specified folders."
msgstr ""
"Prav tako lahko izberete mapo z gumbom <guibutton>Mapa...</guibutton>. Če je "
"za <guilabel>A</guilabel> podana mapa, se začne primerjava /združevanje map. "
"Če <guilabel>A</guilabel> določa datoteko, vendar <guilabel>B</guilabel>, "
"<guilabel>C</guilabel> ali izhod določa mapo, potem &kdiff3; uporablja ime "
"datoteke iz <guilabel>A</guilabel> v navedenih mapah."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:324
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If <guilabel>Merge</guilabel> check box is selected, then the "
"<guilabel>Output</guilabel> line becomes editable. But it is not required to "
"specify the output filename immediately. You can also postpone this until "
"saving."
msgstr ""
"Če je izbrano potrditveno polje <guilabel>Združi</guilabel>, postane vrstica "
"<guilabel>Izhod</guilabel> možna za urejanje. Vendar ni treba takoj določiti "
"imena izhodne datoteke. To lahko tudi odložite do shranjevanja."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:328
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <guibutton>Configure...</guibutton> button opens the settings dialog, so "
"that you can set the options before running the analysis."
msgstr ""
"Gumb <guibutton>Konfiguriraj...</guibutton> odpre pogovorno okno z "
"nastavitvami, tako da lahko nastavite možnosti, preden zaženete analizo."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:334
#, no-c-format
msgid "Paste and Drop Input"
msgstr "Prilepi in spusti vnos"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:335
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Sometimes you want to compare parts of a text that is not an own file. "
"&kdiff3; also allows you to paste text from the clipboard into the diff "
"input window that has the focus. The diff analysis happens immediately then. "
"In the open dialog you need not specify files then, but just close it via "
"<guibutton>Cancel</guibutton> button."
msgstr ""
"Včasih želite primerjati dele besedila, ki ni lastna datoteka. &kdiff3; "
"omogoča tudi lepljenje besedila iz odložišča v okno za vnos razlike, ki ima "
"fokus. Analiza diff se zgodi takoj. V odprtem pogovornem oknu vam takrat ni "
"treba določiti datotek, ampak ga samo zaprete z gumbom <guibutton>Prekliči</"
"guibutton>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:340
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can also use drag and drop: Drag a file from a file manager or selected "
"text from an editor and drop it onto a diff input window."
msgstr ""
"Uporabite lahko tudi povleci in spusti: povlecite datoteko iz upravljalnika "
"datotek ali izbrano besedilo iz urejevalnika in ga spustite v okno za vnos "
"razlike."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:343
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"What's the idea? Sometimes a file contains two similar functions, but "
"checking how similar they really are is a big effort if you first must "
"create two files and then load them. Now you can simply copy, paste and "
"compare the relevant sections."
msgstr ""
"Kaj je ideja? Včasih datoteka vsebuje dve podobni funkciji, vendar je "
"preverjanje, kako podobni sta v resnici, velik napor, če morate najprej "
"ustvariti dve datoteki in ju nato naložiti. Zdaj lahko preprosto kopirate, "
"prilepite in primerjate ustrezne razdelke."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:347
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Currently you cannot drag anything from &kdiff3;. Only dropping in the diff "
"input is supported."
msgstr ""
"Trenutno ne morete vleči ničesar iz &kdiff3;. Podprto je samo spuščanje "
"vnosa razlike."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:350
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Some editors still interpret the drag and drop into another program like cut "
"(instead of copy) and paste. Your original data might be lost then."
msgstr ""
"Nekateri urejevalniki si še vedno razlagajo tehniko povleci in spusti v drug "
"program kot izreži (namesto kopiraj) in prilepi. Vaši izvirni podatki bodo "
"takrat morda izgubljeni."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:356
#, no-c-format
msgid "Comparing Files And Interpreting The Information In The Input Windows"
msgstr "Primerjava datotek in razlaga informacij v vnosnih oknih"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:360
#, no-c-format
msgid "Info Line"
msgstr "Vrstica informacij"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:360
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"At the top of each text window is its \"info line\". The info lines of the "
"input windows contain a letter <guilabel>A</guilabel>, <guilabel>B</"
"guilabel> or <guilabel>C</guilabel>, the editable filename, a button for "
"browsing, and the line number of the first visible line in the window. (Note "
"that window <guilabel>C</guilabel> is optional.) Each info line appears in a "
"different color."
msgstr ""
"Na vrhu vsakega besedilnega okna je njegova \"vrstica informacij\". Vrstice "
"informacij vnosnih oken vsebujejo črko <guilabel>A</guilabel>, <guilabel>B</"
"guilabel> ali <guilabel>C</guilabel>, ime datoteke, ki ga je mogoče urejati, "
"gumb za brskanje in številko vrstice prve vidne vrstice v oknu. "
"(Upoštevajte, da okno <guilabel>C</guilabel> ni obvezno.) Vsaka "
"informacijska vrstica je prikazana v drugi barvi."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:366
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When you selected another file via browsing or finished editing the filename "
"here by pressing &Enter;, the new file will be loaded and compared with the "
"already loaded file(s)."
msgstr ""
"Ko izberete drugo datoteko z brskanjem ali dokončate urejanje imena datoteke "
"tukaj s pritiskom na &Enter;, se bo nova datoteka naložila in primerjala z "
"že naloženimi datotekami."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:370
#, no-c-format
msgid "Coloring"
msgstr "Barvanje"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:370
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The three input windows are assigned the letters <guilabel>A</guilabel>, "
"<guilabel>B</guilabel> and <guilabel>C</guilabel>. <guilabel>A</guilabel> "
"has color blue, <guilabel>B</guilabel> has green and <guilabel>C</guilabel> "
"has magenta. (These are the defaults, but can be changed in the "
"<guilabel>Color</guilabel> item in the settings dialog.)"
msgstr ""
"Trem vnosnim oknom so dodeljene črke <guilabel>A</guilabel>, <guilabel>B</"
"guilabel> in <guilabel>C</guilabel>. <guilabel>A</guilabel> ima modro barvo, "
"<guilabel>B</guilabel> zeleno in <guilabel>C</guilabel> škrlatno. (To so "
"privzete vrednosti, vendar jih lahko spremenite v elementu <guilabel>Barva</"
"guilabel> v pogovornem oknu z nastavitvami.)"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:376
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When a difference is detected then the color shows which input file differs. "
"When both other input files differ then the color used to express this is "
"red by default (<guilabel>Conflict color</guilabel> option in the "
"<guilabel>Color</guilabel> item in the settings dialog). This colorscheme is "
"especially useful in the case of three input files, which will be seen in "
"the next section (<link linkend=\"merging\">Merging</link>)."
msgstr ""
"Ko je zaznana razlika, barva pokaže, katera vhodna datoteka se razlikuje. Če "
"se obe drugi vhodni datoteki razlikujeta, je barva uporabljena za izražanje "
"tega, privzeto rdeča (možnost <guilabel>Barva spora</guilabel> v elementu "
"<guilabel>Barva</guilabel> v pogovornem oknu z nastavitvami). Ta barvna "
"shema je še posebej uporabna v primeru treh vhodnih datotek, kar bo "
"prikazano v naslednjem razdelku (<link linkend=\"merging\">Zlivanje</link>)."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:383
#, no-c-format
msgid "Summary Column"
msgstr "Stolpec povzetka"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:383
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Left of each text is the \"summary\" column. If differences occurred on a "
"line then the summary column shows the respective color. For a white-space-"
"only difference the summary is chequered. For programming languages where "
"white space is not so important this is useful to see at one glance if "
"anything of importance was modified. (In C/C++ white space is only "
"interesting within strings, comments, for the preprocessor, and some only "
"very esoteric situations.)"
msgstr ""
"Levo od vsakega besedila je stolpec \"povzetek\". Če so se v vrstici "
"pojavile razlike, bo stolpec s povzetkom prikazal ustrezno barvo. Za razliko "
"v presledku je povzetek označen. Za programske jezike, kjer prazen prostor "
"ni tako pomemben, je to koristno, da na en pogled vidite, ali je bilo kaj "
"pomembnega spremenjeno. (V C/C++ je prazen prostor zanimiv le znotraj nizov, "
"komentarjev, za predprocesor in v nekaterih le zelo ezoteričnih situacijah.)"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:390
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The vertical line separating the summary column and the text is interrupted "
"if the input file had no lines there. When word-wrap is enabled then this "
"vertical line appears dotted for wrapped lines."
msgstr ""
"Navpična črta, ki ločuje stolpec s povzetkom in besedilo, je prekinjena, če "
"vhodna datoteka tam ni imela vrstic. Ko je prelom besed omogočen, je ta "
"navpična črta prikazana s pikami za prelite vrstice."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:394
#, no-c-format
msgid "Overview Column"
msgstr "Pregledni stolpec"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:394
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"On the right side a \"overview\" column is visible left of the vertical "
"scrollbar. It shows the compressed summary column of input <guilabel>A</"
"guilabel>. All the differences and conflicts are visible at one glance. When "
"only two input windows are used, then all differences appear red here "
"because every difference is also a conflict. A black rectangle frames the "
"visible part of the inputs. For very long input files, when the number of "
"input lines is bigger than the height of the overview column in pixels, then "
"several input lines share one overview line. A conflict then has top "
"priority over simple differences, which have priority over no change, so "
"that no difference or conflict is lost here. By clicking into this overview "
"column the corresponding text will be shown."
msgstr ""
"Na desni strani je levo od navpičnega drsnika viden stolpec »pregled«. "
"Prikazuje stisnjen stolpec povzetka vnosa <guilabel>A</guilabel>. Vse "
"razlike in konflikti so vidni na en pogled. Ko sta uporabljeni samo dve "
"vnosni okni, so vse razlike tukaj rdeče, ker je vsaka razlika tudi konflikt. "
"Črn pravokotnik uokvirja vidni del vnosov. Pri zelo dolgih vhodnih "
"datotekah, ko je število vhodnih vrstic večje od višine preglednega stolpca "
"v slikovnih pikah, si več vhodnih vrstic deli eno pregledno vrstico. "
"Konflikt ima potem glavno prednost pred preprostimi razlikami, ki imajo "
"prednost pred nespremembami, tako da se tu ne izgubi nobena razlika ali "
"konflikt. S klikom na ta pregledni stolpec se prikaže ustrezno besedilo."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:406
#, no-c-format
msgid "Manually Aligning Lines"
msgstr "Ročno poravnavanje črt"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:406
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Sometimes the algorithm places the wrong lines next to each other. Or you "
"want to compare one piece of text with text at a completely different "
"position in the other file. For these situations you can manually instruct "
"&kdiff3; to align certain lines. Mark the text for which you want to improve "
"the alignment with the mouse as you would for copy and paste in the first "
"diff view and then choose <menuchoice><guimenu>Diffview</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Add Manual Diff Alignment</guimenuitem></menuchoice> "
"menu item (<keycombo>&Ctrl;<keycap>Y</keycap></keycombo>). An orange bar "
"will appear in the summary column next to the chosen text. Repeat this for "
"the second and (if available) third diff view. &kdiff3; will immediately "
"recalculate the differences everytime you do this, and will align the chosen "
"lines. Of course some of the previously matching lines in between might not "
"match anymore."
msgstr ""
"Včasih algoritem postavi napačne vrstice eno poleg druge. Ali pa želite "
"primerjati en del besedila z besedilom na povsem drugem mestu v drugi "
"datoteki. Za te situacije lahko ročno naročite &kdiff3; za poravnavo "
"določenih vrstic. Z miško označite besedilo, za katerega želite izboljšati "
"poravnavo, kot bi to naredili za kopiranje in lepljenje v prvem pogledu "
"diff, nato pa izberite <menuchoice><guimenu>Diffview</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Dodaj ročno diff alignment</guimenuitem ></menuchoice> "
"element menija (<keycombo>&Ctrl;<keycap>Y</keycap></keycombo>). V stolpcu s "
"povzetkom se poleg izbranega besedila prikaže oranžna vrstica. To ponovite "
"za drugi in (če je na voljo) tretji pogled razlike. &kdiff3; bo takoj znova "
"izračunal razlike vsakič, ko boste to storili, in bo poravnal izbrane črte. "
"Seveda se nekatere od prej ujemajočih se vmesnih vrstic morda ne bodo več "
"ujemale."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:416
#, no-c-format
msgid "Currently merging doesn't support the use of manual diff help."
msgstr "Trenutno zlivanje ne podpira uporabe pomoči za ročno razlikovanje."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:418
#, no-c-format
msgid "Manually Joining and Splitting Diff Sections"
msgstr "Ročno združevanje in ločevanje razlik"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:418
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In some cases &kdiff3; will see too many or too few diff sections for "
"merging. In such a case you can join or split existing sections."
msgstr ""
"V nekaterih primerih &kdiff3; bo videl preveč ali premalo razlik za "
"združevanje. V tem primeru lahko združite ali razdelite obstoječe razdelke."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:421
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Add new sections by first selecting text in the lines that belong together "
"in either input window (as for copying to the clipboard). Then choose "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>Merge</guimenu><guimenuitem>Split Diff At Selection</"
"guimenuitem></menuchoice> menu item. Splits will be added above the first "
"line and below the last line of the selected text. If you only want to add "
"one section, then select text beginning at another section-split."
msgstr ""
"Dodajte nove razdelke tako, da najprej izberete besedilo v vrsticah, ki "
"sodijo skupaj v katerem koli oknu za vnos (kot pri kopiranju v odložišče). "
"Nato izberite menijski element <menuchoice><guimenu>Zlij</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Razdeli razliko pri izbiri</guimenuitem></menuchoice>. "
"Razdeli bodo dodani nad prvo vrstico in pod zadnjo vrstico izbranega "
"besedila. Če želite dodati samo en razdelek, izberite besedilo, ki se začne "
"pri drugem razdelku razdelka."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:426
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For joining sections in either input window select something in the lines "
"from the sections to join. (You can join several sections in one step too.) "
"Then choose <menuchoice><guimenu>Merge</guimenu><guimenuitem>Join Selected "
"Diffs</guimenuitem></menuchoice> menu item."
msgstr ""
"Za združevanje odsekov v katerem koli vnosnem oknu izberite nekaj v vrsticah "
"iz odsekov, ki jih želite zliti skupaj. (Lahko tudi združite več razdelkov v "
"enem koraku.) Nato izberite menijski element <menuchoice><guimenu>Zlij</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Zlij izbrane razlike</guimenuitem></menuchoice>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:433
#, no-c-format
msgid "Merging And The Merge Output Editor Window"
msgstr "Spajanje in okno urejevalnika spajanja izhodnih podatkov"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:437
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The merge output editor window (below the diff input windows) also has an "
"info line at the top showing <guilabel>Output:</guilabel>, the filename and "
"<replaceable>[Modified]</replaceable> tag if you edited something. Usually "
"it will contain some text through the automatic merge facilities, but often "
"it will also contain conflicts."
msgstr ""
"Okno urejevalnika zlitih izhodov (pod okni za vnos razlike) ima na vrhu tudi "
"informacijsko vrstico, ki prikazuje <guilabel>Izhod:</guilabel>, ime "
"datoteke in oznako <replaceable>[Modified]</replaceable>, če ste nekaj "
"uredili. Običajno bo vseboval nekaj besedila prek možnosti samodejnega "
"združevanja, pogosto pa bo vseboval tudi spore."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:439
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"!!! Saving is disabled until all conflicts are resolved !!! (Use the "
"<guibutton>Go to Previous/Next Unsolved Conflict</guibutton> buttons to find "
"the remaining conflicts.)"
msgstr ""
"!!! Shranjevanje je onemogočeno, dokler niso razrešeni vsi konflikti !!! "
"(Uporabite gumb <guibutton>Pojdi na prejšnji/naslednji nerešeni spor</"
"guibutton>, da poiščete preostale spore.)"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:441
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"With only two input files every difference is also a conflict that must be "
"solved manually."
msgstr ""
"Pri samo dveh vhodnih datotekah je vsaka razlika tudi konflikt, ki ga je "
"treba rešiti ročno."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:444
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"With three input files the first file is treated as base, while the second "
"and third input files contain modifications. When at any line only either "
"input <guilabel>B</guilabel> or input <guilabel>C</guilabel> have changed "
"but not both then the changed source will automatically be selected. Only "
"when <guilabel>B</guilabel> and <guilabel>C</guilabel> have changed on the "
"same lines, then the tool detects a conflict that must be solved manually. "
"When <guilabel>B</guilabel> and <guilabel>C</guilabel> are the same, but not "
"the same as <guilabel>A</guilabel>, then <guilabel>C</guilabel> is selected."
msgstr ""
"Pri treh vhodnih datotekah se prva datoteka obravnava kot osnovna, medtem ko "
"druga in tretja vhodna datoteka vsebujeta spremembe. Če se v kateri koli "
"vrstici spremeni samo vhod <guilabel>B</guilabel> ali vhod <guilabel>C</"
"guilabel>, vendar ne oba, bo spremenjeni vir samodejno izbran. Samo ko sta "
"<guilabel>B</guilabel> in <guilabel>C</guilabel> spremenjena v istih "
"vrsticah, orodje zazna konflikt, ki ga je treba rešiti ročno. Če sta "
"<guilabel>B</guilabel> in <guilabel>C</guilabel> enaka, vendar ne enaka "
"<guilabel>A</guilabel>, je izbran <guilabel>C</guilabel>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:446
#, no-c-format
msgid "The Summary Column"
msgstr "Stolpec s povzetkom"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:446
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The merge output editor window also has a summary column on the left. It "
"shows the letter of the input from which a line was selected or nothing if "
"all three sources where equal on a line. For conflicts it shows a "
"questionmark \"?\" and the line shows \"&lt;Merge Conflict&gt;\", all in "
"red. Because solving conflicts line by line would take very long, the lines "
"are grouped into groups that have the same difference and conflict "
"characteristics. But only-white-space-conflicts are separated from non-white-"
"space-conflicts in order to ease the merging of files were the indentation "
"changed for many lines."
msgstr ""
"Okno urejevalnika zlitih izhodov ima na levi tudi stolpec s povzetkom. "
"Prikazuje črko vnosa, iz katerega je bila izbrana vrstica, ali nič, če so "
"vsi trije viri enaki v vrstici. Za spore prikaže vprašaj \"?\" in vrstica "
"prikazuje \"&lt;Konflikt združevanja&gt;\", vse rdeče. Ker bi reševanje "
"konfliktov vrstico za vrstico trajalo zelo dolgo, so vrstice združene v "
"skupine, ki imajo enake razlike in značilnosti konflikta. Toda konflikti "
"samo-belega-prostora so ločeni od sporov, ki niso-belega-prostora, da bi "
"olajšali združevanje datotek, če se je zamik spremenil za veliko vrstic."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:456
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Setting The Current Group And Synchronising Merge And Diff View Position"
msgstr ""
"Nastavitev trenutne skupine in sinhronizacija položaja pogleda zlivanja in "
"razlike"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:456
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When clicking into the summary column with the &LMB; in either window then "
"the beginning of the group belonging to that line will shown in all windows. "
"This group then becomes the \"current group\". It is highlighted with the "
"<guilabel>Current range diff background color</guilabel> option of "
"<guilabel>Integration</guilabel> item in the settings dialog and a black bar "
"appears on the left side of the text."
msgstr ""
"Ko kliknete na stolpec s povzetkom z &LMB; v katerem koli oknu, bo začetek "
"skupine, ki pripada tej vrstici, prikazan v vseh oknih. Ta skupina nato "
"postane \"Trenutna skupina\". Označeno je z možnostjo <guilabel>Barva ozadja "
"razlike v trenutnem območju</guilabel> elementa <guilabel>Integracija</"
"guilabel> v pogovornem oknu z nastavitvami, na levi strani besedila pa se "
"prikaže črna vrstica."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:458
#, no-c-format
msgid "Choosing Inputs A, B or C For Current Conflict And Editing"
msgstr "Izbira vnosov A, B ali C za trenutni konflikt in urejanje"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:458
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The Button bar below the menubar contains three input selector buttons "
"containing the letters <guilabel>A</guilabel>, <guilabel>B</guilabel> and "
"<guilabel>C</guilabel>. Click the input selector button to insert (or remove "
"if already inserted) the lines from the respective source. To choose the "
"lines from several inputs click the respective buttons in the needed order. "
"For example if you want that the lines from <guilabel>B</guilabel> appear "
"before the lines from <guilabel>A</guilabel> in the output, first click "
"<guilabel>B</guilabel>, then <guilabel>A</guilabel>."
msgstr ""
"Vrstica z gumbi pod menijsko vrstico vsebuje tri gumbe za izbiro vnosa, ki "
"vsebujejo črke <guilabel>A</guilabel>, <guilabel>B</guilabel> in "
"<guilabel>C</guilabel>. Kliknite gumb za izbiro vnosa, da vstavite (ali "
"odstranite, če so že vstavljene) vrstice iz ustreznega vira. Če želite "
"izbrati vrstice iz več vnosov, kliknite ustrezne gumbe v želenem vrstnem "
"redu. Na primer, če želite, da se vrstice iz <guilabel>B</guilabel> "
"prikažejo pred vrsticami iz <guilabel>A</guilabel> v izpisu, najprej "
"kliknite <guilabel>B</guilabel>, nato <guilabel>A </guilabel>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:460
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you use the <guibutton>Automatically Go to Next Unsolved Conflict After "
"Source Selection</guibutton> button (see <link linkend=\"autoadvance\">Auto-"
"Advance</link> section), you should disable this before choosing lines from "
"several inputs or if you want to edit the lines after your choice. Otherwise "
"&kdiff3; will jump to the next conflict after choosing the first input."
msgstr ""
"Če uporabljate gumb <guibutton>Samodejno pojdi na naslednji nerešeni spor po "
"izbiri vira</guibutton> (glejte razdelek <link linkend=\"autoadvance"
"\">Samodejno napredovanje</link>), to onemogočite, preden izberete vrstice "
"iz več vnose ali če želite urediti vrstice po vaši izbiri. V nasprotnem "
"primeru &kdiff3; bo po izbiri prvega vnosa skočil na naslednji konflikt."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:462
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"It is often helpful directly edit the merge output. The summary column will "
"show \"m\" for every line that was manually modified. When for instance the "
"differences are aligned in a way that simply choosing the inputs won't be "
"satisfactory, then you can mark the needed text and use normal <link linkend="
"\"selections\">copy and paste</link> to put it into the merge output."
msgstr ""
"Pogosto je koristno neposredno urediti zliti izhod. Stolpec s povzetkom bo "
"pokazal \"m\" za vsako vrstico, ki je bila ročno spremenjena. Ko so na "
"primer razlike poravnane tako, da preprosto izbiranje vnosov ne bo "
"zadovoljivo, potem lahko označite potrebno besedilo in uporabite običajno "
"<link linkend=\"selections\">kopiraj in prilepi</link>, da ga vstavite v "
"izhod zlivanja."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:468
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Sometimes, when a line is removed either by automatic merge or by editing "
"and no other lines remain in that group, then the text &lt;No src line&gt; "
"will appear in that line. This is just a placeholder for the group for when "
"you might change your mind and select some source again. This text won't "
"appear in the saved file or in any selections you want to copy and paste."
msgstr ""
"Včasih, ko je vrstica odstranjena s samodejnim zlivanjem ali urejanjem in v "
"tej skupini ne ostane nobena druga vrstica, se besedilo &lt;Brez izvorne "
"vrstice&gt; se prikaže v tej vrstici. To je samo nadomestni znak za skupino, "
"ko si morda premislite in znova izberete vir. To besedilo ne bo prikazano v "
"shranjeni datoteki ali v nobenem izboru, ki ga želite kopirati in prilepiti."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:474
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The text \"&lt;Merge Conflict&gt;\" will appear in the clipboard if you copy "
"and paste some text containing such a line. But still be careful to do so."
msgstr ""
"Besedilo \"&lt;Conflikt zlivanja&gt;\" se prikaže v odložišču, če kopirate "
"in prilepite besedilo, ki vsebuje takšno vrstico. Vendar bodite pri tem "
"previdni."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:478
#, no-c-format
msgid "Choosing Input A, B, or C for All Conflicts"
msgstr "Izbira vnosa A, B ali C za vse konflikte"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:478
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The normal merge will start by solving simple conflicts automatically. But "
"the <guimenu>Merge</guimenu> menu provides some actions for other common "
"needs. If you have to select the same source for most conflicts, then you "
"can choose <guilabel>A</guilabel>, <guilabel>B</guilabel> or <guilabel>C</"
"guilabel> everywhere, or only for the remaining unsolved conflicts, or for "
"unsolved white space conflicts. If you want to decide every single delta "
"yourself, you can <guimenuitem>Set Deltas to Conflicts</guimenuitem>. Or if "
"you want to return to the automatic choices of &kdiff3; then select "
"<guimenuitem>Automatically Solve Simple Conflicts</guimenuitem>. &kdiff3; "
"then restarts the merge. For actions that change your previous modifications "
"&kdiff3; will ask for your confirmation before proceeding."
msgstr ""
"Običajno združevanje se bo začelo s samodejnim reševanjem preprostih sporov. "
"Toda meni <guimenu>Združi</guimenu> ponuja nekaj dejanj za druge pogoste "
"potrebe. Če morate za večino sporov izbrati isti vir, potem lahko povsod "
"izberete <guilabel>A</guilabel>, <guilabel>B</guilabel> ali <guilabel>C</"
"guilabel> ali samo za preostale nerešene konflikte ali za nerešene konflikte "
"praznega prostora. Če želite sami določiti vsako posamezno delto, lahko "
"<guimenuitem>nastavite delte na konflikte</guimenuitem>. Ali če se želite "
"vrniti na samodejne izbire &kdiff3; nato izberite <guimenuitem>Samodejno "
"razreši preproste spore</guimenuitem>. &kdiff3; nato znova zažene "
"združevanje. Za dejanja, ki spremenijo vaše prejšnje spremembe &kdiff3; bo "
"pred nadaljevanjem zahteval vašo potrditev."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:480
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When choosing either source for unsolved white space conflicts and the "
"<guilabel>Ignore numbers (treat as white space)</guilabel> or "
"<guilabel>Ignore C/C++ comments (treat as white space)</guilabel> options at "
"<guilabel>Diff</guilabel> item in the settings dialog are used then changes "
"in numbers or comments will be treated like white space too."
msgstr ""
"Pri izbiri katerega koli vira za nerešene konflikte praznega prostora in "
"možnosti <guilabel>Prezri številke (obravnavaj kot presledek)</guilabel> ali "
"<guilabel>Prezri komentarje C/C++ (obravnavaj kot presledek)</guilabel> na "
"<guilabel> Diff</guilabel> v pogovornem oknu z nastavitvami se uporabijo, "
"potem bodo spremembe v številkah ali komentarjih prav tako obravnavane kot "
"prazen prostor."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:483
#, no-c-format
msgid "Automatic Merge of Version Control Keywords and History (Log)"
msgstr ""
"Samodejno spajanje ključnih besed in zgodovine nadzora različic (dnevnik)"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:483
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Many version control systems support special keywords in the file. (&eg; "
"\"<literal>&#36;Date&#36;</literal>\", \"<literal>&#36;Header&#36;</literal>"
"\", \"<literal>&#36;Author&#36;</literal>\", \"<literal>&#36;Log&#36;</"
"literal>\", &etc;) During the check-in the version control system (VCS) "
"changes these lines. For instance \"<literal>&#36;Date&#36;</literal>\" will "
"turn into \"<literal>&#36;Date: 2005/03/22 18:45:01 &#36;</literal>\". Since "
"this line will be different in every version of the file, it would require "
"manual interaction during the merge."
msgstr ""
"Mnogi sistemi za nadzor različic podpirajo posebne ključne besede v "
"datoteki. (&eg; \"<literal>&#36;Datum&#36;</literal>\", \"<literal>&#36;"
"Glava&#36;</literal>\", \"<literal>&#36;Avtor&#36;</literal>\", "
"\"<literal>&#36;Dnevnik&#36;</literal>\", &etc;) Med prijavo sistem za "
"nadzor različic (VCS) spremeni te vrstice. Na primer \"<literal>&#36;"
"Datum&#36;</literal>\" se bo spremenil v \"<literal>&#36;Datum: 2005/03/22 "
"18:45:01 &#36;</literal>\". Ker bo ta vrstica v vsaki različici datoteke "
"drugačna, bo med združevanjem zahtevala ročno interakcijo."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:485
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kdiff3; offers automatic merge for these items at <guilabel>Merge</"
"guilabel> item in the settings dialog. For simple lines that match the "
"<guilabel>Auto merge regular expression</guilabel> option in all input-files "
"&kdiff3; will choose the line from <guilabel>B</guilabel> or - if available "
"- from <guilabel>C</guilabel>. (Additionally it is necessary that the lines "
"in question line up in the comparison and the previous line contains no "
"conflict.) This auto merge can either be run immediately after a merge "
"starts (activate the option <guilabel>Run regular expression auto merge on "
"merge start</guilabel>) or later via <menuchoice><guimenu>Merge</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Run Regular Expression Auto Merge</guimenuitem></"
"menuchoice> menu item."
msgstr ""
"&kdiff3; ponuja samodejno združevanje za te elemente pri elementu "
"<guilabel>Združi</guilabel> v pogovornem oknu z nastavitvami. Za preproste "
"vrstice, ki se ujemajo z možnostjo <guilabel>Samodejno združevanje "
"regularnega izraza</guilabel> v vseh vhodnih datotekah &kdiff3; bo izbral "
"vrstico iz <guilabel>B</guilabel> ali - če je na voljo - iz <guilabel>C</"
"guilabel>. (Poleg tega je potrebno, da se zadevne vrstice pri primerjavi "
"ujemajo in da prejšnja vrstica ne vsebuje spora.) To samodejno združevanje "
"je mogoče zagnati takoj po začetku združevanja (aktivirajte možnost "
"<guilabel>Zaženi samodejno združevanje regularnega izraza ob združevanju "
"zagon</guilabel>) ali pozneje prek menijske postavke "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>Združi</guimenu><guimenuitem>Zaženi samodejno "
"združevanje regularnega izraza</guimenuitem></menuchoice>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:487
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Automatic merge for version control history (also called \"log\") is also "
"supported. The history auto-merge can either run immediately when the merge "
"starts by activating the option <guilabel>Merge version control history on "
"merge start</guilabel> at <guilabel>Merge</guilabel> item in the settings "
"dialog or later via the <menuchoice><guimenu>Merge</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Automatically Solve History Conflicts</guimenuitem></"
"menuchoice> menu item."
msgstr ""
"Podprto je tudi samodejno združevanje za zgodovino nadzora različic "
"(imenovano tudi \"dnevnik\"). Samodejno združevanje zgodovine se lahko "
"zažene takoj, ko se združevanje začne, tako da aktivirate možnost "
"<guilabel>Združi zgodovino nadzora različic ob začetku združevanja</"
"guilabel> pri elementu <guilabel>Združi</guilabel> v pogovornem oknu z "
"nastavitvami ali pozneje prek <menuchoice><guimenu>Združi</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Samodejno razreši zgodovinske konflikte</guimenuitem></"
"menuchoice> menijski element."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:489
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Usually the version control history begins with a line containing the "
"keyword \"<literal>&#36;Log&#36;</literal>\". This must be matched by the "
"<guilabel>History start regular expression:</guilabel> option. &kdiff3; "
"detects which subsequent lines are in the history by analysing the leading "
"characters that came before the \"<literal>&#36;Log&#36;</literal>\" "
"keyword. If the same \"leading comment\" characters also appears in the "
"following lines, then they are also included in the history."
msgstr ""
"Običajno se zgodovina nadzora različic začne z vrstico, ki vsebuje ključno "
"besedo \"<literal>&#36;Log&#36;</literal>\". To se mora ujemati z možnostjo "
"<guilabel>Regularni izraz za začetek zgodovine:</guilabel>. &kdiff3; zazna, "
"katere naslednje vrstice so v zgodovini, tako da analizira glavne znake, ki "
"so bili pred ključno besedo \"<literal>&#36;Log&#36;</literal>\". Če se v "
"naslednjih vrsticah pojavijo isti znaki \"vodilnega komentarja\", so prav "
"tako vključeni v zgodovino."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:491
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"During each check-in the VCS writes a unique line specifying version-, date- "
"and time-information followed by lines with user comments. These lines form "
"one history-entry. This history section grows with every check-in and the "
"most recent entries appear at the top (after the history start line)."
msgstr ""
"Med vsako prijavo VCS zapiše edinstveno vrstico, ki določa podatke o "
"različici, datumu in času, ki jim sledijo vrstice s komentarji uporabnikov. "
"Te vrstice tvorijo en vnos zgodovine. Ta razdelek z zgodovino se poveča z "
"vsako prijavo in najnovejši vnosi so prikazani na vrhu (za začetno vrstico "
"zgodovine)."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:496
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When for parallel development two or more developers check-in a branch of "
"the file then the merge history will contain several entries that appear as "
"conflicts during the merge of the branches. Since merging these can become "
"very tedious, &kdiff3; offers support with two possible strategies: Just "
"insert the history information from both contributors at the top or sort the "
"history information by a user defined key."
msgstr ""
"Ko za vzporedni razvoj dva ali več razvijalcev prijavi vejo datoteke, bo "
"zgodovina združevanja vsebovala več vnosov, ki se med združevanjem vej "
"prikažejo kot spori. Ker lahko njihovo združevanje postane zelo dolgočasno, "
"&kdiff3; ponuja podporo z dvema možnima strategijama: samo vstavite podatke "
"o zgodovini obeh sodelavcev na vrh ali razvrstite informacije o zgodovini po "
"uporabniško določenem ključu."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:502
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The just-insert-all-entries-method is easier to configure. &kdiff3; just "
"needs a method to detect, which lines belong to one history entry. Most VCS "
"insert an empty line after each history entry. If there are no other empty "
"lines, this is a sufficient criterion for &kdiff3;. Just set an empty "
"<guilabel>History entry start regular expression</guilabel> at "
"<guilabel>Merge</guilabel> item in the settings dialog. If the empty line "
"criterion isn't sufficient, you can specify a regular expression to detect "
"the history entry start."
msgstr ""
"Metodo samo vstavi vse vnose je lažje konfigurirati. &kdiff3; potrebuje le "
"metodo za odkrivanje, katere vrstice pripadajo enemu vnosu v zgodovino. "
"Večina VCS vstavi prazno vrstico za vsakim vnosom v zgodovino. Če ni drugih "
"praznih vrstic, je to zadosten kriterij za &kdiff3;. Samo nastavite prazen "
"<guilabel>regularni izraz za začetek vnosa v zgodovino</guilabel> pri "
"elementu <guilabel>Spoji</guilabel> v pogovornem oknu z nastavitvami. Če "
"kriterij prazne vrstice ne zadostuje, lahko podate regularni izraz za "
"zaznavanje začetka vnosa v zgodovino."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:504
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Note that &kdiff3; will remove duplicate history entries. If a history entry "
"appeared several times in the history of a input file, only one entry will "
"remain in the output."
msgstr ""
"Upoštevajte, da bo &kdiff3; odstranil podvojene vnose v zgodovino. Če se "
"zgodovinski vnos pojavi večkrat v zgodovini vhodne datoteke, bo v izhodu "
"ostal samo en vnos."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:507
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you want to sort the history, then you have to specify how the sort key "
"should be built. Use parentheses in the <guilabel>History entry start "
"regular expression</guilabel> at <guilabel>Merge</guilabel> item in the "
"settings dialog to group parts of the regular expression that should later "
"be used for the sort key. Then specify the <guilabel>History entry start "
"sort key order</guilabel> option specifying a comma \",\" separated list of "
"numbers referring to the position of the group in the regular expression."
msgstr ""
"Če želite razvrstiti zgodovino, morate določiti, kako naj bo ključ za "
"razvrščanje zgrajen. Uporabite oklepaje v <guilabel>Začetek regularnega "
"izraza v zgodovini</guilabel> pri elementu <guilabel>Spoji</guilabel> v "
"pogovornem oknu z nastavitvami, da združite dele regularnega izraza, ki naj "
"se pozneje uporabijo za ključ za razvrščanje. Nato določite možnost "
"<guilabel>Začetek vrstnega reda razvrščanja vnosa v zgodovino</guilabel> z "
"navedbo z vejico \",\" ločenega seznama številk, ki se nanašajo na položaj "
"skupine v regularnem izrazu."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:509
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Because this is not so easy to get right immediately, you are able to test "
"and improve the regular expressions and key-generation in a dedicated dialog "
"by pressing the <guibutton>Test your regular expressions</guibutton> button."
msgstr ""
"Ker tega ni tako enostavno narediti takoj, lahko preizkusite in izboljšate "
"regularne izraze in generiranje ključev v namenskem pogovornem oknu s "
"pritiskom na gumb <guibutton>Preizkusite svoje regularne izraze</guibutton>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:511
#, no-c-format
msgid "Example: Assume a history that looks like this:"
msgstr "Primer: Predpostavimo, da je zgodovina videti takole:"

#. Tag: screen
#: index.docbook:513
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"/**************************************************************************\n"
"** HISTORY:    &#36;Log: \\toms_merge_main_view\\MyApplication\\src"
"\\complexalgorithm.cpp &#36;\n"
"**\n"
"**     \\main\\integration_branch_12   2 Apr 2001 10:45:41   tom\n"
"**  Merged branch simon_branch_15.\n"
"**\n"
"**     \\main\\henry_bugfix_branch_7\\1   30 Mar 2001 19:22:05   henry\n"
"**  Improved the speed for subroutine convertToMesh().\n"
"**  Fixed crash.\n"
"**************************************************************************/"
msgstr ""
"/**************************************************************************\n"
"** HISTORY:    &#36;Log: \\toms_merge_main_view\\MyApplication\\src"
"\\complexalgorithm.cpp &#36;\n"
"**\n"
"**     \\main\\integration_branch_12   2 Apr 2001 10:45:41   tom\n"
"**  Merged branch simon_branch_15.\n"
"**\n"
"**     \\main\\henry_bugfix_branch_7\\1   30 Mar 2001 19:22:05   henry\n"
"**  Improved the speed for subroutine convertToMesh().\n"
"**  Fixed crash.\n"
"**************************************************************************/"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:514
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The history start line matches the regular expression \"<literal>.*\\&#36;"
"Log.*\\&#36;.*</literal>\". Then follow the history entries."
msgstr ""
"Začetna vrstica zgodovine se ujema z regularnim izrazom \"<literal>.*\\&#36;"
"Log.*\\&#36;.*</literal>\". Nato sledi vnosom v zgodovino."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:516
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The line with the \"<literal>&#36;Log&#36;</literal>\" keyword begins with "
"two \"*\" after which follows a space. &kdiff3; uses the first non-white-"
"space string as \"leading comment\" and assumes that the history ends in the "
"first line without this leading comment. In this example the last line ends "
"with a string that also starts with two \"*\", but instead of a space "
"character more \"*\" follow. Hence this line ends the history."
msgstr ""
"Vrstica s ključno besedo »<literal>&#36;Log&#36;</literal>« se začne z dvema "
"»*«, ki jima sledi presledek. &kdiff3; uporablja prvi niz brez presledka kot "
"\"uvodni komentar\" in predpostavlja, da se zgodovina konča v prvi vrstici "
"brez tega uvodnega komentarja. V tem primeru se zadnja vrstica konča z "
"nizom, ki se prav tako začne z dvema \"*\", vendar namesto presledka sledi "
"več \"*\". Zato ta vrstica konča zgodovino."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:518
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If history sorting isn't required then the history entry start line regular "
"expression could look like this. (This line is split in two because it "
"wouldn't fit otherwise.)"
msgstr ""
"Če razvrščanje zgodovine ni potrebno, bi lahko regularni izraz začetne "
"vrstice vnosa zgodovine izgledal takole. (Ta vrstica je razdeljena na dva "
"dela, ker drugače ne bi ustrezala.)"

#. Tag: screen
#: index.docbook:522
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\\s*\\\\main\\\\\\S+\\s+[0-9]+ (Jan|Feb|Mar|Apr|May|Jun|Jul|Aug|Sep|Oct|Nov|"
"Dec)\n"
" [0-9][0-9][0-9][0-9] [0-9][0-9]:[0-9][0-9]:[0-9][0-9]\\s+.*"
msgstr ""
"\\s*\\\\main\\\\\\S+\\s+[0-9]+ (Jan|Feb|Mar|Apr|May|Jun|Jul|Aug|Sep|Oct|Nov|"
"Dec)\n"
" [0-9][0-9][0-9][0-9] [0-9][0-9]:[0-9][0-9]:[0-9][0-9]\\s+.*"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:523
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For details about regular expressions please see the <ulink url=\"https://"
"doc.qt.io/qt-5/qregularexpression.html\">regular expression documentation</"
"ulink>. Note that \"<literal>\\s</literal>\" (with lowercase \"<literal>s</"
"literal>\") matches any white space and \"<literal>\\S</literal>\" (with "
"uppercase \"<literal>S</literal>\") matches any non-white-space. In our "
"example the history entry start contains first the version info with reg. "
"exp. \"<literal>\\\\main\\\\\\S+</literal>\", the date consisting of day "
"\"<literal>[0-9]+</literal>\", month \"<literal>(Jan|Feb|Mar|Apr|May|Jun|Jul|"
"Aug|Sep|Oct|Nov|Dec)</literal>\" and year \"<literal>[0-9][0-9][0-9][0-9]</"
"literal>\", the time \"<literal>[0-9][0-9]:[0-9][0-9]:[0-9][0-9]</literal>\" "
"and finally the developers login name \"<literal>.*</literal>\"."
msgstr ""
"Za podrobnosti o regularnih izrazih glejte <ulink url=\"https://doc.qt.io/"
"qt-5/qregularexpression.html\">dokumentacijo o regularnih izrazih</ulink>. "
"Upoštevajte, da se \"<literal>\\s</literal>\" (z malimi črkami \"<literal>s</"
"literal>\") ujema s katerim koli presledkom in \"<literal>\\S</literal>\" (z "
"velikimi črkami \"<literal>S</literal>\") se ujema s katerim koli ne-belim "
"prostorom. V našem primeru začetek vnosa zgodovine vsebuje najprej "
"informacije o različici z reg. exp. \"<literal>\\\\main\\\\\\S+</literal>, "
"datum, sestavljen iz dneva \"<literal>[0-9]+</literal>\", meseca "
"\"<literal>(Jan|Feb|Mar|Apr|May|Jun|Jul|Aug|Sep|Oct|Nov|Dec)</literal>\" in "
"leto \"<literal>[0-9][0-9][0-9][ 0-9]</literal>\", čas \"<literal>[0-9][0-9]:"
"[0-9][0-9]:[0-9][0-9]</literal>\" in končno prijavno ime razvijalca "
"\"<literal>.*</literal>\"."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:525
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Note that the \"leading comment\" characters (in the example \"<literal>**</"
"literal>\") will already be removed by &kdiff3; before trying to match, "
"hence the regular expression begins with a match for none or more white-"
"space characters \"<literal>\\s*</literal>\". Because comment characters can "
"differ in each file (&eg; C/C++ uses other comment characters than a Perl "
"script) &kdiff3; takes care of the leading comment characters and you should "
"not specify them in the regular expression."
msgstr ""
"Upoštevajte, da bodo znaki \"uvodnega komentarja\" (v primeru \"<literal>**</"
"literal>\") že odstranjeni s &kdiff3; pred poskusom ujemanja, se zato "
"regularni izraz začne z ujemanjem za nobenega ali več znakov belega prostora"
"\"<literal>\\s*</literal>\". Ker se znaki komentarjev lahko razlikujejo v "
"vsaki datoteki (&eg; C/C++ uporablja druge znake komentarjev kot skript "
"Perl), &kdiff3; skrbi za glavne znake komentarjev in jih ne bi smeli "
"podajati v regularnem izrazu."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:527
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you require a sorted history. Then the sortkey must be calculated. For "
"this the relevant parts in the regular expression must be grouped by "
"parentheses. (The extra parentheses can also stay in if history sorting is "
"disabled.)"
msgstr ""
"Če potrebujete urejeno zgodovino. Nato je treba izračunati sortkey. Za to "
"morajo biti ustrezni deli v regularnem izrazu združeni v oklepaje. (Dodatni "
"oklepaji lahko tudi ostanejo, če je razvrščanje zgodovine onemogočeno.)"

#. Tag: screen
#: index.docbook:532
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\\s*\\\\main\\\\(\\S+)\\s+([0-9]+) (Jan|Feb|Mar|Apr|May|Jun|Jul|Aug|Sep|Oct|"
"Nov|Dec)\n"
" ([0-9][0-9][0-9][0-9]) ([0-9][0-9]:[0-9][0-9]:[0-9][0-9])\\s+(.*)"
msgstr ""
"\\s*\\\\main\\\\(\\S+)\\s+([0-9]+) (Jan|Feb|Mar|Apr|May|Jun|Jul|Aug|Sep|Oct|"
"Nov|Dec)\n"
" ([0-9][0-9][0-9][0-9]) ([0-9][0-9]:[0-9][0-9]:[0-9][0-9])\\s+(.*)"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:533
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The parentheses now contain <literal>1</literal>. version info, <literal>2</"
"literal>. day, <literal>3</literal>. month, <literal>4</literal>. year, "
"<literal>5</literal>. time, <literal>6</literal>. name. But if we want to "
"sort by date and time, we need to construct a key with the elements in a "
"different order of appearance: First the year, followed by month, day, time, "
"version info and name. Hence the sortkey order to specify is "
"\"<literal>4,3,2,5,1,6</literal>\"."
msgstr ""
"Oklepaji zdaj vsebujejo <literal>1</literal>. informacije o različici, "
"<literal>2</literal>. dan, <literal>3</literal>. mesec, <literal>4</"
"literal>. leto, <literal>5</literal>. čas, <literal>6</literal>. ime. Če pa "
"želimo razvrščati po datumu in času, moramo sestaviti ključ z elementi v "
"drugačnem vrstnem redu: najprej leto, sledijo mesec, dan, čas, informacije o "
"različici in ime. Zato je vrstni red ključev za razvrščanje, ki ga je treba "
"določiti, \"<literal>4,3,2,5,1,6</literal>\"."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:537
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Because month names aren't good for sorting (\"<literal>Apr</literal>\" "
"would be first) &kdiff3; detects in which order the month names were given "
"and uses that number instead (\"<literal>Apr</literal>\" -&gt; "
"\"<literal>04</literal>\"). And if a pure number is found it will be "
"transformed to a 4-digit value with leading zeros for sorting. Finally the "
"resulting sort key for the first history entry start line will be:"
msgstr ""
"Ker imena mesecev niso dobra za razvrščanje (\"<literal>Apr</literal>\" bi "
"bil prvi) &kdiff3; zazna, v katerem vrstnem redu so bila navedena imena "
"mesecev, in namesto tega uporabi to številko (\"<literal>Apr</literal>\" -"
"&gt; \"<literal>04</literal>\"). In če je najdeno čisto število, bo "
"pretvorjeno v 4-mestno vrednost z začetnimi ničlami za razvrščanje. Končno "
"bo dobljeni ključ za razvrščanje za prvo začetno vrstico vnosa v zgodovino:"

#. Tag: screen
#: index.docbook:540
#, no-c-format
msgid "2001 04 0002 10:45:41 integration_branch_12   tom"
msgstr "2001 04 0002 10:45:41 integracija_veja_12 tom"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:541
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For more information also see <link linkend=\"mergeoptions\">Merge Settings</"
"link> section."
msgstr ""
"Za več informacij glejte tudi razdelek <link linkend=\"mergeoptions"
"\">Nastavitve združevanja</link>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:547
#, no-c-format
msgid "Navigation And Editing"
msgstr "Navigacija in urejanje"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:548
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Much navigation will be done with the scroll bars and the mouse but you can "
"also navigate with the keys. If you click into either window then you can "
"use the shortcuts &Left;, &Right;, &Up;, &Down;, &PgUp;, &PgDn;, &Home;, "
"&End;, <keycombo>&Ctrl;&Home;</keycombo> and <keycombo>&Ctrl;&End;</"
"keycombo> as you would in other programs. The overview-column next to the "
"vertical scroll bar of the input files can also be used for navigating by "
"clicking into it."
msgstr ""
"Večino navigacije boste opravili z drsniki in miško, vendar lahko krmarite "
"tudi s tipkami. Če kliknete katero koli okno, lahko uporabite bližnjice "
"&Left;, &Right;, &Up;, &Down;, &PgUp;, &PgDn;, &Home;, &End;, "
"<keycombo>&Ctrl;&Home;</keycombo> in <keycombo>&Ctrl;&End;</keycombo> kot bi "
"v drugih programih. Pregledni stolpec polegnavpičnega drsnika vhodnih "
"datotek lahko uporabite tudi za navigacijo s klikom vanjo."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:550
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can also use the <mousebutton>wheel</mousebutton> mouse to scroll up and "
"down."
msgstr ""
"Uporabite lahko tudi <mousebutton>kolesce</mousebutton> miške za pomikanje "
"navzgor in navzdol."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:552
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In the merge output editor you can also use the other keys for editing. You "
"can toggle between insert and overwrite mode with the &Ins; key. (Default is "
"insert-mode.)"
msgstr ""
"V urejevalniku spajanja izhodov lahko za urejanje uporabite tudi druge "
"tipke. Lahko preklapljate med načinoma vstavljanja in prepisovanja s tipko "
"&Ins;. (Privzete jenačin vstavljanja.)"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:556
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A click with the &LMB; into any summary column will synchronise all windows "
"to show the beginning of the same group of lines (as explained in section "
"<link linkend=\"synchronise_views\">Setting The Current Group And "
"Synchronising Merge And Diff View Position</link>)."
msgstr ""
"Klik z &LMB; v kateri koli stolpec povzetka bo sinhroniziral vsa oknaza "
"prikaz začetka iste skupine vrstic (kot je razloženo v razdelku<link linkend="
"\"synchronise_views\">Nastavitev trenutne skupine insinhroniziranje položaja "
"pogleda združevanja in razlikovanja</link>).​"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:560
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The Button bar also contains nine navigation buttons with which you can jump "
"to the current/first/last difference, to the previous/next difference "
"(<keycombo>&Ctrl;&Down;</keycombo>/<keycombo>&Ctrl;&Up;</keycombo>), to the "
"previous/next conflict (<keycombo>&Ctrl;&PgDn;</keycombo>/<keycombo>&Ctrl;"
"&PgUp;</keycombo>), or to the previous/next unsolved conflict. Note that for "
"&kdiff3; a \"conflict\" that was not automatically solved at the start of "
"the merge stays a \"conflict\" even if it is solved. Hence the necessity to "
"distinguish \"unsolved conflicts\"."
msgstr ""
"Vrstica z gumbi vsebuje tudi devet navigacijskih gumbov, s katerimi lahko "
"skačetena trenutno/prvo/zadnjo razliko, na prejšnjo/naslednjo razliko "
"(<keycombo>&Ctrl;&Down;</keycombo>/<keycombo>&Ctrl;&Up;</keycombo>), "
"naprejšnji/naslednji konflikt (<keycombo>&Ctrl;&PgDn;</keycombo>/"
"<keycombo>&Ctrl;&PgUp;</keycombo>) ali prejšnji/naslednji nerešen konflikt. "
"Upoštevajte, da za &kdiff3; \"konflikt\", ki ni bil samodejno rešen na "
"začetku spajanja, ostane \"konflikt\", tudi če je rešen. Zato je potreba po "
"razlikovanju \"nerešenih konfliktov\"."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:569
#, no-c-format
msgid "Auto-Advance"
msgstr "Samodejno napredovanje"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:570
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"There also is a button <guibutton>Automatically Go to Next Unsolved Conflict "
"After Source Selection</guibutton> (Auto-Advance). If you enable this, then, "
"when one source is selected, &kdiff3; will jump to and select the next "
"unsolved conflict automatically. This can help when you always want to "
"choose one source only. When you need both sources, or you want to edit "
"after selecting, then you probably want to switch this off. Before "
"proceeding to the next unsolved conflict &kdiff3; shows you the effect of "
"your choice for a short time. This delay is adjustable in the "
"<guilabel>Merge</guilabel> item in the settings dialog: You can specify the "
"<guilabel>Auto advance delay (ms):</guilabel> in milli seconds between 0 and "
"2000. Hint: Tired of many clicks? - Use a small Auto-Advance-delay and the "
"shortcuts <keycombo>&Ctrl;<keycap>1</keycap></keycombo>/<keycap>2</keycap>/"
"<keycap>3</keycap> to select <guilabel>A</guilabel>/<guilabel>B</guilabel>/"
"<guilabel>C</guilabel> for many conflicts."
msgstr ""
"Obstaja tudi gumb <guibutton>Samodejno pojdi na naslednji nerešeni spor po "
"izbiri vira</guibutton> (Samodejno napredovanje). Če to omogočite, potem ko "
"je izbran en vir, &kdiff3; samodejno skoči na in izbere naslednji nerešen "
"konflikt. To lahko pomaga, ko želite vedno izbrati samo en vir. Ko "
"potrebujete oba vira ali želite urediti po izbiri, boste to verjetno želeli "
"izklopiti. Preden nadaljujete do naslednjega nerešenega spora &kdiff3; vam "
"za kratek čas pokaže učinek vaše izbire. Ta zakasnitev je nastavljiva v "
"elementu <guilabel>Združi</guilabel> v pogovornem oknu z nastavitvami: "
"Določite lahko <guilabel>Zakasnitev samodejnega napredovanja (ms):</"
"guilabel> v milisekundah med 0 in 2000. Namig: Utrujen od veliko klikov? - "
"Uporabite majhen zamik samodejnega napredovanja in bližnjice <keycombo>&Ctrl;"
"<keycap>1</keycap></keycombo>/<keycap>2</keycap>/<keycap>3</keycap>, da "
"izberete <guilabel>A</guilabel>/<guilabel>B</guilabel>/<guilabel>C</"
"guilabel> za številne konflikte."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:587
#, no-c-format
msgid "Select, Copy And Paste"
msgstr "Izberi, kopiraj in prilepi"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:588
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The input windows don't show a cursor, so selections must be made with the "
"mouse by clicking with the &RMB; at the start, holding down the mousebutton "
"and moving to the end, where you release the mouse button again. You can "
"also select a word by double clicking it. In the merge output editor you can "
"also select via the keyboard by holding the &Shift; key and navigation with "
"the cursor keys."
msgstr ""
"Okna za vnos ne prikazujejo kazalca, zato je treba izbire opraviti z miško s "
"klikom z &RMB; na začetku, držite tipko miške in se pomaknite do konca, kjer "
"znova spustite tipko miške. Besedo lahko izberete tudi tako, da jo dvakrat "
"kliknete. V urejevalniku spajanja izpisov lahko izberete tudi prek "
"tipkovnice tako, da držite &Shift; in navigacijo s smernimi tipkami."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:595
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If the selection exceeds the visible range you can move the mouse over the "
"window borders which causes &kdiff3; to scroll in that direction."
msgstr ""
"Če izbor presega vidni obseg, lahko premaknete miško čez meje okna, kar "
"povzroči &kdiff3; da se pomakne v to smer."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:598
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For very large selections you can also use the navigation keys while holding "
"down the mouse. E.g. use &PgUp; and &PgDn; to quickly go to a certain "
"position. At the end position release the mouse button."
msgstr ""
"Za zelo velike izbire lahko uporabite tudi navigacijske tipke, medtem ko "
"držite miško. Npr. uporabite &PgUp; in &PgDn; za hiter prehod na določen "
"položaj. Na končnem položaju spustite gumb miške."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:602
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In order to select everything in the current window use "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>Edit</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Select All</guimenuitem></"
"menuchoice> menu item (<keycombo>&Ctrl;<keycap>A</keycap></keycombo>)."
msgstr ""
"Če želite izbrati vse v trenutnem oknu, uporabite menijski element "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>Uredi</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Izberi vse</guimenuitem></"
"menuchoice> (<keycombo>&Ctrl;<keycap>A</keycap> </keycombo>)."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:605
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To copy to the clipboard you must press the <guibutton>Copy</guibutton> "
"button (<keycombo>&Ctrl;<keycap>C</keycap></keycombo> or <keycombo>&Ctrl;"
"&Ins;</keycombo>). But there exists an option <guilabel>Auto copy selection</"
"guilabel> at <guilabel>Editor</guilabel> item in the settings dialog. If "
"this is enabled, then whatever you select is copied immediately and you "
"don't need to explicitly copy. But pay attention when using this because the "
"contents of the clipboard might then be destroyed accidentally."
msgstr ""
"Za kopiranje v odložišče morate pritisniti gumb <guibutton>Kopiraj</"
"guibutton> (<keycombo>&Ctrl;<keycap>C</keycap></keycombo> ali "
"<keycombo>&Ctrl;&Ins;</keycombo>). Obstaja pa možnost <guilabel>Izbira "
"samodejnega kopiranja</guilabel> pri elementu <guilabel>Urejevalnik</"
"guilabel> v pogovornem oknu z nastavitvami. Če je to omogočeno, se vse, kar "
"izberete, takoj kopira in vam ni treba izrecno kopirati. Toda pri uporabi "
"bodite pozorni, ker se lahko vsebina odložišča po nesreči uniči."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:607
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<guibutton>Cut</guibutton> (<keycombo>&Ctrl;<keycap>X</keycap></keycombo> or "
"<keycombo>&Shift;&Del;</keycombo>) copies to the clipboard and deletes the "
"selected text."
msgstr ""
"<guibutton>Izreži</guibutton> (<keycombo>&Ctrl;<keycap>X</keycap></keycombo> "
"ali <keycombo>&Shift;&Del;</keycombo>) kopira v odložišče in izbriše izbrano "
"besedilo."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:609
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<guibutton>Paste</guibutton> (<keycombo>&Ctrl;<keycap>V</keycap></keycombo> "
"or <keycombo>&Shift;&Ins;</keycombo>) inserts the text in the clipboard at "
"the cursorposition or over the current selection. If you paste to either "
"diff input window the contents of the clipboard will be shown in that window "
"and the comparison will restart immediately. This is useful if you want to "
"quickly grab a piece of text from somewhere and compare it with something "
"else without first creating files."
msgstr ""
"<guibutton>Prilepi</guibutton> (<keycombo>&Ctrl;<keycap>V</keycap></"
"keycombo> ali <keycombo>&Shift;&Ins;</keycombo>) vstavi besedilo v odložišče "
"na položaj kazalca ali čez trenutni izbor. Če prilepite v katero koli okno "
"za vnos razlike, bo vsebina odložišča prikazana v tem oknu in primerjava se "
"bo takoj znova začela. To je uporabno, če želite od nekje hitro zagrabiti "
"del besedila in ga primerjati z nečim drugim, ne da bi prej ustvarili "
"datoteke."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:619
#, no-c-format
msgid "Saving"
msgstr "Shranjevanje"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:620
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Saving will only be allowed, when all conflicts were solved. If the file "
"already exists and the <guilabel>Backup files</guilabel> option is enabled "
"at <guilabel>Folder</guilabel> item in the settings dialog then the existing "
"file will be renamed with an <literal role=\"extension\">.orig</literal> "
"extension, but if such a file exists it will be deleted. When you exit or "
"start another diff-analysis and data wasn't saved yet, then &kdiff3; will "
"ask if you want to save, cancel or proceed without saving. (&kdiff3; does "
"not catch any signals. So if you \"kill\" a &kdiff3; instance then your data "
"will be lost.)"
msgstr ""
"Shranjevanje bo dovoljeno šele, ko bodo rešeni vsi konflikti. Če datoteka že "
"obstaja in je možnost <guilabel>Varnostne kopije datotek</guilabel> "
"omogočena pri elementu <guilabel>Mapa</guilabel> v pogovornem oknu z "
"nastavitvami, bo obstoječa datoteka preimenovana s <literal role=\"extension"
"\"> pripono .orig</literal>, če pa takšna datoteka obstaja, bo izbrisana. Ko "
"zaprete ali začnete drugo diff-analizo in podatki še niso bili shranjeni, "
"potem vas bo &kdiff3; vprašal, ali želite shraniti, preklicati ali "
"nadaljevati brez shranjevanja. (&kdiff3; ne lovi nobenih signalov. Torej, če "
"\"ubijete\" pojavek &kdiff3;, bodo vaši podatki izgubljeni.)"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:622
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Line endings are saved according to the normal method on the underlying "
"operating system. For Unices each line ends with an linefeed-character "
"\"<literal>\\n</literal>\", while for Win32-based systems each line ends "
"with a carriage-return + a linefeed \"<literal>\\r\\n</literal>\". &kdiff3; "
"does not preserve the line-endings of the input files, which also means that "
"you shouldn't use &kdiff3; with binary files."
msgstr ""
"Konci vrstic se shranijo v skladu z običajno metodo v osnovnem operacijskem "
"sistemu. Za Unixe se vsaka vrstica konča z znakom za začetek vrstice "
"\"<literal>\\n</literal>\", medtem ko se pri sistemih, ki temeljijo na "
"Win32, vsaka vrstica konča s povratnim znakom + znak za začetek vrstice "
"\"<literal>\\r\\n</literal>\". &kdiff3; ne ohrani končnic vrstic vhodnih "
"datotek, kar tudi pomeni, da ne smete uporabljati &kdiff3; z binarnimi "
"datotekami."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:627
#, no-c-format
msgid "Finding Strings"
msgstr "Iskanje nizov"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:628
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can search for a string in any text-window of &kdiff3;. The "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>Edit</guimenu><guimenuitem>Find...</guimenuitem></"
"menuchoice> menu item (<keycombo>&Ctrl;<keycap>F</keycap></keycombo>) opens "
"a dialog that lets you specify the string to search for. You can also select "
"the windows which should be searched. Searching will always start at the "
"top. Use the <menuchoice><guimenu>Edit</guimenu><guimenuitem>Find Next...</"
"guimenuitem></menuchoice> menu item (<keycap>F3</keycap>) to proceed to the "
"next occurrence. If you select to search several windows then the first "
"window will be searched from top to bottom before the search starts in the "
"next window at the top again, &etc;"
msgstr ""
"Niz lahko iščete v katerem koli besedilnem oknu &kdiff3;. Element menija "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>Uredi</guimenu><guimenuitem>Najdi...</guimenuitem></"
"menuchoice> (<keycombo>&Ctrl;<keycap>F</keycap></keycombo>) pogovorno okno, "
"v katerem lahko določite niz za iskanje. Izberete lahko tudi okna, ki jih "
"želite preiskati. Iskanje se vedno začne na vrhu. Uporabite element menija "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>Uredi</guimenu><guimenuitem>Najdi naprej ...</"
"guimenuitem></menuchoice> (<keycap>F3</keycap>), da nadaljujete do "
"naslednjega pojava. Če izberete iskanje po več oknih, bo prvo okno preiskano "
"od vrha do dna, preden se bo iskanje spet začelo v naslednjem oknu na vrhu "
"&etc;"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:633
#, no-c-format
msgid "Printing"
msgstr "Tiskanje"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:634
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kdiff3; supports printing for textfile differences. The "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>File</guimenu><guimenuitem>Print...</guimenuitem></"
"menuchoice> menu item (<keycombo>&Ctrl;<keycap>P</keycap></keycombo>) opens "
"a dialog that allows you to select the printer and to adjust other options."
msgstr ""
"&kdiff3; podpira tiskanje za razlike besedilnih datotek. Element menija "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>Datoteka</guimenu><guimenuitem>Natisni...</"
"guimenuitem></menuchoice> (<keycombo>&Ctrl;<keycap>P</keycap></keycombo>) "
"odpre pogovorno okno, v katerem lahko izberete tiskalnik in prilagodite "
"druge možnosti."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:636
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"There are several possibilities to adjust the range. Due to different "
"printing dialogs on different operating systems, the method to achieve "
"certain range selections varies."
msgstr ""
"Obstaja več možnosti za prilagajanje obsega. Zaradi različnih pogovornih "
"oken za tiskanje v različnih operacijskih sistemih se način doseganja "
"določenih izbir obsega razlikuje."

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:641
#, no-c-format
msgid "All:"
msgstr "Vse:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:641
#, no-c-format
msgid "Print everything."
msgstr "Natisni vse."

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:642
#, no-c-format
msgid "Current:"
msgstr "Trenutno:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:642
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Print a page starting at the first visible line in the window. (On systems "
"without this option this can be achieved by specifying page number 10000 for "
"printing.)"
msgstr ""
"Natisni stran, ki se začne pri prvi vidni vrstici v oknu. (V sistemih brez "
"te možnosti je to mogoče doseči z določitvijo številke strani 10000 za "
"tiskanje.)"

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:644
#, no-c-format
msgid "Selection:"
msgstr "Izbira:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:644
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Before choosing to print select text with the mouse (like for copy and "
"paste) in one of the diff input windows to define the start and end line. If "
"no text in one of the diff input windows was selected, then this won't be an "
"available choice. (On systems without this option this can be achived by "
"specifying page number 9999 for printing.)"
msgstr ""
"Preden se odločite za tiskanje, izberite besedilo z miško (kot pri kopiranju "
"in lepljenju) v enem od oken za vnos razlike, da določite začetno in končno "
"vrstico. Če v enem od oken za vnos razlike ni bilo izbrano nobeno besedilo, "
"potem to ne bo na voljo. (V sistemih brez te možnosti je to mogoče doseči z "
"določitvijo številke strani 9999 za tiskanje.)"

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:650
#, no-c-format
msgid "Range:"
msgstr "Obseg:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:650
#, no-c-format
msgid "Specify the first and last page."
msgstr "Določite prvo in zadnjo stran."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:653
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Other important options for printing will be taken from the normal options:"
msgstr "Druge pomembne možnosti za tiskanje bodo vzete iz običajnih možnosti:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:656
#, no-c-format
msgid "Font, font size"
msgstr "Pisava, velikost pisave"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:657
#, no-c-format
msgid "Show line numbers"
msgstr "Pokaži številke vrstic"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:658
#, no-c-format
msgid "Word wrap"
msgstr "Prelom besed"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:659
#, no-c-format
msgid "<para>Colors</para>"
msgstr "<para>Barve</para>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:660
#, no-c-format
msgid "&etc;"
msgstr "&etc;"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:662
#, no-c-format
msgid "Landscape formatting is also recommended for printing."
msgstr "Za tiskanje je priporočljivo tudi ležeče oblikovanje."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:667
#, no-c-format
msgid "Options"
msgstr "Možnosti"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:668
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Options and the recent-file-list will be saved when you exit the program, "
"and reloaded when you start it. (<menuchoice><guimenu>Settings</guimenu> "
"<guimenuitem>Configure &kdiff3;...</guimenuitem></menuchoice> menu item)."
msgstr ""
"Možnosti in seznam nedavnih datotek bodo shranjeni, ko zapustite program, in "
"znova naloženi, ko ga zaženete. (<menuchoice><guimenu>Nastavitve</guimenu> "
"<guimenuitem>Konfiguriraj &kdiff3;...</guimenuitem></menuchoice> menijski "
"element)."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:673
#, no-c-format
msgid "Font"
msgstr "Pisava"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:674
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Select a fixed width font. (On some systems this dialog will also present "
"variable width fonts, but you should not use them.)"
msgstr ""
"Izberite pisavo s fiksno širino. (V nekaterih sistemih bo to pogovorno okno "
"predstavilo tudi pisave spremenljive širine, vendar jih ne smete "
"uporabljati.)"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:680
#, no-c-format
msgid "<title>Colors</title>"
msgstr "<title>Barve</title>"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:682
#, no-c-format
msgid "Editor and Diff Views:"
msgstr "Pogled urejevalnika in razlike:"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:684
#, no-c-format
msgid "Foreground color:"
msgstr "Barva ospredja:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:684 index.docbook:700
#, no-c-format
msgid "Usually black."
msgstr "Ponavadi črna."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:685
#, no-c-format
msgid "Background color:"
msgstr "Barva ozadja:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:685
#, no-c-format
msgid "Usually white."
msgstr "Ponavadi bela."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:686
#, no-c-format
msgid "Diff background color:"
msgstr "Različna barva ozadja:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:686
#, no-c-format
msgid "Usually light gray."
msgstr "Ponavadi svetlo siva."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:687
#, no-c-format
msgid "Color A:"
msgstr "Barva A:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:687
#, no-c-format
msgid "Usually dark blue."
msgstr "Ponavadi temno modra."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:688
#, no-c-format
msgid "Color B:"
msgstr "Barva B:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:688
#, no-c-format
msgid "Usually dark green."
msgstr "Ponavadi temno zelena."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:689
#, no-c-format
msgid "Color C:"
msgstr "Barva C:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:689
#, no-c-format
msgid "Usually dark magenta."
msgstr "Ponavadi temna magenta."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:690
#, no-c-format
msgid "Conflict color:"
msgstr "Barva spora:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:690 index.docbook:698
#, no-c-format
msgid "Usually red."
msgstr "Običajno rdeče."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:691
#, no-c-format
msgid "Current range background color:"
msgstr "Barva ozadja trenutnega obsega:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:691
#, no-c-format
msgid "Usually light yellow."
msgstr "Ponavadi svetlo rumena."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:692
#, no-c-format
msgid "Current range diff background color:"
msgstr "Barva ozadja razlike v trenutnem območju:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:692
#, no-c-format
msgid "Usually dark yellow."
msgstr "Običajno temno rumena."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:693
#, no-c-format
msgid "Color for manually aligned difference ranges:"
msgstr "Barva za ročno poravnane razpone razlik:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:693
#, no-c-format
msgid "Usually orange."
msgstr "Običajno oranžna."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:695
#, no-c-format
msgid "Folder Comparison View:"
msgstr "Primerjalni pogled mape:"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:697
#, no-c-format
msgid "Newest file color:"
msgstr "Najnovejša barva datoteke:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:697
#, no-c-format
msgid "Usually green."
msgstr "Običajno zelena."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:698
#, no-c-format
msgid "Oldest file color:"
msgstr "Barva najstarejše datoteke:"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:699
#, no-c-format
msgid "Middle age file color:"
msgstr "Barva datoteke srednjih let:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:699
#, no-c-format
msgid "Usually strong yellow."
msgstr "Običajno močno rumena."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:700
#, no-c-format
msgid "Color for missing files:"
msgstr "Barva za manjkajoče datoteke:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:703
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Changing the colors for folder comparison will be effective only when "
"starting the next folder comparison."
msgstr ""
"Spreminjanje barv za primerjavo map bo učinkovito šele ob začetku naslednje "
"primerjave map."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:706
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"On systems with only 16 or 256 colors some colors are not available in pure "
"form. On such systems the <guibutton>Defaults</guibutton> button will choose "
"a pure color."
msgstr ""
"Pri sistemih s samo 16 ali 256 barvami nekatere barve niso na voljo v čisti "
"obliki. V takih sistemih bo gumb <guibutton>Privzeto</guibutton> izbral "
"čisto barvo."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:712
#, no-c-format
msgid "Editor Settings"
msgstr "Nastavitve urejevalnika"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:714
#, no-c-format
msgid "Tab inserts spaces"
msgstr "Tab vstavi presledke"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:714
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If this is disabled and you press the &Tab; key, a tab-character is "
"inserted, otherwise the appropriate amount of characters is inserted."
msgstr ""
"Če je to onemogočeno in pritisnete &Tab; tipko, se vstavi tabulator, sicer "
"pa ustrezno število znakov."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:717
#, no-c-format
msgid "Tab size:"
msgstr "Velikost tabulatorja:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:717
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Can be adjusted for your specific needs. Default is <literal>8</literal>."
msgstr ""
"Lahko se prilagodi vašim posebnim potrebam. Privzeto je <literal>8</literal>."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:719
#, no-c-format
msgid "Auto indentation"
msgstr "Samodejno zamikanje"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:719
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When pressing &Enter; or <keycap>Return</keycap> the indentation of the "
"previous line is used for the new line."
msgstr ""
"Ko pritisnete &Enter; ali <keycap>Return</keycap> se za novo vrstico uporabi "
"zamik prejšnje vrstice."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:722
#, no-c-format
msgid "Auto copy selection"
msgstr "Izbira samodejnega kopiranja"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:722
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Every selection is immediately copied to the clipboard when active and you "
"needn't explicitly copy it."
msgstr ""
"Vsak izbor se takoj kopira v odložišče, ko je aktiven, in vam ga ni treba "
"izrecno kopirati."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:725
#, no-c-format
msgid "Line end style:"
msgstr "Slog konca vrstice:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:725
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When saving you can select what line end style you prefer. The default "
"setting is the common choice for the used operating system."
msgstr ""
"Pri shranjevanju lahko izberete želeni slog konca črte. Privzeta nastavitev "
"je običajna izbira za uporabljeni operacijski sistem."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:731
#, no-c-format
msgid "Diff Settings"
msgstr "Diff Settings"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:732
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When comparing files, &kdiff3; first it tries to match lines that are equal "
"in all input files. Only during this step it might ignore white space. The "
"second step compares each line. In this step white space will not be "
"ignored. Also during the merge white space will not be ignored."
msgstr ""
"Pri primerjavi datotek &kdiff3; najprej poskuša ujemati vrstice, ki so enake "
"v vseh vhodnih datotekah. Samo med tem korakom lahko prezre prazen prostor. "
"Drugi korak primerja vsako vrstico. V tem koraku prazen prostor ne bo "
"prezrt. Tudi med združevanjem prazen prostor ne bo prezrt."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:740
#, no-c-format
msgid "Ignore numbers (treat as white space)"
msgstr "Ignoriraj številke (obravnavaj kot presledek)"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:740
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Default is off. Number characters ('0'-'9', '.', '-') will be ignored in the "
"first part of the analysis in which the line matching is done. In the result "
"the differences will be shown nevertheless, but they are treated as white "
"space."
msgstr ""
"Privzeto je izklopljeno. Številski znaki ('0'-'9', '.', '-') bodo prezrti v "
"prvem delu analize, v katerem se izvede ujemanje vrstic. V rezultatu bodo "
"razlike kljub temu prikazane, vendar se obravnavajo kot prazen prostor."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:745
#, no-c-format
msgid "Ignore C/C++ comments (treat as white space)"
msgstr "Prezri komentarje C/C++ (obravnavaj kot prazen prostor)"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:745
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Default is off. Changes in comments will be treated like changes in white "
"space."
msgstr ""
"Privzeto je izklopljeno. Spremembe komentarjev bodo obravnavane kot "
"spremembe praznega prostora."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:748
#, no-c-format
msgid "Ignore case (treat as white space)"
msgstr "Ignoriraj velike in male črke (obravnavaj kot beli prostor)"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:748
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Default is off. Case-differences of characters (like 'A' vs. 'a') will be "
"treated like changes in white space."
msgstr ""
"Privzeto je izklopljeno. Razlike med velikimi in malimi črkami (kot je 'A' "
"proti 'a') bodo obravnavane kot spremembe v belem prostoru."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:751 index.docbook:928
#, no-c-format
msgid "Preprocessor command:"
msgstr "Ukaz predprocesorja:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:751 index.docbook:754
#, no-c-format
msgid "See <link linkend=\"preprocessors\">next section</link>."
msgstr "Glejte <link linkend=\"preprocessors\">naslednji razdelek</link>."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:754 index.docbook:935
#, no-c-format
msgid "Line-matching preprocessor command:"
msgstr "Ukaz predprocesorja za ujemanje vrstic:"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:757
#, no-c-format
msgid "Try hard (slower)"
msgstr "Potrudi se (počasneje)"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:757
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Try hard to find an even smaller delta. (Default is on.) This will probably "
"be effective for complicated and big files. And slow for very big files."
msgstr ""
"Poskusite najti še manjšo delto. (Privzeto je vklopljeno.) To bo verjetno "
"učinkovito za zapletene in velike datoteke. In počasno za zelo velike "
"datoteke."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:761
#, no-c-format
msgid "Align B and C for 3 input files"
msgstr "Poravnajte B in C za 3 vhodne datoteke"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:761
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Try to align <guilabel>B</guilabel> and <guilabel>C</guilabel> when "
"comparing or merging three input files. Not recommended for merging because "
"merge might get more complicated. (Default is off.)"
msgstr ""
"Poskusite poravnati <guilabel>B</guilabel> in <guilabel>C</guilabel>, ko "
"primerjate ali združujete tri vhodne datoteke. Ni priporočljivo za "
"združevanje, ker je združevanje lahko bolj zapleteno. (Privzeto je "
"izklopljeno.)"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:769
#, no-c-format
msgid "Merge Settings"
msgstr "Nastavitve združevanja"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:771
#, no-c-format
msgid "Auto advance delay (ms):"
msgstr "Zakasnitev samodejnega napredovanja (ms):"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:771
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When in auto-advance-mode this setting specifies how long to show the result "
"of the selection before jumping to the next unsolved conflict."
msgstr ""
"Ko je v načinu samodejnega napredovanja, ta nastavitev določa, kako dolgo "
"naj bo prikazan rezultat izbire, preden skoči na naslednji nerešen konflikt."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:775
#, no-c-format
msgid "Show info dialogs"
msgstr "Prikaži pogovorna okna z informacijami"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:775
#, no-c-format
msgid "Show a dialog with information about the number of conflicts."
msgstr "Prikaži pogovorno okno z informacijami o številu sporov."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:778
#, no-c-format
msgid "White space 2/3-file merge default:"
msgstr "Privzeto združevanje datotek praznega prostora 2/3:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:778
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Automatically solve all white-space conflict by choosing the specified file. "
"(Default is manual choice.) Useful if white space really isn't important in "
"many files. If you need this only occasionally better use <guilabel>Choose A/"
"B/C for All Unsolved Whitespace Conflicts</guilabel> in the <guimenu>Merge</"
"guimenu> menu. Note that if you enable either <guilabel>Ignore numbers "
"(treat as white space)</guilabel> or <guilabel>Ignore C/C++ comments (treat "
"as white space)</guilabel> then this auto-choice also applies for conflicts "
"in numbers or comments."
msgstr ""
"Samodejno reši vse konflikte praznega prostora z izbiro navedene datoteke. "
"(Privzeta je ročna izbira.) Uporabno, če prazen prostor v mnogih datotekah "
"res ni pomemben. Če to potrebujete le občasno, bolje uporabite "
"<guilabel>Izberi A/B/C za vse nerešene spore belega prostora</guilabel> v "
"meniju <guimenu>Združi</guimenu>. Upoštevajte, da če omogočite "
"<guilabel>Prezri številke (obravnavaj kot presledek)</guilabel> ali "
"<guilabel>Prezri komentarje C/C++ (obravnavaj kot presledek)</guilabel>, "
"potem ta samodejna izbira velja tudi za spore v številke ali komentarje."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:787
#, no-c-format
msgid "Auto merge regular expression:"
msgstr "Samodejno združevanje regularnega izraza:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:787
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Regular expression for lines where &kdiff3; should automatically choose one "
"source. See also <link linkend=\"vcskeywordsmergesupport\">Automatic Merge..."
"</link>."
msgstr ""
"Regularni izraz za vrstice, kjer &kdiff3; mora samodejno izbrati en vir. "
"Glejte tudi <link linkend=\"vcskeywordsmergesupport\">Samodejno "
"združevanje...</link>."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:790
#, no-c-format
msgid "Run regular expression auto merge on merge start"
msgstr "Zaženi samodejno združevanje regularnih izrazov ob začetku združevanja"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:790
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If activated &kdiff3; runs the automatic merge using the <guilabel>Auto "
"merge regular expression:</guilabel> option when a merge is started."
msgstr ""
"Če je aktivirano &kdiff3; zažene samodejno spajanje z možnostjo "
"<guilabel>Regularni izraz samodejnega združevanja:</guilabel>, ko se "
"združevanje začne."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:793 index.docbook:798
#, no-c-format
msgid "History entry start regular expression:"
msgstr "Začetek vnosa v zgodovino regularnega izraza"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:793
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Regular expression for the start of the merge history entry. Usually this "
"line contains the \"<literal>&#36;Log&#36;</literal>\" keyword. Default "
"value: \"<literal>.*\\&#36;Log.*\\&#36;.*</literal>\""
msgstr ""
"Regularni izraz za začetek vnosa v zgodovino združevanja. Običajno ta "
"vrstica vsebuje ključno besedo \"<literal>&#36;Log&#36;</literal>\". "
"Privzeta vrednost: \"<literal>.*\\&#36;Log.*\\&#36;.*</literal>\""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:798
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A merge history entry consists of several lines. Specify the regular "
"expression to detect the first line (without the leading comment). Use "
"parentheses to group the keys you want to use for sorting. If left empty, "
"then &kdiff3; assumes that empty lines separate history entries. See also "
"<link linkend=\"vcskeywordsmergesupport\">Automatic Merge...</link>."
msgstr ""
"Vnos v zgodovino spajanja je sestavljen iz več vrstic. Podajte regularni "
"izraz za zaznavanje prve vrstice (brez uvodnega komentarja). Z oklepaji "
"združite ključe, ki jih želite uporabiti za razvrščanje. Če ostane prazno, "
"potem &kdiff3; predpostavlja, da prazne vrstice ločujejo vnose zgodovine. "
"Glejte tudi <link linkend=\"vcskeywordsmergesupport\">Samodejno "
"združevanje...</link>."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:805
#, no-c-format
msgid "History merge sorting"
msgstr "Razvrščanje združevanja zgodovine"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:805
#, no-c-format
msgid "Enable version control history sorting."
msgstr "Omogoči razvrščanje zgodovine nadzora različic."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:808
#, no-c-format
msgid "History entry start sort key order:"
msgstr "Vrstni red ključa za začetek vnosa v zgodovino:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:808
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Each pair of parentheses used in the regular expression for the history "
"start entry groups a key that can be used for sorting. Specify the list of "
"keys (that are numbered in order of occurrence starting with <literal>1</"
"literal>) using ',' as separator (&eg; \"<literal>4,5,6,1,2,3,7</literal>"
"\"). If left empty, then no sorting will be done. See also <link linkend="
"\"vcskeywordsmergesupport\">Automatic Merge...</link>."
msgstr ""
"Vsak par oklepajev, uporabljen v regularnem izrazu za začetni vnos "
"zgodovine, združuje ključ, ki se lahko uporablja za razvrščanje. Podajte "
"seznam ključev (ki so oštevilčeni po vrstnem redu pojavljanja, začenši z "
"<literal>1</literal>) z uporabo ',' kot ločilo (&eg; "
"\"<literal>4,5,6,1,2,3,7 </literal>\"). Če polje ostane prazno, razvrščanje "
"ne bo izvedeno. Glejte tudi <link linkend=\"vcskeywordsmergesupport"
"\">Samodejno združevanje...</link>."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:816
#, no-c-format
msgid "Merge version control history on merge start"
msgstr "Zgodovina nadzora različic združevanja ob začetku združevanja"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:816
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If activated &kdiff3; runs the automatic history merging using "
"aforementioned options when a merge is started."
msgstr ""
"Če je aktivirano, &kdiff3; zažene samodejno združevanje zgodovine z uporabo "
"zgoraj omenjenih možnosti, ko se združevanje začne."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:819
#, no-c-format
msgid "Max number of history entries:"
msgstr "Največje število vnosov v zgodovino:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:819
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kdiff3; truncates the history list after the specified number of entries. "
"Use <literal>-1</literal> to avoid truncation. (Default is <literal>-1</"
"literal>)."
msgstr ""
"&kdiff3; obreže seznam zgodovine po podanem številu vnosov. Uporabite "
"<literal>-1</literal>, da preprečite obrezovanje. (Privzeto je <literal>-1</"
"literal>)."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:822
#, no-c-format
msgid "Test your regular expressions"
msgstr "Preizkusite svoje regularne izraze"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:822
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This button shows a dialog that allows you to improve and test the regular "
"expressions above. Just copy the respective data from your files into the "
"example lines. The <guilabel>Match result:</guilabel> option will "
"immediately show whether the match succeeds or not. The <guilabel>Sort key "
"result:</guilabel> will display the key used for history merge sorting."
msgstr ""
"Ta gumb prikaže pogovorno okno, ki vam omogoča izboljšanje in testiranje "
"zgornjih regularnih izrazov. Preprosto kopirajte ustrezne podatke iz svojih "
"datotek v vzorčne vrstice. Možnost <guilabel>Rezultat ujemanja:</guilabel> "
"bo takoj pokazala, ali je ujemanje uspelo ali ne. <guilabel>Rezultat ključa "
"za razvrščanje:</guilabel> bo prikazal ključ, uporabljen za razvrščanje "
"zgodovine združevanja."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:827
#, no-c-format
msgid "Irrelevant merge command:"
msgstr "Nepomemben ukaz združevanja:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:827
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Specify a command of your own that should be called when &kdiff3; detects "
"that for a three file merge the file from <guilabel>B</guilabel> doesn't "
"contribute any relevant data that isn't already contained in the file from "
"<guilabel>C</guilabel>. The command is called with the three filenames as "
"parameters. Data matched by the <guilabel>Auto merge regular expression</"
"guilabel> or in the history isn't considered relevant."
msgstr ""
"Določite lasten ukaz, ki naj se kliče, ko &kdiff3; zazna, da pri združevanju "
"treh datotek datoteka iz <guilabel>B</guilabel> ne prispeva nobenih "
"ustreznih podatkov, ki jih že ne vsebuje datoteka iz <guilabel>C</guilabel>. "
"Ukaz se kliče s tremi imeni datotek kot parametri. Podatki, ki se ujemajo z "
"<guilabel>regularnim izrazom za samodejno združevanje</guilabel> ali v "
"zgodovini, se ne štejejo za pomembne."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:835
#, no-c-format
msgid "Auto save and quit on merge without conflicts"
msgstr "Samodejno shranjevanje in zapiranje ob združevanju brez sporov"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:835
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If &kdiff3; was started for a file-merge from the command line and all "
"conflicts are solvable without user interaction then automatically save and "
"quit. (Similar to command line option <option>--auto</option>.)"
msgstr ""
"Če je bil &kdiff3; zagnan za združevanje datotek iz ukazne vrstice in vsi "
"konflikti so rešljivi brez interakcije uporabnika, nato pa se samodejno "
"shranijo in zaprejo. (Podobno možnosti ukazne vrstice <option>--auto</"
"option>.)"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:844
#, no-c-format
msgid "Folder Merge"
msgstr "Združevanje map"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:845
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"These options are concerned with scanning the folder and handling the merge: "
"See the <link linkend=\"dirmergeoptions\">Folder Comparison/Merge Docs</"
"link> for details."
msgstr ""
"Te možnosti se nanašajo na prečesavanje mape in obravnavo združevanja: Za "
"podrobnosti glejte <link linkend=\"dirmergeoptions\">Primerjava map/"
"dokumentov o združevanju</link>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:849
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Yet there is one option here that is also relevant for saving single files:"
msgstr ""
"Obstaja pa ena možnost, ki je pomembna tudi za shranjevanje posameznih "
"datotek:"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:853 index.docbook:1600
#, no-c-format
msgid "Backup files (.orig)"
msgstr "Varnostne kopije datotek (.orig)"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:853
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When a file is saved and an older version already exists, then the original "
"version will be renamed with an <literal role=\"extension\">.orig</literal> "
"extension. If an old backup file with <literal role=\"extension\">.orig</"
"literal> extension already exists then this will be deleted without backup."
msgstr ""
"Ko je datoteka shranjena in že obstaja starejša različica, bo prvotna "
"različica preimenovana s pripono <literal role=\"extension\">.orig</"
"literal>. Če stara datoteka varnostne kopije s končnico <literal role="
"\"extension\">.orig</literal> že obstaja, bo ta izbrisana brez varnostne "
"kopije."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:858
#, no-c-format
msgid "Regional and Language Options"
msgstr "Regionalne in jezikovne možnosti"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:860
#, no-c-format
msgid "Use the same encoding for everything"
msgstr "Uporabite isto kodiranje za vse"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:860
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The following encoding options can be adjusted separately for each item or "
"if this option is true, all values will take the first value."
msgstr ""
"Naslednje možnosti kodiranja je mogoče prilagoditi ločeno za vsak element "
"ali če je ta možnost nastavljena, bodo vse vrednosti prevzele prvo vrednost."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:862
#, no-c-format
msgid "Note: Local Encoding is \"...\""
msgstr "Opomba: lokalno kodiranje je \"...\""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:862
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Above the codec-selectors appears this note that tells you what the local "
"encoding is. (This is not adjustable but for your information just in case "
"you don't know your local encoding, but need to select it.)"
msgstr ""
"Nad izbirniki kodekov se prikaže ta opomba, ki vam pove, kakšno je lokalno "
"kodiranje. (To ni nastavljivo, ampak za vašo informacijo, če ne poznate "
"svojega lokalnega kodiranja, vendar ga morate izbrati.)"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:864
#, no-c-format
msgid "Auto Detect"
msgstr "Samodejno zaznavanje"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:864
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This option attempts to use the BOM or meta data from XML/HTML documents to "
"detect encoding. Failing that it will check if a short sample from the "
"beginning of the file can be interpreted as UTF-8. If this check passes "
"UTF-8 will be used. Otherwise it will fall back to the user selected codec. "
"Only UTF-8 is supported with no BOM or metadata present."
msgstr ""
"Ta možnost poskuša uporabiti BOM ali meta podatke iz dokumentov XML/HTML za "
"zaznavanje kodiranja. Če tega ne stori, bo preveril, ali je kratek vzorec z "
"začetka datoteke mogoče interpretirati kot UTF-8. Če je to preverjanje "
"uspešno, bo uporabljen UTF-8. V nasprotnem primeru se bo vrnil na "
"uporabniško izbrani kodek. Podprt je samo UTF-8 brez BOM ali metapodatkov."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:866
#, no-c-format
msgid "File Encoding for A/B/C:"
msgstr "Kodiranje datoteke za A/B/C:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:866
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Adjust the file encoding for input files. This has an effect on how the "
"special characters are interpreted. Since you can adjust each codec "
"separately you can even compare and merge files that were saved using "
"different codecs."
msgstr ""
"Prilagodite kodiranje datoteke za vhodne datoteke. To vpliva na "
"interpretacijo posebnih znakov. Ker lahko prilagodite vsak kodek posebej, "
"lahko celo primerjate in združite datoteke, ki so bile shranjene z uporabo "
"različnih kodekov."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:868
#, no-c-format
msgid "File Encoding for Merge Output and Saving:"
msgstr "Kodiranje datoteke za spajanje in shranjevanje:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:868
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When you have edited a file, then you can adjust which encoding will be used "
"when saving to disk."
msgstr ""
"Ko uredite datoteko, lahko prilagodite, katero kodiranje bo uporabljeno pri "
"shranjevanju na disk."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:870
#, no-c-format
msgid "File Encoding for Preprocessor Files:"
msgstr "Kodiranje datoteke za datoteke predprocesorja:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:870
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When you define preprocessors then they might not be able to operate on your "
"codec. (&eg;: Your files are 16 bit unicode and your preprocessor can only "
"take 8 bit &ASCII;.) With this option you can define the encoding of "
"preprocessor output."
msgstr ""
"Ko definirate predprocesorje, morda ne bodo mogli delovati na vašemkodek. "
"(&eg;: vaše datoteke so 16-bitne unicode in vaš predprocesor lahko samo "
"vzame 8-bitni &ASCII;.) S to možnostjo lahko določite kodiranjeizhod "
"predprocesorja."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:872
#, no-c-format
msgid "Right To Left Language:"
msgstr "Jezik od desne proti levi:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:872
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Some languages are written right to left. When this option is enabled, "
"&kdiff3; draws the text from right to left in the diff input windows and in "
"the merge output window. Note that if you start &kdiff3; with the command "
"line option <option>--reverse</option> then all layouting will be done right "
"to left too. (This is a feature provided by &Qt;.)"
msgstr ""
"Nekateri jeziki pišejo z desne proti levi. Ko je ta možnost omogočena, "
"&kdiff3; nariše besedilo od desne proti levi v oknih za vnos razlike in v "
"oknu za spajanje izhodov. Upoštevajte, da če zaženete &kdiff3; z možnostjo "
"ukazne vrstice <option>--reverse</option> bo tudi vsa postavitev izvedena od "
"desne proti levi. (To je zmožnost, ki jo ponuja &Qt;.)"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:873
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This documentation was written assuming that this option or reverse layout "
"are disabled. So some references to \"left\" or \"right\" must be replaced "
"by their respective counterpart if you use these options."
msgstr ""
"Ta dokumentacija je bila napisana ob predpostavki, da sta ta možnost ali "
"obratna postavitev onemogočeni. Zato je treba nekatere sklice na \"levo\" "
"ali \"desno\" nadomestiti z ustreznim primerkom, če uporabljate te možnosti."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:880
#, no-c-format
msgid "Miscellaneous"
msgstr "Razno"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:881
#, no-c-format
msgid "(These options and actions are available in menus or the buttonbar.)"
msgstr "(Te možnosti in dejanja so na voljo v menijih ali vrstici z gumbi.)"

#. Tag: emphasis
#: index.docbook:883
#, no-c-format
msgid "Overview options:"
msgstr "Možnosti pregleda:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:883
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"These choices are only available when you compare three files. In normal "
"mode all differences are shown in one color-coded overview-column. But "
"sometimes you are especially interested in the differences between only two "
"of these three files. Selecting \"A vs. B\", \"A vs. C\" or \"B vs. C\"-"
"overview will show a second overview column with the required information "
"next to the normal overview."
msgstr ""
"Te možnosti so na voljo le, če primerjate tri datoteke. V običajnem načinu "
"so vse razlike prikazane v enem barvno kodiranem preglednem stolpcu. Toda "
"včasih vas še posebej zanimajo razlike med samo dvema od teh treh datotek. "
"Če izberete pregled \"A proti B\", \"A proti C\" ali \"B proti C\", bo "
"prikazan drugi stolpec pregleda z zahtevanimi informacijami poleg običajnega "
"pregleda."

#. Tag: guimenuitem
#: index.docbook:890
#, no-c-format
msgid "Word Wrap Diff Windows"
msgstr "Okna preloma besed razlik"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:890
#, no-c-format
msgid "Wrap lines when their length would exceed the width of a window."
msgstr "Zavihajte vrste, ko bi njihova dolžina presegla širino okna."

#. Tag: guibutton
#: index.docbook:893
#, no-c-format
msgid "Show Window A/B/C:"
msgstr "Pokaži okno A/B/C:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:893
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Sometimes you want to use the space on the screen better for long lines. "
"Hide the windows that are not important. (In the Windows-menu.)"
msgstr ""
"Včasih želite bolje izkoristiti prostor na zaslonu za dolge vrste. Skrijte "
"okna, ki niso pomembna. (V meniju oken.)"

#. Tag: guibutton
#: index.docbook:896
#, no-c-format
msgid "Toggle Split Orientation"
msgstr "Preklopi razdeljeno usmerjenost"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:896
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Switch between diff windows shown next to each other (<guilabel>A</guilabel> "
"left of <guilabel>B</guilabel> left of <guilabel>C</guilabel>) or above each "
"other (<guilabel>A</guilabel> above <guilabel>B</guilabel> above "
"<guilabel>C</guilabel>). This should also help for long lines. (In the "
"<guimenu>Window</guimenu> menu.)"
msgstr ""
"Preklapljajte med okni za razlikovanje, ki so prikazana eno poleg drugega "
"(<guilabel>A</guilabel> levo od <guilabel>B</guilabel> levo od <guilabel>C</"
"guilabel>) ali eno nad drugim (<guilabel>A</guilabel> nad <guilabel>B</"
"guilabel> nad <guilabel>C</guilabel>). To bi moralo pomagati tudi pri dolgih "
"vrstah. (V meniju <guimenu>Okno</guimenu>.)"

#. Tag: guibutton
#: index.docbook:899
#, no-c-format
msgid "Merge Current File"
msgstr "Združi trenutno datoteko"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:899
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Works if you only compare two files. A single click starts the merge and "
"uses the filename of the last input-file as the default output filename. "
"(When this is used to restart a merge, then the output filename will be "
"preserved.)"
msgstr ""
"Deluje, če primerjate samo dve datoteki. En sam klik zažene združevanje in "
"uporabi ime zadnje vhodne datoteke kot privzeto ime izhodne datoteke. (Ko se "
"to uporabi za ponovni zagon združevanja, bo ime izhodne datoteke ohranjeno.)"

#. Tag: guibutton
#: index.docbook:903
#, no-c-format
msgid "Show White Space"
msgstr "Prikaži beli prostor"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:903
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Turn this off to suppress any highlighting of white-space-only changes in "
"the text or overview-columns. (Note that this also applies to changes in "
"numbers or comments if the options <guilabel>Ignore numbers (treat as white "
"space)</guilabel> or <guilabel>Ignore C/C++ comments (treat as white space)</"
"guilabel> are active.)"
msgstr ""
"To izklopite, če želite onemogočiti označevanje sprememb samo s presledki v "
"besedilu ali preglednih stolpcih. (Upoštevajte, da to velja tudi za "
"spremembe v številkah ali komentarjih, če sta možnosti <guilabel>Prezri "
"številke (obravnavaj kot presledek)</guilabel> ali <guilabel>Prezri "
"komentarje C/C++ (obravnavaj kot presledek)</guilabel> aktivno.)"

#. Tag: guibutton
#: index.docbook:908
#, no-c-format
msgid "Show Space &amp;&amp; Tabulator Characters"
msgstr "Prikaz prostora &amp;&amp; Znaki tabulatorja"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:908
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Sometimes the visible spaces and tabs are disturbing. You can turn this off."
msgstr "Včasih so vidni prostori in zavihki moteči. To lahko izklopite."

#. Tag: guibutton
#: index.docbook:910
#, no-c-format
msgid "Show Line Numbers"
msgstr "Prikazuj številke vrstic"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:910
#, no-c-format
msgid "You can select if line numbers should be shown for the input files."
msgstr ""
"Izberete lahko, ali naj bodo prikazane številke vrstic za vhodne datoteke."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:915
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configuring Keyboard-Shortcuts"
msgstr "Konfiguriranje bližnjic na tipkovnici"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:916
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Currently only the &frameworks; version supports user-configurable keyboard-"
"shortcuts. (Menu <menuchoice><guimenu>Settings</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Configure Shortcuts...</guimenuitem></menuchoice>)"
msgstr ""
"Trenutno samo &frameworks; različica podpira uporabniško nastavljive "
"bližnjice na tipkovnici. (Meni <menuchoice><guimenu>Nastavitve</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Konfiguriraj bližnjice...</guimenuitem></menuchoice>)"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:923
#, no-c-format
msgid "Preprocessor Commands"
msgstr "Ukazi predprocesorja"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:924
#, no-c-format
msgid "&kdiff3; supports two preprocessor options."
msgstr "&kdiff3; podpira dve možnosti predprocesorja."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:928
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When any file is read, it will be piped through this external command. The "
"output of this command will be visible instead of the original file. You can "
"write your own preprocessor that fulfills your specific needs. Use this to "
"cut away disturbing parts of the file, or to automatically correct the "
"indentation &etc;"
msgstr ""
"Ko je katera koli datoteka prebrana, bo posredovana skozi ta zunanji ukaz. "
"Izhod tega ukaza bo viden namesto izvirne datoteke. Napišete lahko svoj "
"predprocesor, ki bo ustrezal vašim posebnim potrebam. Uporabite to, da "
"odrežete moteče dele datoteke ali samodejno popravite zamik &etc;"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:935
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When any file is read, it will be piped through this external command. If a "
"preprocessor-command (see above) is also specified, then the output of the "
"preprocessor is the input of the line-matching preprocessor. The output will "
"only be used during the line matching phase of the analysis. You can write "
"your own preprocessor that fulfills your specific needs. Each input line "
"must have a corresponding output line."
msgstr ""
"Ko je katera koli datoteka prebrana, bo posredovana skozi ta zunanji ukaz. "
"Če je podan tudi ukaz predprocesorja (glejte zgoraj), je izhod "
"predprocesorja vhod predprocesorja za ujemanje vrstic. Izhod bo uporabljen "
"le med fazo analize ujemanja vrstic. Napišete lahko svoj predprocesor, ki bo "
"ustrezal vašim posebnim potrebam. Vsaka vhodna vrstica mora imeti ustrezno "
"izhodno vrstico."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:945
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The idea is to allow the user greater flexibility while configuring the diff-"
"result. But this requires an external program, and many users don't want to "
"write one themselves. The good news is that very often <command>sed</"
"command> or <command>perl</command> will do the job."
msgstr ""
"Ideja je omogočiti uporabniku večjo prilagodljivost med konfiguriranjem "
"rezultata razlik.  Toda to zahteva zunanji program in mnogi uporabniki ga ne "
"želijo napisati sami. Dobra novica je, da zelo pogosto <command>sed</"
"command> ali <command>perl</command> opravita to delo."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:951
#, no-c-format
msgid "Example: Simple testcase: Consider file a.txt (6 lines):"
msgstr ""
"Primer: Preprost testni primer: Razmislite o datoteki a.txt (6 vrstic):"

#. Tag: screen
#: index.docbook:953
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"aa\n"
"      ba\n"
"      ca\n"
"      da\n"
"      ea\n"
"      fa"
msgstr ""
"aa\n"
"      ba\n"
"      ca\n"
"      da\n"
"      ea\n"
"      fa"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:954
#, no-c-format
msgid "And file b.txt (3 lines):"
msgstr "In datoteka b.txt (3 vrstice):"

#. Tag: screen
#: index.docbook:957
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"cg\n"
"      dg\n"
"      eg"
msgstr ""
"cg\n"
"      dg\n"
"      eg"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:958
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Without a preprocessor the following lines would be placed next to each "
"other:"
msgstr ""
"Brez predprocesorja bi bile naslednje vrstice postavljene ena poleg druge: "

#. Tag: screen
#: index.docbook:961
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"aa - cg\n"
"      ba - dg\n"
"      ca - eg\n"
"      da\n"
"      ea\n"
"      fa"
msgstr ""
"aa - cg\n"
"      ba - dg\n"
"      ca - eg\n"
"      da\n"
"      ea\n"
"      fa"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:962
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This is probably not wanted since the first letter contains the actually "
"interesting information. To help the matching algorithm to ignore the second "
"letter we can use a line matching preprocessor command, that replaces 'g' "
"with 'a':"
msgstr ""
"To verjetno ni zaželeno, saj je v prvi črki dejansko zanimiv podatek. Da "
"algoritmu za ujemanje pomagamo prezreti drugo črko, lahko uporabimo ukaz "
"predprocesorja za ujemanje vrstic, ki nadomesti 'g' z 'a':"

#. Tag: screen
#: index.docbook:967
#, no-c-format
msgid "<command>sed</command> 's/g/a/'"
msgstr "<command>sed</command> 's/g/a/'"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:968
#, no-c-format
msgid "With this command the result of the comparison would be:"
msgstr "S tem ukazom bi bil rezultat primerjave:"

#. Tag: screen
#: index.docbook:971
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"aa\n"
"      ba\n"
"      ca - cg\n"
"      da - dg\n"
"      ea - eg\n"
"      fa"
msgstr ""
"aa\n"
"      ba\n"
"      ca - cg\n"
"      da - dg\n"
"      ea - eg\n"
"      fa"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:972
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Internally the matching algorithm sees the files after running the line "
"matching preprocessor, but on the screen the file is unchanged. (The normal "
"preprocessor would change the data also on the screen.)"
msgstr ""
"Notranji algoritem za ujemanje vidi datoteke po zagonu predprocesorja za "
"ujemanje vrstic, toda na zaslonu je datoteka nespremenjena. (Običajni "
"predprocesor bi spremenil podatke tudi na zaslonu.)"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:978
#, no-c-format
msgid "<command>sed</command> Basics"
msgstr "<command>sed</command> Osnove"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:979
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This section only introduces some very basic features of <command>sed</"
"command>. For more information see <ulink url=\"info:/sed\">info:/sed</"
"ulink> or <ulink url=\"https://www.gnu.org/software/sed/manual/html_mono/sed."
"html\"> https://www.gnu.org/software/sed/manual/html_mono/sed.html</ulink>. "
"A precompiled version for &Windows; can be found at <ulink url=\"http://"
"unxutils.sourceforge.net\"> http://unxutils.sourceforge.net</ulink>. Note "
"that the following examples assume that the <command>sed</command> command "
"is in some folder in the <envar>PATH</envar> environment variable. If this "
"is not the case, you have to specify the full absolute path for the command."
msgstr ""
"Ta razdelek predstavlja le nekaj zelo osnovnih funkcij <command>sed</"
"command>. Za več informacij glejte <ulink url=\"info:/sed\">info:/sed</"
"ulink> ali <ulink url=\"https://www.gnu.org/software/sed/manual/html_mono/"
"sed.html\"> https://www.gnu.org/software/sed/manual/html_mono/sed.html</"
"ulink>. Vnaprej prevedena različica za &Windows; najdete na <ulink url="
"\"http://unxutils.sourceforge.net\"> http://unxutils.sourceforge.net</"
"ulink>. Upoštevajte, da naslednji primeri predpostavljajo, da je ukaz "
"<command>sed</command> v neki mapi v spremenljivki okolja <envar>PATH</"
"envar>. Če temu ni tako, morate podati celotno absolutno pot za ukaz."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:990
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In this context only the <command>sed</command> substitute command is used:"
msgstr ""
"V tem kontekstu se uporablja samo nadomestni ukaz <command>sed</command>:"

#. Tag: screen
#: index.docbook:993
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<command>sed</command> 's/<replaceable>REGEXP</replaceable>/"
"<replaceable>REPLACEMENT</replaceable>/<replaceable>FLAGS</replaceable>'"
msgstr ""
"<command>sed</command> 's/<replaceable>REGEXP</replaceable>/"
"<replaceable>REPLACEMENT</replaceable>/<replaceable>FLAGS</replaceable>'"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:994
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Before you use a new command within &kdiff3;, you should first test it in a "
"console. Here the <command>echo</command> command is useful. Example:"
msgstr ""
"Preden uporabite nov ukaz znotraj &kdiff3;, ga najprej preizkusite v "
"konzoli. Tukaj je uporaben ukaz <command>echo</command>. Primer:"

#. Tag: screen
#: index.docbook:998
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<command>echo</command> abrakadabra | <command>sed</command> 's/a/o/'\n"
"   -> obrakadabra"
msgstr ""
"<command>echo</command> abrakadabra | <command>sed</command> 's/a/o/' -> "
"abrakadabra"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:999
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This example shows a very simple sed-command that replaces the first "
"occurrence of \"a\" with \"o\". If you want to replace all occurrences then "
"you need the \"g\" flag:"
msgstr ""
"Ta primer prikazuje zelo preprost ukaz sed, ki zamenja prvo pojavitev \"a\" "
"z \"o\". Če želite zamenjati vse pojavitve, potem potrebujete zastavico \"g"
"\":"

#. Tag: screen
#: index.docbook:1003
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<command>echo</command> abrakadabra | <command>sed</command> 's/a/o/g'\n"
"   -> obrokodobro"
msgstr ""
"<command>echo</command> abrakadabra | <command>sed</command> 's/a/o/g' -> "
"obrokodobro"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1004
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The \"|\"-symbol is the pipe-command that transfers the output of the "
"previous command to the input of the following command. If you want to test "
"with a longer file then you can use <command>cat</command> on &UNIX; like "
"systems or <command>type</command> on &Windows; like systems. <command>sed</"
"command> will do the substitution for each line."
msgstr ""
"Simbol \"|\" je cevni ukaz, ki prenese izhod prejšnjega ukaza na vhod "
"naslednjega ukaza. Če želite preizkusiti z daljšo datoteko, lahko uporabite "
"<command>cat</command> na sistemu &UNIX; ali <command>type</command> v "
"sistemu &Windows;. <command>sed</command> bo izvedel zamenjavo za vsako "
"vrstico."

#. Tag: screen
#: index.docbook:1009
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<command>cat</command> <replaceable>filename</replaceable> | <command>sed</"
"command> <replaceable>options</replaceable>"
msgstr ""
"<command>cat</command> <replaceable>imedatoteke</replaceable> | "
"<command>sed</command> <replaceable>možnosti</replaceable>"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1012
#, no-c-format
msgid "Examples For <command>sed</command> Use In &kdiff3;"
msgstr "Primeri uporabe <command>sed</command> v &kdiff3;"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1013
#, no-c-format
msgid "Ignoring Other Types Of Comments"
msgstr "Ignoriranje drugih vrst komentarjev"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1014
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Currently &kdiff3; understands only C/C++ comments. Using the <guilabel>Line-"
"matching preprocessor command:</guilabel> option you can also ignore other "
"types of comments, by converting them into C/C++-comments."
msgstr ""
"Trenutno &kdiff3; razume le komentarje C/C++. Z možnostjo <guilabel>Ukaz "
"predprocesorja za ujemanje vrstic:</guilabel> lahko tudi prezrete druge "
"vrste komentarjev, tako da jih pretvorite v komentarje C/C++."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1019
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Example: To ignore comments starting with \"<literal>#</literal>\", you "
"would like to convert them to \"<literal>//</literal>\". Note that you also "
"must enable the <guilabel>Ignore C/C++ comments (treat as white space)</"
"guilabel> option to get an effect. An appropriate <guilabel>Line-matching "
"preprocessor command:</guilabel> would be:"
msgstr ""
"Primer: Če želite prezreti komentarje, ki se začnejo z \"<literal>#</literal>"
"\", jih želite pretvoriti v \"<literal>//</literal>\". Upoštevajte, da "
"morate za učinek omogočiti tudi možnost <guilabel>Prezri komentarje C/C++ "
"(obravnavaj kot presledek)</guilabel>. Ustrezen <guilabel>Ukaz "
"predprocesorja za ujemanje vrstic:</guilabel> bi bil:"

#. Tag: screen
#: index.docbook:1022
#, no-c-format
msgid "<command>sed</command> 's/#/\\/\\//'"
msgstr "<command>sed</command> 's/#/\\/\\//'"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1023
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Since for <command>sed</command> the \"<literal>/</literal>\" character has "
"a special meaning, it is necessary to place the \"<literal>\\</literal>\" "
"character before each \"<literal>/</literal>\" in the replacement-string. "
"Sometimes the \"<literal>\\</literal>\" is required to add or remove a "
"special meaning of certain characters. The single quotation marks (') are "
"only important when testing on the command shell as it will otherwise "
"attempt to process some characters. &kdiff3; does not do this except for the "
"escape sequences '<literal>\\\"</literal>' and '<literal>\\\\</literal>'."
msgstr ""
"Ker ima za <command>sed</command> znak \"<literal>/</literal>\" poseben "
"pomen, je treba znak  \"<literal>\\</literal>\" postaviti pred vsak "
"\"<literal>/</literal>\" v nadomestnem nizu. Včasih je  \"<literal>\\</"
"literal>\" potreben za dodajanje ali odstranjevanje posebnega pomena "
"določenih znakov. Enojni narekovaji (') so pomembni samo pri testiranju na "
"ukazni lupini, saj bo drugače poskušala obdelati nekatere znake. &kdiff3; "
"tega ne naredi, razen za ubežna zaporedja '<literal>\\\"</literal>' in "
"'<literal>\\\\</literal>'."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1028
#, no-c-format
msgid "Caseinsensitive Diff"
msgstr "Razlika pri razlikovanju velikih/malih črk"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1029
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Use the following <guilabel>Line-matching preprocessor command:</guilabel> "
"to convert all input to uppercase:"
msgstr ""
"Uporabite naslednji <guilabel>ukaz predprocesorja za ujemanje vrstic:</"
"guilabel> za pretvorbo vseh vnosov v velike črke:"

#. Tag: screen
#: index.docbook:1032
#, no-c-format
msgid "<command>sed</command> 's/\\(.*\\)/\\U\\1/'"
msgstr "<command>sed</command> 's/\\(.*\\)/\\U\\1/'"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1033
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Here the \"<literal>.*</literal>\" is a regular expression that matches any "
"string and in this context matches all characters in the line. The "
"\"<literal>\\1</literal>\" in the replacement string refers to the matched "
"text within the first pair of \"<literal>\\(</literal>\" and \"<literal>\\)</"
"literal>\". The \"<literal>\\U</literal>\" converts the inserted text to "
"uppercase."
msgstr ""
"Tu je  \"<literal>.*</literal>\" regularni izraz, ki se ujema s katerim koli "
"nizom in se v tem kontekstu ujema z vsemi znaki v vrstici. \"<literal>\\1</"
"literal>\" v nadomestnem nizu se nanaša na ujemajoče se besedilo v prvem "
"paru \"<literal>\\(</literal>\" and \"<literal>\\)</literal>\". \"<literal>"
"\\U</literal>\" pretvori vstavljeno besedilo v velike črke."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1040
#, no-c-format
msgid "Ignoring Version Control Keywords"
msgstr "Ignoriranje ključnih besed za nadzor različic"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1041
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"CVS and other version control systems use several keywords to insert "
"automatically generated strings (<ulink url=\"info:/cvs/Keyword substitution"
"\">info:/cvs/Keyword substitution</ulink>). All of them follow the pattern "
"\"<replaceable>$KEYWORD generated text$</replaceable>\". We now need a line-"
"matching preprocessor command that removes only the generated text:"
msgstr ""
"CVS in drugi sistemi za nadzor različic uporabljajo več ključnih besed za "
"vstavljanje samodejno ustvarjenih nizov (<ulink url=\"info:/cvs/Keyword "
"substitution\">info:/cvs/Keyword substitution</ulink>). Vsi sledijo vzorcu "
"\"<replaceable>$KEYWORD generirano besedilo$</replaceable>\". Zdaj "
"potrebujemo ukaz predprocesorja za ujemanje vrstic, ki odstrani samo "
"generirano besedilo:"

#. Tag: screen
#: index.docbook:1047
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<command>sed</command> 's/\\$\\(Revision\\|Author\\|Log\\|Header\\|Date\\).*"
"\\$/\\$\\1\\$/'"
msgstr ""
"<command>sed</command> 's/\\$\\(Revision\\|Author\\|Log\\|Header\\|Date\\).*"
"\\$/\\$\\1\\$/'"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1048
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The \"<literal>\\|</literal>\" separates the possible keywords. You might "
"want to modify this list according to your needs. The \"<literal>\\</literal>"
"\" before the \"<literal>$</literal>\" is necessary because otherwise the "
"\"<literal>$</literal>\" matches the end of the line."
msgstr ""
"\"<literal>\\|</literal>\" ločuje možne ključne besede. Ta seznam boste "
"morda želeli spremeniti glede na svoje potrebe. \"<literal>\\</literal>\" "
"pred \"<literal>$</literal>\" je potreben, ker se drugače \"<literal>$</"
"literal>\" ujema s koncem vrstice."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1053
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"While experimenting with <command>sed</command> you might come to understand "
"and even like these regular expressions. They are useful because there are "
"many other programs that also support similar things."
msgstr ""
"Med eksperimentiranjem z <command>sed</command> boste morda razumeli in vam "
"bodo celo všeč ti regularni izrazi. Uporabni so, ker obstaja veliko drugih "
"programov, ki prav tako podpirajo podobne stvari."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1060
#, no-c-format
msgid "Ignoring Numbers"
msgstr "Ignoriranje številk"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1061
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Ignoring numbers actually is a built-in option. But as another example, this "
"is how it would look as a line-matching preprocessor command."
msgstr ""
"Ignoriranje številk je pravzaprav vgrajena možnost. Toda kot drug primer, "
"takole bi bil videti ukaz predprocesorja za ujemanje vrstic."

#. Tag: screen
#: index.docbook:1065
#, no-c-format
msgid "<command>sed</command> 's/[0123456789.-]//g'"
msgstr "<command>sed</command> 's/[0123456789.-]//g'"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1066
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Any character within '<literal>[</literal>' and '<literal>]</literal>' is a "
"match and will be replaced with nothing."
msgstr ""
"Vsak znak znotraj '<literal>[</literal>' in '<literal>]</literal>' se ujema "
"in ne bo zamenjan z ničemer."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1071
#, no-c-format
msgid "Ignoring Certain Columns"
msgstr "Ignoriranje določenih stolpcev"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1072
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Sometimes a text is very strictly formatted, and contains columns that you "
"always want to ignore, while there are other columns you want to preserve "
"for analysis. In the following example the first five columns (characters) "
"are ignored, the next ten columns are preserved, then again five columns are "
"ignored and the rest of the line is preserved."
msgstr ""
"Včasih je besedilo zelo strogo oblikovano in vsebuje stolpce, ki jih želite "
"vedno prezreti, medtem ko obstajajo drugi stolpci, ki jih želite ohraniti za "
"analizo. V naslednjem primeru je prvih pet stolpcev (znakov) prezrtih, "
"naslednjih deset stolpcev je ohranjenih, nato je spet pet stolpcev prezrtih "
"in preostala vrstica je ohranjena."

#. Tag: screen
#: index.docbook:1077
#, no-c-format
msgid "<command>sed</command> 's/.....\\(..........\\).....\\(.*\\)/\\1\\2/'"
msgstr "<command>sed</command> 's/.....\\(..........\\).....\\(.*\\)/\\1\\2/'"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1078
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Each dot '<literal>.</literal>' matches any single character. The \"<literal>"
"\\1</literal>\" and \"<literal>\\2</literal>\" in the replacement string "
"refer to the matched text within the first and second pair of \"<literal>"
"\\(</literal>\" and \"<literal>\\)</literal>\" denoting the text to be "
"preserved."
msgstr ""
"Vsaka pika '<literal>.</literal>' se ujema s katerim koli posameznim znakom. "
"\"<literal>\\1</literal>\" in \"<literal>\\2</literal>\" v nadomestnem nizu "
"se nanašata na ujemajoče se besedilo znotraj prvega in drugega para "
"\"<literal>\\(</literal>\" in \"<literal>\\)</literal>\", ki označujeta "
"besedilo, ki ga je treba ohraniti."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1084
#, no-c-format
msgid "Combining Several Substitutions"
msgstr "Kombinacija več zamenjav"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1085
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Sometimes you want to apply several substitutions at once. You can then use "
"the semicolon '<literal>;</literal>' to separate these from each other. "
"Example:"
msgstr ""
"Včasih želite uporabiti več zamenjav hkrati. Nato jih lahko ločite med seboj "
"s podpičjem '<literal>;</literal>'. Primer:"

#. Tag: screen
#: index.docbook:1089
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<command>echo</command> abrakadabra | <command>sed</command> 's/a/o/g;s/\\(.*"
"\\)/\\U\\1/'\n"
"   -> OBROKODOBRO"
msgstr ""
"<command>echo</command> abrakadabra | <command>sed</command> 's/a/o/g;s/\\(.*"
"\\)/\\U\\1/'\n"
"   -> OBROKODOBRO"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1092
#, no-c-format
msgid "Using <command>perl</command> instead of <command>sed</command>"
msgstr "Uporaba <command>perl</command> namesto <command>sed</command>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1093
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Instead of <command>sed</command> you might want to use something else like "
"<command>perl</command>."
msgstr ""
"Namesto <command>sed</command> boste morda želeli uporabiti nekaj drugega, "
"kot je <command>perl</command>."

#. Tag: screen
#: index.docbook:1097
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<command>perl</command> -p -e 's/<replaceable>REGEXP</replaceable>/"
"<replaceable>REPLACEMENT</replaceable>/<replaceable>FLAGS</replaceable>'"
msgstr ""
"<command>perl</command> -p -e 's/<replaceable>REGEXP</replaceable>/"
"<replaceable>REPLACEMENT</replaceable>/<replaceable>FLAGS</replaceable>'"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1098
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"But some details are different in <command>perl</command>. Note that where "
"<command>sed</command> needed \"<literal>\\(</literal>\" and \"<literal>\\)</"
"literal>\" <command>perl</command> requires the simpler \"<literal>(</"
"literal>\" and \"<literal>)</literal>\" without preceding '<literal>\\</"
"literal>'. Example:"
msgstr ""
"Toda nekatere podrobnosti so drugačne v <command>perl</command>. "
"Upoštevajte, da kjer <command>sed</command> potrebuje \"<literal>\\(</"
"literal>\" in \"<literal>\\)</literal>\", <command>perl</command> zahteva "
"enostavnejši \"<literal>(</literal>\" in \"<literal>)</literal>\" brez "
"'<literal>\\</literal>'. Primer:"

#. Tag: screen
#: index.docbook:1103
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<command>sed</command> 's/\\(.*\\)/\\U\\1/'\n"
"   <command>perl</command> -p -e 's/(.*)/\\U\\1/'"
msgstr ""
"<command>sed</command> 's/\\(.*\\)/\\U\\1/'\n"
"   <command>perl</command> -p -e 's/(.*)/\\U\\1/'"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1107
#, no-c-format
msgid "Order Of Preprocessor Execution"
msgstr "Vrstni red izvajanja predprocesorja"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1108
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The data is piped through all internal and external preprocessors in the "
"following order:"
msgstr ""
"Podatki se prenašajo skozi vse notranje in zunanje predprocesorje v "
"naslednjem vrstnem redu:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1113
#, no-c-format
msgid "Normal preprocessor,"
msgstr "Običajni predprocesor,"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1114
#, no-c-format
msgid "Line-matching preprocessor,"
msgstr "Predprocesor za ujemanje vrstic,"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1115
#, no-c-format
msgid "Ignore case (treat as white space) (conversion to uppercase),"
msgstr ""
"Ignoriraj velike črke (obravnavaj kot presledek) (pretvorba v velike črke),"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1116
#, no-c-format
msgid "Detection of C/C++ comments,"
msgstr "Zaznavanje komentarjev C/C++,"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1117
#, no-c-format
msgid "Ignore numbers (treat as white space),"
msgstr "Ignoriraj številke (obravnavaj kot beli prostor),"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1118
#, no-c-format
msgid "Ignore white space"
msgstr "Ignoriraj beli prostor"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1120
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The data after the normal preprocessor will be preserved for display and "
"merging. The other operations only modify the data that the line-matching-"
"diff-algorithm sees."
msgstr ""
"Podatki po običajnem predprocesorju bodo ohranjeni za prikaz in združevanje. "
"Druge operacije spreminjajo le podatke, ki jih vidi algoritem za ujemanje "
"razlik med vrsticami."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1123
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In the rare cases where you use a normal preprocessor note that the line-"
"matching-preprocessor sees the output of the normal preprocessor as input."
msgstr ""
"V redkih primerih, ko uporabljate običajni predprocesor, upoštevajte, da "
"predprocesor za ujemanje vrstic vidi izhod običajnega predprocesorja kot "
"vhod."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1129
#, no-c-format
msgid "Warning"
msgstr "Opozorilo"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1130
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The preprocessor-commands are often very useful, but as with any option that "
"modifies your texts or hides away certain differences automatically, you "
"might accidentally overlook certain differences and in the worst case "
"destroy important data."
msgstr ""
"Ukazi predprocesorja so pogosto zelo uporabni, a kot pri vsaki možnosti, ki "
"spremeni vaša besedila ali samodejno skrije določene razlike, lahko pomotoma "
"spregledate določene razlike in v najslabšem primeru uničite pomembne "
"podatke."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1134
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For this reason during a merge if a normal preprocessor-command is being "
"used &kdiff3; will tell you so and ask you if it should be disabled or not. "
"But it won't warn you if a <guilabel>Line-matching preprocessor command:</"
"guilabel> option is active. The merge will not complete until all conflicts "
"are solved. If you disabled <menuchoice><guimenu>Diffview</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Show White Space</guimenuitem></menuchoice> menu item "
"then the differences that were removed with the <guilabel>Line-matching "
"preprocessor command:</guilabel> option will also be invisible. If the "
"<guibutton>Save</guibutton> button remains disabled during a merge (because "
"of remaining conflicts), make sure to enable <menuchoice><guimenu>Diffview</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Show White Space</guimenuitem></menuchoice> menu item. "
"If you don't want to merge these less important differences manually you can "
"select <menuchoice><guimenu>Merge</guimenu><guimenuitem>Choose [A|B|C] for "
"All Unsolved Whitespace Conflicts</guimenuitem></menuchoice> menu item."
msgstr ""
"Iz tega razloga med združevanjem, če se uporablja običajen predprocesorski "
"ukaz, vam bo &kdiff3; to povedal in vas vprašal, ali naj bo onemogočeno ali "
"ne. Vendar vas ne bo opozoril, če je aktivna možnost <guilabel>Ukaz "
"predprocesorja za ujemanje vrstic:</guilabel>. Združevanje se ne bo "
"dokončalo, dokler niso razrešeni vsi spori. Če ste onemogočili menijski "
"element <menuchoice><guimenu>Diffview</guimenu><guimenuitem>Pokaži prazen "
"prostor</guimenuitem></menuchoice>, bodo razlike, ki so bile odstranjene z "
"<guilabel>ukazom predprocesorja za ujemanje vrstic:</guilabel > možnost bo "
"prav tako nevidna. Če gumb <guibutton>Shrani</guibutton> ostane onemogočen "
"med združevanjem (zaradi preostalih sporov), se prepričajte, da ste "
"omogočili elelent menija <menuchoice><guimenu>Diffview</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Pokaži prazen prostor</guimenuitem></menuchoice>. Če "
"teh manj pomembnih razlik ne želite združiti ročno, lahko izberete "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>Združi</guimenu><guimenuitem>Izberi [A|B|C] za vse "
"nerešene spore presledkov</guimenuitem></menuchoice > element menija."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1143
#, no-c-format
msgid "Folder Comparison and Merge with &kdiff3;"
msgstr "Primerjava map in združevanje s &kdiff3;"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1144
#, no-c-format
msgid "Introduction into Folder Comparison and Merge"
msgstr "Uvod v primerjavo in združevanje map"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1145
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Often programmers must modify many files in a folder to achieve their "
"purpose. For this &kdiff3; also lets you compare and merge complete folders "
"recursively!"
msgstr ""
"Programerji morajo pogosto spremeniti veliko datotek v mapi, da dosežejo "
"svoj namen. Za ta &kdiff3; omogoča tudi primerjavo in rekurzivno združevanje "
"celotnih map!"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1149
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Even though comparing and merging folders seems to be quite obvious, there "
"are several details that you should know about. Most important is of course "
"the fact that now many files might be affected by each operation. If you "
"don't have backups of your original data, then it can be very hard or even "
"impossible to return to the original state. So before starting a merge, make "
"sure that your data is safe, and going back is possible. If you make an "
"archive or use some version control system is your decision, but even "
"experienced programmers and integrators need the old sources now and then. "
"And note that even though I (the author of &kdiff3;) try to do my best, I "
"can't guarantee that there are no bugs. According to the &GNU; GPL there is "
"NO WARRANTY whatsoever for this program. So be humble and always keep in "
"mind:"
msgstr ""
"Čeprav se zdi, da sta primerjava in združevanje map povsem očitna, morate "
"vedeti več podrobnosti. Najpomembnejše je seveda dejstvo, da zdaj lahko "
"vsaka operacija vpliva na veliko datotek. Če nimate varnostne kopije "
"izvirnih podatkov, se je lahko zelo težko ali celo nemogoče vrniti v prvotno "
"stanje. Zato se pred začetkom združevanja prepričajte, da so vaši podatki "
"varni in da je vrnitev možna. Ali boste naredili arhiv ali uporabili kakšen "
"sistem za nadzor različic, je vaša odločitev, a tudi izkušeni programerji in "
"integratorji tu in tam potrebujejo stare vire. In upoštevajte, da čeprav se "
"jaz (avtor &kdiff3;) trudim po svojih najboljših močeh, ne morem zagotoviti, "
"da ne bo nobenih napak. Glede na &GNU; GPL za ta program NI nikakršnega "
"JAMSTVA. Zato bodite ponižni in vedno imejte v mislih:"

#. Tag: emphasis
#: index.docbook:1163
#, no-c-format
msgid "To err is human, but to really mess things up you need a computer."
msgstr ""
"Motiti se je človeško, a če želite stvari zares zamočiti, potrebujete "
"računalnik."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1165
#, no-c-format
msgid "So this is what this program can do for you: &kdiff3; ..."
msgstr "In to lahko naredi ta program za vas: &kdiff3; ..."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1169
#, no-c-format
msgid "... reads and compares two or three folders recursively,"
msgstr "... rekurzivno bere in primerja dve ali tri mape,"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1170
#, no-c-format
msgid "... takes special care of symbolic links,"
msgstr "... še posebej skrbi za simbolne povezave,"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1171
#, no-c-format
msgid "... lets you browse files on mouse double click,"
msgstr "... vam omogoča brskanje po datotekah z dvojnim klikom miške,"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1172
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"... for each item proposes a merge operation, which you can change before "
"starting the folder merge,"
msgstr ""
"... za vsak element predlaga operacijo združevanja, ki jo lahko spremenite "
"pred začetkom združevanja map,"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1174
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"... lets you simulate the merge and lists the actions that would take place, "
"without actually doing them,"
msgstr ""
"... vam omogoča simulacijo združevanja in navede dejanja, ki bi se zgodila, "
"ne da bi jih dejansko izvedli,"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1176
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"... lets you really do the merge, and lets you interact whenever manual "
"interaction is needed,"
msgstr ""
"... vam omogoča resnično združevanje in vam omogoča interakcijo, kadar koli "
"je potrebna ročna interakcija,"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1178
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"... lets you run the selected operation for all items (<keycap>F7</keycap> "
"key) or the selected item (<keycap>F6</keycap> key),"
msgstr ""
"... omogoča zagon izbrane operacije za vse elemente (tipka <keycap>F7</"
"keycap>) ali izbrani element (tipka <keycap>F6</keycap>),"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1179
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"... lets you continue the merge after manual interaction with <keycap>F7</"
"keycap> key,"
msgstr ""
"... omogoča nadaljevanje združevanja po ročni interakciji s tipko "
"<keycap>F7</keycap>,"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1180
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"... optionally creates backups, with the <literal role=\"extension\">.orig</"
"literal> extension,"
msgstr ""
"... po želji ustvari varnostne kopije z razširitvijo <literal role="
"\"extension\">.orig</literal>,"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1185
#, no-c-format
msgid "Starting Folder Comparison Or Merge"
msgstr "Začetek primerjave ali spajanja map"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1186
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This is very similar to the single file merge and comparison. You just have "
"to specify folders on the command line or in the file-open dialog."
msgstr ""
"To je zelo podobno spajanju in primerjavi posamezne datoteke. Določiti "
"morate samo mape v ukazni vrstici ali v pogovornem oknu za odpiranje "
"datoteke."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1191
#, no-c-format
msgid "Compare/Merge two folders:"
msgstr "Primerjaj/združi dve mapi:"

#. Tag: screen
#: index.docbook:1192
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<command>kdiff3</command> <replaceable>folder1 folder2</replaceable>\n"
"   <command>kdiff3</command> <replaceable>folder1 folder2</replaceable> -o "
"<replaceable>destdir</replaceable>"
msgstr ""
"<command>kdiff3</command> <replaceable>mapa1 mapa2</replaceable> "
"<command>kdiff3</command> <replaceable>mapa1 mapa2</replaceable> -o "
"<replaceable>destdir</replaceable>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1193
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If no destination folder is specified, then &kdiff3; will use "
"<replaceable>folder2</replaceable>."
msgstr ""
"Če ciljna mapa ni navedena, potem &kdiff3; bo uporabil <replaceable>mapo2</"
"replaceable>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1198
#, no-c-format
msgid "Compare/Merge three folders:"
msgstr "Primerjaj/združi tri mape:"

#. Tag: screen
#: index.docbook:1199
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<command>kdiff3</command> <replaceable>folder1 folder2 folder3</"
"replaceable>\n"
"   <command>kdiff3</command> <replaceable>folder1 folder2 folder3</"
"replaceable> -o <replaceable>destdir</replaceable>"
msgstr ""
"<command>kdiff3</command> <replaceable>mapa1 folder2 folder3</replaceable>\n"
"<command>kdiff3</command> <replaceable>folder1 folder2 folder3</replaceable> "
"-o <replaceable>destdir</replaceable>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1200
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When three folders are merged then <replaceable>folder1</replaceable> is "
"used as the base for the merge. If no destination folder is specified, then "
"&kdiff3; will use <replaceable>folder3</replaceable> as the destination "
"folder for the merge."
msgstr ""
"Ko se združijo tri mape, se kot osnova za združevanje uporabi "
"<replaceable>mapa1</replaceable>. Če ciljna mapa ni navedena, potem bo "
"&kdiff3; kot ciljno mapo za združevanje uporabil <replaceable>mapo3</"
"replaceable>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1207
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Note that only the comparison starts automatically, not the merge. For this "
"you first must select a menu entry or the <keycap>F7</keycap> key. (More "
"details later.)"
msgstr ""
"Upoštevajte, da se samodejno začne samo primerjava, ne pa tudi združevanje. "
"Za to morate najprej izbrati vnos v meniju ali tipko <keycap>F7</keycap>. "
"(Več podrobnosti pozneje.)"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1214
#, no-c-format
msgid "Folder Merge Visible Information"
msgstr "Vidne informacije o združevanju map"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1215
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"While reading the folders a message-box appears that informs you of the "
"progress. If you abort the folder scan, then only files that have been "
"compared until then will be listed."
msgstr ""
"Med branjem map se prikaže okno s sporočilom, ki vas obvešča o napredku. Če "
"prekinete pregled mape, bodo prikazane samo datoteke, ki so bile do takrat "
"primerjane."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1219
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When the folder scan is complete then &kdiff3; will show a listbox with the "
"results left, ..."
msgstr ""
"Ko je pregled mape končan, &kdiff3; bo prikazalo seznamsko polje z rezultati "
"na levi, ..."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1226
#, no-c-format
msgid "... and details about the currently selected item on the right:"
msgstr "... in podrobnosti o trenutno izbranem artiklu na desni:"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1234
#, no-c-format
msgid "The Name Column"
msgstr "Stolpec z imenom"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1235
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Each file and folder that was found during the scan is shown here in a tree. "
"You can select an item by clicking it with the mouse once."
msgstr ""
"Vsaka datoteka in mapa, ki je bila najdena med prečesavanjem, je prikazana "
"tukaj v drevesu. Predmet lahko izberete tako, da ga enkrat kliknete z miško."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1238
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The folders are collapsed by default. You can expand and collapse them by "
"clicking on the \"+\"/\"-\" or by double-clicking the item or by using the "
"&Left;/&Right; cursor keys. The <guimenu>Folder</guimenu> menu also contains "
"two actions <guimenuitem>Fold All Subfolders</guimenuitem> and "
"<guimenuitem>Unfold All Subfolders</guimenuitem> with which you can collapse "
"or expand all folders at once."
msgstr ""
"Mape so privzeto strnjene. Lahko jih razširite in strnete s klikom na \"+\"/"
"\"-\" ali z dvojnim klikom na element ali z uporabo smerne tipke &Left;/"
"&Right;. Meni <guimenu>Mapa</guimenu> vsebuje tudi dve dejanji "
"<guimenuitem>Zloži vse podmape</guimenuitem> in <guimenuitem>Razgrni vse "
"podmape</guimenuitem>, s katerima lahko strnete ali razširite vse mape "
"hkrati."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1244
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you double-click a file item then the file comparison starts and the file-"
"diff-window will appear."
msgstr ""
"Če dvokliknete element datoteke, se začne primerjava datotek in prikaže se "
"okno razlik datotek."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1248
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The image in the name column reflects the file type in the first folder "
"(<guilabel>A</guilabel>). It can be one of these:"
msgstr ""
"Slika v stolpcu z imenom odraža vrsto datoteke v prvi mapi (<guilabel>A</"
"guilabel>). Lahko je eno od teh:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1253
#, no-c-format
msgid "Normal file"
msgstr "Normalna datoteka"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1254
#, no-c-format
msgid "Normal folder (folder image)"
msgstr "Običajna mapa (slika mape)"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1255
#, no-c-format
msgid "Link to a file (file image with a link arrow)"
msgstr "Povezava do datoteke (slika datoteke s puščico povezave)"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1256
#, no-c-format
msgid "Link to a folder (folder image with a link arrow)"
msgstr "Povezava do mape (slika mape s puščico povezave)"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1258
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If the file type is different in the other folders, then this is visible in "
"the columns <guilabel>A</guilabel>/<guilabel>B</guilabel>/<guilabel>C</"
"guilabel> and in the window that shows the details about the selected item. "
"Note that for such a case no merge operation can be selected automatically. "
"When starting the merge, then the user will be informed of problems of that "
"kind."
msgstr ""
"Če je vrsta datoteke v drugih mapah drugačna, je to vidno v stolpcih "
"<guilabel>A</guilabel>/<guilabel>B</guilabel>/<guilabel>C</guilabel> in v "
"oknu, ki prikazuje podrobnosti o izbranem predmetu. Upoštevajte, da v tem "
"primeru ni mogoče samodejno izbrati operacije združevanja. Ob začetku "
"spajanja bo uporabnik obveščen o tovrstnih težavah."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1267
#, no-c-format
msgid "The Columns A/B/C and the Coloring Scheme"
msgstr "Stolpci A/B/C in barvna shema"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1268
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"As can be seen in the image above the colors red, green, yellow and black "
"are used in the columns <guilabel>A</guilabel>/<guilabel>B</guilabel>/"
"<guilabel>C</guilabel>."
msgstr ""
"Kot lahko vidite na zgornji sliki, so v stolpcih <guilabel>A</guilabel>/"
"<guilabel>B</guilabel>/<guilabel>C</guilabel> uporabljene barve rdeča, "
"zelena, rumena in črna."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1273
#, no-c-format
msgid "Black: This item doesn't exist in this folder."
msgstr "Črna: ta element ne obstaja v tej mapi."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1274
#, no-c-format
msgid "Green: Newest item."
msgstr "Zelena: najnovejši predmet."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1275
#, no-c-format
msgid "Yellow: Older than green, newer than red."
msgstr "Rumena: Starejša od zelene, novejše od rdeče."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1276
#, no-c-format
msgid "Red: Oldest item."
msgstr "Rdeča: Najstarejši predmet."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1278
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"But for items that were identical in the comparison their color also is "
"identical even if the age is not."
msgstr ""
"Toda pri predmetih, ki so bili v primerjavi enaki, je tudi njihova barva "
"enaka, tudi če starost ni enaka."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1281
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Folders are considered equal if all items they contain are identical. Then "
"they also will have the same color. But the age of a folder is not "
"considered for its color."
msgstr ""
"Mape veljajo za enake, če so vsi elementi, ki jih vsebujejo, enaki. Potem "
"bodo tudi enake barve. Toda starost mape se ne upošteva pri njeni barvi."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1285
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The idea for this coloring scheme I came upon in <ulink url=\"https://www."
"samba.org/ftp/paulus/\"><command>dirdiff</command> command</ulink>. The "
"colors resemble the colors of a leaf that is green when new, turns yellow "
"later and red when old."
msgstr ""
"Na idejo za to barvno shemo sem naletel v <ulink url=\"https://www.samba.org/"
"ftp/paulus/\"><command>dirdiff</command> ukazu</ulink>. Barve so podobne "
"barvam lista, ki je zelen, ko je nov, postane kasneje rumen in rdeč, ko je "
"star."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1292
#, no-c-format
msgid "The Operation Column"
msgstr "Stolpec operacij"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1293
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"After comparing the folders &kdiff3; also evaluates a proposal for a merge "
"operation. This is shown in the <guilabel>Operation</guilabel> column. You "
"can modify the operation by clicking on the operation you want to change. A "
"small menu will popup and allows you to select an operation for that item. "
"(You can also select the most needed operations via keyboard. "
"<keycombo>&Ctrl;<keycap>1</keycap></keycombo>/<keycap>2</keycap>/<keycap>3</"
"keycap>/<keycap>4</keycap>/&Del; will select <guilabel>A</guilabel>/"
"<guilabel>B</guilabel>/<guilabel>C</guilabel>/<guilabel>Merge</guilabel>/ "
"<guilabel>Delete</guilabel> respectively if available.) This operation will "
"be executed during the merge. It depends on the item and on the merge-mode "
"you are in, what operations are available. The merge-mode is one of"
msgstr ""
"Po primerjavi map &kdiff3; oceni tudi predlog združitve. To je prikazano v "
"stolpcu <guilabel>Operacija</guilabel>. Operacijo lahko spremenite s klikom "
"na operacijo, ki jo želite spremeniti. Odpre se majhen meni, v katerem lahko "
"izberete operacijo za ta element. (Najbolj potrebne operacije lahko izberete "
"tudi s tipkovnico. <keycombo>&Ctrl;<keycap>1</keycap></keycombo>/<keycap>2</"
"keycap>/<keycap>3</keycap>/<keycap >4</keycap>/&Del; bo izbral <guilabel>A</"
"guilabel>/<guilabel>B</guilabel>/<guilabel>C</guilabel>/<guilabel>Združi</"
"guilabel>/ <guilabel> Izbriši</guilabel>, če je na voljo.) Ta operacija bo "
"izvedena med združevanjem. Katere operacije so na voljo, je odvisno od "
"predmeta in načina združevanja, v katerem ste. Način združevanja je le en "
"izmed"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1305
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Three-folder merge (<guilabel>A</guilabel> is treated as older base of both)."
msgstr ""
"Spajanje treh map (<guilabel>A</guilabel> se obravnava kot starejša osnova "
"obeh)."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1306
#, no-c-format
msgid "Two-folder merge."
msgstr "Spajanje dveh map."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1307
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Two-folder sync-mode (activate via <guilabel>Synchronize folders</guilabel> "
"option)."
msgstr ""
"Način sinhronizacije dveh map (aktivirajte prek možnosti "
"<guilabel>Sinhroniziraj mape</guilabel>)."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1309
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In three-folder merge the operation proposal will be: If for an item ..."
msgstr "Pri spajanju treh map bo predlog operacije: Če za element..."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1313
#, no-c-format
msgid "... all three folders are equal: Copy from <guilabel>C</guilabel>"
msgstr ".. vse tri mape so enake: Kopiraj iz <guilabel>C</guilabel>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1316
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"... <guilabel>A</guilabel> and <guilabel>C</guilabel> are equal but "
"<guilabel>B</guilabel> is not: Copy from <guilabel>B</guilabel> (or if "
"<guilabel>B</guilabel> does not exist, delete the destination if exists)"
msgstr ""
"... <guilabel>A</guilabel> in <guilabel>C</guilabel> sta enaka, vendar "
"<guilabel>B</guilabel> ni: Kopiraj iz <guilabel>B</guilabel> (ali če "
"<guilabel> B</guilabel> ne obstaja, izbriši cilj, če obstaja)"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1319
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"... <guilabel>A</guilabel> and <guilabel>B</guilabel> are equal but "
"<guilabel>C</guilabel> is not: Copy from <guilabel>C</guilabel> (or if "
"<guilabel>C</guilabel> does not exist, delete the destination if exists)"
msgstr ""
"... <guilabel>A</guilabel> in <guilabel>B</guilabel> sta enaka, <guilabel>C</"
"guilabel> pa ni: Kopiraj iz <guilabel>C</guilabel> (ali če <guilabel> C</"
"guilabel> ne obstaja, izbriši cilj, če obstaja)"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1322
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"... <guilabel>B</guilabel> and <guilabel>C</guilabel> are equal but "
"<guilabel>A</guilabel> is not: Copy from <guilabel>C</guilabel> (or if "
"<guilabel>C</guilabel> does not exist, delete the destination if exists)"
msgstr ""
"... <guilabel>B</guilabel> in <guilabel>C</guilabel> sta enaka, vendar "
"<guilabel>A</guilabel> ni: Kopiraj iz <guilabel>C</guilabel> (ali če "
"<guilabel> C</guilabel> ne obstaja, izbriši cilj, če obstaja)"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1325
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"... only <guilabel>A</guilabel> exists: Delete the destination (if exists)"
msgstr "... obstaja samo <guilabel>A</guilabel>: Izbriši cilj (če obstaja)"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1328
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"... only <guilabel>B</guilabel> exists: Copy from <guilabel>B</guilabel>"
msgstr ""
"... obstaja samo <guilabel>B</guilabel>: Kopiraj iz <guilabel>B</guilabel>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1331
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"... only <guilabel>C</guilabel> exists: Copy from <guilabel>C</guilabel>"
msgstr ""
"... obstaja samo <guilabel>C</guilabel>: Kopiraj iz <guilabel>C</guilabel>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1334
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"... <guilabel>A</guilabel>, <guilabel>B</guilabel> and <guilabel>C</"
"guilabel> are not equal: Merge"
msgstr ""
"... <guilabel>A</guilabel>, <guilabel>B</guilabel> in <guilabel>C</guilabel> "
"niso enaki: Združi"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1337
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"... <guilabel>A</guilabel>, <guilabel>B</guilabel> and <guilabel>C</"
"guilabel> don't have the same file type (&eg; <guilabel>A</guilabel> is a "
"folder, <guilabel>B</guilabel> is a file): \"Error: Conflicting File Types"
"\". While such items exist the folder merge cannot start."
msgstr ""
"... <guilabel>A</guilabel>, <guilabel>B</guilabel> in <guilabel>C</guilabel> "
"nimajo iste vrste datoteke (&eg; <guilabel>A</guilabel> je mapa, "
"<guilabel>B</guilabel> je datoteka): \"Napaka: Vrste datotek v nasprotju\". "
"Medtem ko taki elementi obstajajo, se združevanje map ne more začeti."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1341
#, no-c-format
msgid "In two-folder merge the operation proposal will be: If for an item ..."
msgstr "Pri spajanju dveh map bo predlog operacije: Če za element ..."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1345
#, no-c-format
msgid "... both folders are equal: Copy from <guilabel>B</guilabel>"
msgstr "... obe mapi sta enaki: Kopiraj iz <guilabel>B</guilabel>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1348
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"... <guilabel>A</guilabel> exists, but not <guilabel>B</guilabel>: Copy from "
"<guilabel>A</guilabel>"
msgstr ""
"... <guilabel>A</guilabel> obstaja, vendar ne <guilabel>B</guilabel>: "
"Kopiraj iz <guilabel>A</guilabel>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1351
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"... <guilabel>B</guilabel> exists, but not <guilabel>A</guilabel>: Copy from "
"<guilabel>B</guilabel>"
msgstr ""
"... <guilabel>B</guilabel> obstaja, vendar ne <guilabel>A</guilabel>: "
"Kopiraj iz <guilabel>B</guilabel>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1354
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"... <guilabel>A</guilabel> and <guilabel>B</guilabel> exist but are not "
"equal: Merge"
msgstr ""
"... <guilabel>A</guilabel> in <guilabel>B</guilabel> obstajata, vendar nista "
"enaka: Spoji"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1357 index.docbook:1380
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"... <guilabel>A</guilabel> and <guilabel>B</guilabel> don't have the same "
"file type (&eg; <guilabel>A</guilabel> is a folder, <guilabel>B</guilabel> "
"is a file): \"Error: Conflicting File Types\". While such items exist the "
"folder merge cannot start."
msgstr ""
"... <guilabel>A</guilabel> in <guilabel>B</guilabel> nimata iste vrste "
"datoteke (&eg; <guilabel>A</guilabel> je mapa, <guilabel>B</guilabel> > je "
"datoteka): \"Napaka: Vrste datotek v nasprotju\". Medtem ko taki elementi "
"obstajajo, se združevanje map ne more začeti."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1361
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Sync-mode is active if only two folders and no explicit destination were "
"specified and if the <guilabel>Synchronize folders</guilabel> option is "
"active. &kdiff3; then selects a default operation so that both folders are "
"the same afterwards. If for an item ..."
msgstr ""
"Način sinhronizacije je aktiven, če sta bili podani samo dve mapi in noben "
"izrecni cilj in če je aktivna možnost <guilabel>Sinhroniziraj mape</"
"guilabel>. &kdiff3; nato izbere privzeto operacijo, tako da sta pozneje obe "
"mapi enaki. Če za artikel ..."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1368
#, no-c-format
msgid "... both folders are equal: Nothing will be done."
msgstr "... obe mapi sta enakovredni: Ne bo narejeno ničesar."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1371
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"... <guilabel>A</guilabel> exists, but not <guilabel>B</guilabel>: Copy "
"<guilabel>A</guilabel> to <guilabel>B</guilabel>"
msgstr ""
"... <guilabel>A</guilabel> obstaja, vendar ne <guilabel>B</guilabel>: "
"Kopiraj <guilabel>A</guilabel> v <guilabel>B</guilabel>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1374
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"... <guilabel>B</guilabel> exists, but not <guilabel>A</guilabel>: Copy "
"<guilabel>B</guilabel> to <guilabel>A</guilabel>"
msgstr ""
"... <guilabel>B</guilabel> obstaja, vendar ne <guilabel>A</guilabel>: "
"Kopiraj <guilabel>B</guilabel> v <guilabel>A</guilabel>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1377
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"... <guilabel>A</guilabel> and <guilabel>B</guilabel> exist, but are not "
"equal: Merge and store the result in both folders. (For the user the visible "
"save-filename is <guilabel>B</guilabel>, but then &kdiff3; copies "
"<guilabel>B</guilabel> also to <guilabel>A</guilabel>.)"
msgstr ""
"... <guilabel>A</guilabel> in <guilabel>B</guilabel> obstajata, vendar nista "
"enaka: Spoji in shrani rezultat v obe mapi. (Za uporabnika je vidno ime "
"shranjevalne datoteke <guilabel>B</guilabel>, potem pa &kdiff3; prekopira "
"<guilabel>B</guilabel> tudi v <guilabel>A</guilabel>.)"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1384
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When two folders are merged and the <guilabel>Copy newer instead of merging "
"(unsafe)</guilabel> option is selected, then &kdiff3; looks at the dates and "
"proposes to choose the newer file. If the files are not equal but have equal "
"dates, then the operation will contain \"Error: Dates are equal but files "
"are not.\" While such items exist the folder merge cannot start."
msgstr ""
"Ko sta dve mapi združeni in je izbrana možnost <guilabel>Kopiraj novejše "
"namesto združevanja (nevarno)</guilabel>, potem &kdiff3; pogleda datume in "
"predlaga izbiro novejše datoteke. Če datoteke niso enake, vendar imajo enake "
"datume, bo operacija vsebovala \"Napaka: Datumi so enaki, datoteke pa ne.\" "
"Medtem ko taki elementi obstajajo, se združevanje map ne more začeti."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1389
#, no-c-format
msgid "The Status Column"
msgstr "Stolpec stanja"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1390
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"During the merge one file after the other will be processed. The status "
"column will show <guilabel>Done</guilabel> for items where the merge "
"operation has succeeded, and other texts if something unexpected happened. "
"When a merge is complete, then you should make a last check to see if the "
"status for all items is agreeable."
msgstr ""
"Med združevanjem bodo obdelane ena datoteka za drugo. V stolpcu stanja bo "
"prikazano <guilabel>Končano</guilabel> za elemente, pri katerih je bila "
"operacija združevanja uspešna, in druga besedila, če se zgodi kaj "
"nepričakovanega. Ko je združevanje končano, morate opraviti zadnji pregled, "
"da vidite, ali je stanje za vse elemente sprejemljivo."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1399
#, no-c-format
msgid "Statistics Columns"
msgstr "Statistični stolpci"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1400
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When the file comparison mode <guilabel>Full Analysis</guilabel> is enabled "
"in the options, then &kdiff3; will show extra columns containing the numbers "
"of Unsolved, Solved, Nonwhite and Whitespace conflicts. (The "
"<guilabel>Solved</guilabel> column will only show when comparing or merging "
"three folders.)"
msgstr ""
"Ko je v možnostih omogočen način primerjave datotek <guilabel>Popolna "
"analiza</guilabel>, &kdiff3; bodo prikazani dodatni stolpci s številom "
"nerešenih, rešenih, nebelih in belo prostornih sporov. (Stolpec "
"<guilabel>Rešeno</guilabel> bo prikazan samo pri primerjavi ali združevanju "
"treh map.)"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1407
#, no-c-format
msgid "Selecting Listed Files"
msgstr "Izbira navedenih datotek"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1408
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Several options influence which files are listed here. Some are accessible "
"in the <link linkend=\"dirmergeoptions\">settings dialog</link>. The "
"<guilabel>Folder</guilabel> menu contains the entries:"
msgstr ""
"Več možnosti vpliva na to, katere datoteke so tukaj navedene. Nekateri so "
"dostopni v <link linkend=\"dirmergeoptions\">pogovornem oknu z nastavitvami</"
"link>. Meni <guilabel>Mapa</guilabel> vsebuje vnose:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1412
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<guilabel>Show Identical Files</guilabel>: Files that have been detected "
"equal in all input folders."
msgstr ""
"<guilabel>Pokaži enake datoteke</guilabel>: Datoteke, ki so bile zaznane kot "
"enake v vseh vhodnih mapah."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1415
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<guilabel>Show Different Files</guilabel>: Files that exist in two or more "
"folders but are not equal."
msgstr ""
"<guilabel>Pokaži različne datoteke</guilabel>: Datoteke, ki obstajajo v dveh "
"ali več mapah, vendar niso enake."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1418
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<guilabel>Show Files only in A</guilabel>: Files that exist only in "
"<guilabel>A</guilabel>, but not in <guilabel>B</guilabel> or <guilabel>C</"
"guilabel>."
msgstr ""
"<guilabel>Prikaži datoteke samo v A</guilabel>: datoteke, ki obstajajo samo "
"v <guilabel>A</guilabel>, ne pa tudi v <guilabel>B</guilabel> ali "
"<guilabel>C</guilabel>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1421
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<guilabel>Show Files only in B</guilabel>: Files that exist only in "
"<guilabel>B</guilabel>, but not in <guilabel>A</guilabel> or <guilabel>C</"
"guilabel>."
msgstr ""
"<guilabel>Prikaži datoteke samo v B</guilabel>: datoteke, ki obstajajo samo "
"v <guilabel>B</guilabel>, ne pa tudi v <guilabel>A</guilabel> ali "
"<guilabel>C</guilabel>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1424
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<guilabel>Show Files only in C</guilabel>: Files that exist only in "
"<guilabel>C</guilabel>, but not in <guilabel>A</guilabel> or <guilabel>B</"
"guilabel>."
msgstr ""
"<guilabel>Prikaži datoteke samo v C</guilabel>: datoteke, ki obstajajo samo "
"v <guilabel>C</guilabel>, ne pa tudi v <guilabel>A</guilabel> ali "
"<guilabel>B</guilabel>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1428
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Activate only the <guilabel>Show</guilabel> options for the items you want "
"listed. If for example you only want to list all items that exist either in "
"<guilabel>A</guilabel> or in <guilabel>B</guilabel> but not in both, you'll "
"have to activate <guilabel>Show Files only in A</guilabel> and "
"<guilabel>Show Files only in B</guilabel> and deactivate all others "
"(<guilabel>Show Identical Files</guilabel>, <guilabel>Show Different Files</"
"guilabel>, <guilabel>Show Files only in C</guilabel>). The list will be "
"updated immediately to reflect the change."
msgstr ""
"Aktivirajte samo možnosti <guilabel>Pokaži</guilabel> za elemente, ki jih "
"želite na seznamu. Če na primer želite navesti samo vse elemente, ki "
"obstajajo v <guilabel>A</guilabel> ali v <guilabel>B</guilabel>, vendar ne v "
"obeh, boste morali aktivirati <guilabel>Prikaži datoteke samo v A</guilabel> "
"in <guilabel>Pokaži datoteke samo v B</guilabel> in deaktiviraj vse druge "
"(<guilabel>Pokaži enake datoteke</guilabel>, <guilabel>Pokaži različne "
"datoteke</guilabel>, <guilabel>Pokaži datoteke samo v C</guilabel>). Seznam "
"bo takoj posodobljen, da bo odražal spremembo."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1430
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"These options also apply for folders with one exception: Disabling "
"<guilabel> Show Different Files</guilabel> will not hide any complete "
"folders. This will work only for files within."
msgstr ""
"Te možnosti veljajo tudi za mape z eno izjemo: Če onemogočite <guilabel> "
"Pokaži različne datoteke</guilabel>, ne boste skrili nobene celotne mape. To "
"bo delovalo samo za datoteke znotraj."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1434
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Note that of these only the <guilabel>Show Identical Files</guilabel> option "
"is persistant. The others are enabled when starting &kdiff3;."
msgstr ""
"Upoštevajte, da je od teh samo možnost <guilabel>Pokaži enake datoteke</"
"guilabel> obstojna. Drugi so omogočeni ob zagonu &kdiff3;."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1442
#, no-c-format
msgid "Doing A Folder Merge"
msgstr "Izvajanje združevanja map"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1443
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can either merge the currently selected item (file or folder), or all "
"items. When you have made all your operation choices (in all subfolders too) "
"then you can start the merge."
msgstr ""
"Združujete lahko trenutno izbrani element (datoteko ali mapo) ali vse "
"elemente. Ko izberete vse svoje operacije (tudi v vseh podmapah), lahko "
"začnete združevanje."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1447
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Be aware that if you didn't specify a destination folder explicitly, then "
"the destination will be <guilabel>C</guilabel> in three-folder mode, "
"<guilabel>B</guilabel> in two-folder merge mode, and in sync-mode it will be "
"<guilabel>A</guilabel> or/and <guilabel>B</guilabel>."
msgstr ""
"Zavedajte se, da če ciljne mape niste izrecno določili, bo cilj <guilabel>C</"
"guilabel> v načinu treh map, <guilabel>B</guilabel> v načinu združevanja "
"dveh map in v sinhronizacijski način bo <guilabel>A</guilabel> ali/in "
"<guilabel>B</guilabel>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1449
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you have specified a destination folder also check that all items that "
"should be in the output, are in the tree. There are some options that cause "
"certain items to be omitted from the folder comparison and merge. Check "
"these options to avoid unpleasant surprises:"
msgstr ""
"Če ste določili ciljno mapo, preverite tudi, ali so vsi elementi, ki bi "
"morali biti v izhodu, v drevesu. Obstaja nekaj možnosti, zaradi katerih so "
"nekateri elementi izpuščeni iz primerjave in združevanja map. Preverite te "
"možnosti, da se izognete neprijetnim presenečenjem:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1456
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<guilabel>Recursive Folders</guilabel>: If this is off, then items in "
"subfolders will not be found."
msgstr ""
"<guilabel>Rekurzivne mape</guilabel>: če je to izklopljeno, elementov v "
"podmapah ne bo mogoče najti."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1457
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<guilabel>Pattern</guilabel>/<guilabel>Anti-Pattern</guilabel>: Include/"
"exclude items that match"
msgstr ""
"<guilabel>Vzorec</guilabel>/<guilabel>Protivzorec</guilabel>: Vključi/"
"izključi elemente, ki se ujemajo"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:1458
#, no-c-format
msgid "Exclude Hidden Files"
msgstr "Izključi skrite datoteke"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1459
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<link linkend=\"selectingvisiblefiles\">Show options</link> (<guilabel>Show "
"Identical/Different Files</guilabel>, <guilabel>Files only in A/B/C</"
"guilabel>)"
msgstr ""
"<link linkend=\"selectingvisiblefiles\">Pokaži možnosti</link> "
"(<guilabel>Pokaži enake/različne datoteke</guilabel>, <guilabel>Datoteke "
"samo v A/B/C</guilabel>)"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1461
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you change the settings in order to list more files, you must do a rescan "
"via menu <menuchoice><guimenu>Folder</guimenu><guimenuitem>Rescan</"
"guimenuitem> </menuchoice> yourself. (The reason for this is that for faster "
"comparison-speed &kdiff3; omits the comparison for files suppressed by these "
"criteria.) If you changed your file and folder patterns to exclude files, "
"then the file-list will immediately be updated on closing the options-dialog."
msgstr ""
"Če spremenite nastavitve, da prikažete seznam več datotek, morate sami "
"opraviti ponovno prečesavanje prek menija <menuchoice><guimenu>Mapa</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Ponovno skeniranje</guimenuitem> </menuchoice>. (Razlog "
"za to je, da zaradi hitrejše primerjave hitrosti &kdiff3; izpusti primerjavo "
"za datoteke, ki jih ti kriteriji zavrnejo.) Če ste spremenili vzorce datotek "
"in map, da izključite datoteke, bo seznam datotek takoj posodobljen, ko "
"zaprete dialog možnosti."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1468
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Note that when you write to a completely new folder then you usually also "
"want to copy the identical files. In that case enable the <guilabel>Show "
"Identical Files</guilabel> option. If your destination folder is one of the "
"inputs, then this isn't necessary because the file is already there."
msgstr ""
"Upoštevajte, da ko pišete v popolnoma novo mapo, običajno želite kopirati "
"tudi enake datoteke. V tem primeru omogočite možnost <guilabel>Pokaži enake "
"datoteke</guilabel>. Če je vaša ciljna mapa eden od vnosov, potem to ni "
"potrebno, ker je datoteka že tam."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1472
#, no-c-format
msgid "If you are satisfied so far, the rest is easy."
msgstr "Če ste do sedaj zadovoljni, je ostalo enostavno."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1474
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To merge all items: Select <guimenuitem>Start/Continue Folder Merge</"
"guimenuitem> in the <guimenu>Folder</guimenu> menu or press <keycap>F7</"
"keycap> (which is the default shortcut). To merge only the current item: "
"Select <guilabel>Run Operation for Current Item</guilabel> or press "
"<keycap>F6</keycap>."
msgstr ""
"Če želite združiti vse elemente: izberite <guimenuitem>Začni/Nadaljuj "
"združevanje mape</guimenuitem> v meniju <guimenu>Mapa</guimenu> ali "
"pritisnite <keycap>F7</keycap> (kar je privzeta bližnjica). Če želite "
"združiti samo trenutni element: izberite <guilabel>Zaženi operacijo za "
"trenutnem elementu</guilabel> ali pritisnite <keycap>F6</keycap>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1479
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If due to conflicting filetypes some items with invalid operations still "
"exist, then a messagebox will appear and these items will be pointed out, so "
"you can select a valid operation for the item."
msgstr ""
"Če zaradi nasprotujočih si vrst datotek nekateri elementi z neveljavnimi "
"operacijami še vedno obstajajo, se bo prikazalo sporočilo in ti elementi "
"bodo označeni, tako da lahko izberete veljavno operacijo za element."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1483
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you merge all items a dialog will appear giving you the options "
"<guilabel>Do it</guilabel>, <guilabel>Simulate it</guilabel> and "
"<guilabel>Cancel</guilabel>."
msgstr ""
"Če združujete vse elemente, se prikaže pogovorno okno z možnostmi "
"<guilabel>Naredi</guilabel>, <guilabel>Simuliraj</guilabel> in "
"<guilabel>Prekliči</guilabel>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1489
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Select <guilabel>Simulate it</guilabel> if you want to see what would be "
"done without actually doing it. A verbose list of all operations will be "
"shown."
msgstr ""
"Izberite <guilabel>Simuliraj</guilabel>, če želite videti, kaj bi naredili, "
"ne da bi tega dejansko storili. Prikazan bo podroben seznam vseh operacij."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1491
#, no-c-format
msgid "Otherwise select <guilabel>Do it</guilabel> to really start merging."
msgstr ""
"V nasprotnem primeru izberite <guilabel>Naredi to</guilabel>, da resnično "
"začnete združevati."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1493
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Then &kdiff3; will run the specified operation for all items. If manual "
"interaction is required (single file merge), then a merge window will open "
"(<link linkend=\"dirmergebigscreenshot\">see the big screenshot</link>)."
msgstr ""
"Nato bo &kdiff3; izvedel navedeno operacijo za vse elemente. Če je potrebna "
"ročna interakcija (združitev ene datoteke), se odpre okno za združevanje "
"(<link linkend=\"dirmergebigscreenshot\">glejte velik posnetek zaslona</"
"link>)."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1497
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When you have finished with manually merging a file, again select "
"<guimenuitem>Start/ Continue Folder Merge</guimenuitem> or the <keycap>F7</"
"keycap> key. If you haven't saved it yet, a dialog will ask you to do so. "
"Then &kdiff3; will continue with the next item."
msgstr ""
"Ko končate z ročnim združevanjem datoteke, ponovno izberite "
"<guimenuitem>Začni/Nadaljuj združevanje map</guimenuitem> ali tipko "
"<keycap>F7</keycap>. Če ga še niste shranili, vas bo pogovorno okno pozvalo, "
"da to storite. Nato bo &kdiff3; nadaljeval z naslednjim elementom."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1502
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When &kdiff3; encounters an error, it will tell you so and will show the "
"verbose-status-information. At the bottom of this list, there will be some "
"error messages which should help you to understand the cause of the problem. "
"When you continue merging (<keycap>F7</keycap> key) &kdiff3; will give you "
"the choice to retry or skip the item that caused the problem. This means "
"that before continuing you can choose another operation or solve the problem "
"by other means."
msgstr ""
"Ko &kdiff3; naleti na napako, vam bo to povedal in prikazal verbose-status-"
"information. Na dnu tega seznama bo nekaj sporočil o napakah, ki vam bodo "
"pomagali razumeti vzrok težave. Ko nadaljujete z združevanjem (tipka "
"<keycap>F7</keycap>) &kdiff3; vam bo ponudil možnost, da poskusite znova ali "
"preskočite element, ki je povzročil težavo. To pomeni, da lahko pred "
"nadaljevanjem izberete drugo operacijo ali rešite težavo na drug način."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1509
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When the merge is complete, then &kdiff3; will inform you via a message box."
msgstr ""
"Ko je združevanje končano, vas bo &kdiff3; obvestil preko sporočilnega polja."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1512
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If some items were merged individually before running the directorymerge "
"then &kdiff3; remembers this (while this merge-session goes on), and doesn't "
"merge them again when later the merge for all items is run. Even when the "
"merge was skipped or nothing was saved these items count as completed. Only "
"when you change the merge operation the <guilabel>Done</guilabel> status of "
"the item will be removed and it can be merged again."
msgstr ""
"Če so bili nekateri elementi združeni posamezno pred zagonom directorymerge, "
"potem &kdiff3; si to zapomni (medtem ko teče ta združevalna seja) in jih ne "
"združi znova, ko se pozneje izvede združevanje za vse elemente. Tudi če je "
"bilo spajanje preskočeno ali ni bilo nič shranjeno, se ti elementi štejejo "
"kot dokončani. Šele ko spremenite operacijo spajanja, bo status "
"<guilabel>Končano</guilabel> elementa odstranjen in ga bo mogoče znova "
"združiti."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1522
#, no-c-format
msgid "Options for Comparing and Merging Folders"
msgstr "Možnosti za primerjavo in združevanje map"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1523
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The &kdiff3; preferences (menu <menuchoice><guimenu>Settings</guimenu> "
"<guimenuitem>Configure &kdiff3;...</guimenuitem></menuchoice>) has a section "
"called \"Folder Merge\" with these options:"
msgstr ""
"&kdiff3; nastavitve (meni <menuchoice><guimenu>Nastavitve</guimenu> "
"<guimenuitem>Konfiguriraj &kdiff3;...</guimenuitem></menuchoice>) ima "
"razdelek z imenom \"Združevanje map\" s temi možnostmi:"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:1530
#, no-c-format
msgid "Recursive folders"
msgstr "Rekurzivne mape"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1530
#, no-c-format
msgid "Select whether to search folders recursively."
msgstr "Izberite, ali želite po mapah iskati rekurzivno."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:1532
#, no-c-format
msgid "File pattern(s):"
msgstr "Vzorci datotek:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1532
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Only files that match any pattern here will be put in the tree. More than "
"one pattern may be specified here by using the semicolon \";\" as separator. "
"Valid wildcards: '*' and '?'. (&eg; \"<literal>*.cpp;*.h</literal>\"). "
"Default is \"*\". This pattern is not used on folders."
msgstr ""
"V drevo bodo postavljene samo datoteke, ki se ujemajo s katerim koli vzorcem "
"tukaj. Tukaj lahko določite več kot en vzorec z uporabo podpičja \";\" kot "
"ločilo. Veljavni nadomestni znaki: '*' in '?'. (&eg;. \"<literal>*.cpp;*.h</"
"literal>\"). Privzeto je \"*\". Ta vzorec se ne uporablja za mape."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:1536
#, no-c-format
msgid "File-anti-pattern(s):"
msgstr "Datotečni proti-vzorci:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1536
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Files that match this pattern will be excluded from the tree. More than one "
"pattern may be specified here via using the semicolon \";\" as separator. "
"Valid wildcards: '*' and '?'. Default is \"<literal>*.orig;*.o;*.obj</"
"literal>\"."
msgstr ""
"Datoteke, ki ustrezajo temu vzorcu, bodo izključene iz drevesa. Tukaj lahko "
"določite več kot en vzorec z uporabo podpičja \";\" kot ločila. Veljavni "
"nadomestni znaki: '*' in '?'. Privzeto je \"<literal>*.orig;*.o;*.obj</"
"literal>\"."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:1540
#, no-c-format
msgid "Folder-anti-pattern(s):"
msgstr "Anti-vzorci map:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1540
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Folders that match this pattern will be excluded from the tree. More than "
"one pattern may be specified here via using the semicolon \";\" as "
"separator. Valid wildcards: '*' and '?'. Default is \"<literal>CVS;deps;."
"svn</literal>\"."
msgstr ""
"Mape, ki se ujemajo s tem vzorcem, bodo izključene iz drevesa. Tukaj lahko "
"določite več kot en vzorec z uporabo podpičja \";\" kot ločila. Veljavni "
"nadomestni znaki: '*' in '?'. Privzeto je \"<literal>CVS;deps;.svn</literal>"
"\"."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:1544
#, no-c-format
msgid "Use Ignore File"
msgstr "Uporabite Prezri datoteko"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1544
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Ignore files and folders that would also be ignored by the your source "
"control. Many automatically generated files are ignored using ignore lists. "
"The big advantage is that this can be folder-specific via a local ignore "
"file. (See version control docs for more detail.)"
msgstr ""
"Prezrite datoteke in mape, ki bi jih prezrl tudi vaš nadzor vira. Številne "
"samodejno ustvarjene datoteke so prezrte s seznami prezrtih. Velika prednost "
"je, da je to lahko specifično za mapo prek lokalne datoteke za prezrtje. (Za "
"več podrobnosti si oglejte dokumente za nadzor različic.)"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:1550
#, no-c-format
msgid "Find hidden files and folders"
msgstr "Poiščite skrite datoteke in mape"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1550
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"On some file systems files have an \"Hidden\"-attribute. On other systems a "
"filename starting with a dot \".\" causes it to be hidden. This option "
"allows you to decide whether to include these files in the tree or not. "
"Default is on."
msgstr ""
"V nekaterih datotečnih sistemih imajo datoteke atribut \"Skrita (Hidden)\". "
"Na drugih sistemih ime datoteke, ki se začne s piko \".\" povzroči, da se "
"skrije. Ta možnostvam omogoča, da se odločite, ali želite te datoteke "
"vključiti v drevo ali ne.Privzeto je vklopljeno."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:1554
#, no-c-format
msgid "Follow file links"
msgstr "Sledite povezavam datotek"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1554
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For links to files: When disabled, then the symbolic links are compared. "
"When enabled, then the files behind the links are compared. Default is off."
msgstr ""
"Za povezave do datotek: Ko je onemogočeno, se primerjajo simbolične "
"povezave. Ko je omogočeno, se primerjajo datoteke za povezavami. Privzeto je "
"izklopljeno."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:1557
#, no-c-format
msgid "Follow folder links"
msgstr "Sledite povezavam map"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1557
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For links to folders: When disabled, then the symbolic links will be "
"compared. When enabled then the link will be treated like a folder and it "
"will be scanned recursively. (Note that the program doesn't check if the "
"link is \"recursive\". So for example a folder that contains a link to the "
"folder would cause an infinite loop, and after some time when the stack "
"overflows or all memory is used up, crash the program.) Default is off."
msgstr ""
"Za povezave do map: Ko je onemogočeno, bodo simbolične povezave primerjane. "
"Ko je omogočeno, bo povezava obravnavana kot mapa in bo pregledana "
"rekurzivno. (Upoštevajte, da program ne preveri, ali je povezava \"rekurzivna"
"\". Tako bi na primer mapa, ki vsebuje povezavo do mape, povzročila "
"neskončno zanko in čez nekaj časa, ko se sklad prelije ali je ves pomnilnik "
"porabljen, zruši program.) Privzeto je izklopljeno."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:1564
#, no-c-format
msgid "Case sensitive filename comparison"
msgstr "Primerjava imen datotek, občutljiva na velike in male črke"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1564
#, no-c-format
msgid "Default is false on &Windows;, true for other operating systems."
msgstr ""
"Privzeta vrednost je false v &Windows;, true za druge operacijske sisteme."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:1566
#, no-c-format
msgid "File Comparison Mode:"
msgstr "Način primerjave datotek:"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:1568
#, no-c-format
msgid "Binary comparison"
msgstr "Binarna primerjava"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1568
#, no-c-format
msgid "This is the default file comparison mode."
msgstr "To je privzeti način primerjave datotek."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:1571
#, no-c-format
msgid "Full analysis"
msgstr "Popolna analiza"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1571
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Do a full analysis of each file and show the statistics information columns. "
"(Number of <guilabel>Solved</guilabel>, <guilabel>Unsolved</guilabel>, "
"<guilabel>Nonwhite</guilabel> and <guilabel>White</guilabel> conflicts.) The "
"full analysis is slower than a simple binary analysis, and much slower when "
"used on files that don't contain text. (Specify the appropriate file-"
"antipatterns.)"
msgstr ""
"Izvedite popolno analizo vsake datoteke in prikažite stolpce s statističnimi "
"informacijami. (Število <guilabel>rešenih</guilabel>, <guilabel>nerešenih</"
"guilabel>, <guilabel>nebelih</guilabel> in <guilabel>belih</guilabel> "
"konfliktov.) Popolna analiza je počasnejša od preproste dvojiške analiza in "
"veliko počasnejši pri uporabi v datotekah, ki ne vsebujejo besedila. "
"(Določite ustrezne protivzorce datotek.)"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:1579
#, no-c-format
msgid "Trust the size and modification date (unsafe)"
msgstr "Zaupaj velikosti in datumu spremembe (nevarno)"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1579
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you compare big folders over a slow network, it might be faster to "
"compare the modification dates and file length alone. But this speed "
"improvement comes with the price of a little uncertainty. Use this option "
"with care. Default is off."
msgstr ""
"Če primerjate velike mape prek počasnega omrežja, bo morda hitreje "
"primerjati samo datume sprememb in dolžino datoteke. Toda to izboljšanje "
"hitrosti prihaja s ceno majhne negotovosti. To možnost uporabljajte "
"previdno. Privzeto je izklopljeno."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:1584
#, no-c-format
msgid "Trust the size (unsafe)"
msgstr "Zaupajte velikosti (nevarno)"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1584
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Similar to trusting the modification date. No real comparison happens. Two "
"files are considered equal if their file-sizes are equal. This is useful "
"when the file-copy operation didn't preserve the modification date. Use this "
"option with care. Default is off."
msgstr ""
"Podobno kot pri zaupanju v datum spremembe. Tu do prave primerjave ne pride. "
"Dve datoteki veljata za enaki, če sta njuni velikosti datotek enaki. To je "
"uporabno, če operacija kopiranja datoteke ni ohranila datuma spremembe. To "
"možnost uporabljajte previdno. Privzeto je izklopljeno."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:1591
#, no-c-format
msgid "Synchronize folders"
msgstr "Sinhronizirajte mape"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1591
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Activates sync-mode when two folders are compared and no explicit "
"destination folder was specified. In this mode the proposed operations will "
"be chosen so that both source folders are equal afterwards. Also the merge "
"result will be written to both folders. Default is off."
msgstr ""
"Aktivira sinhronizacijski način, ko se primerjata dve mapi in ni bila "
"določena izrecna ciljna mapa. V tem načinu bodo predlagane operacije izbrane "
"tako, da sta obe izvorni mapi pozneje enaki. Tudi rezultat združevanja bo "
"zapisan v obe mapi. Privzeto je izklopljeno."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:1596
#, no-c-format
msgid "Copy newer instead of merging (unsafe)"
msgstr "Kopiraj novejše namesto združevanja (nevarno)"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1596
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Instead of merging the proposed operation will copy the newer source if "
"changes happened. (Considered unsafe, because it implies that you know, that "
"the other file hasn't been edited too. Check to make sure in every case.) "
"Default is off."
msgstr ""
"Namesto združevanja bo predlagana operacija kopirala novejši vir, če pride "
"do sprememb. (Šteje za nevarno, ker pomeni, da veste, da tudi druga datoteka "
"ni bila urejena. V vsakem primeru preverite, da se prepričate.) Privzeto je "
"izklopljeno."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1600
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If a file or complete folder is replaced by another or is deleted then the "
"original version will be renamed with an <literal role=\"extension\">.orig</"
"literal> extension. If an old backup file with <literal role=\"extension\">."
"orig</literal> extension already exists then this will be deleted without "
"backup. This also affects the normal merging of single files, not only in "
"folder-merge mode. Default is on."
msgstr ""
"Če je datoteka ali celotna mapa zamenjana z drugo ali je izbrisana, bo "
"prvotna različica preimenovana s pripono <literal role=\"extension\">.orig</"
"literal>. Če stara datoteka varnostne kopije s končnico <literal role="
"\"extension\">.orig</literal> že obstaja, bo ta izbrisana brez varnostne "
"kopije. To vpliva tudi na običajno združevanje posameznih datotek, ne samo v "
"načinu združevanja map. Privzeto je vklopljeno."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1610
#, no-c-format
msgid "Other Functions in Folder Merge Window"
msgstr "Druge funkcije v oknu za združevanje map"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1611
#, no-c-format
msgid "Split/Full Screen Mode"
msgstr "Razdeljeni/celozaslonski način"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1612
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Usually the folder-merge list view remains visible while a single file is "
"compared or merged. With the mouse you can move the splitter bar that "
"separates the file list from the text-diff windows. If you don't want this, "
"you can disable <menuchoice><guimenu>Folder</guimenu><guimenuitem>Folder "
"&amp;&amp; Text Split Screen View</guimenuitem></menuchoice> menu item. Then "
"you can use <menuchoice><guimenu>Folder</guimenu><guimenuitem>Toggle View</"
"guimenuitem></menuchoice> menu item to switch between the file list and the "
"text-diff view that then occupy the full screen."
msgstr ""
"Običajno pogled seznama z združevanjem map ostane viden, medtem ko se ena "
"datoteka primerja ali združuje. Z miško lahko premikate razdelilno vrstico, "
"ki ločuje seznam datotek od oken za razlikovanje besedila. Če tega ne "
"želite, lahko onemogočite <menuchoice><guimenu>Mapa</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Mapa &amp;&amp; Element menija Pogled razdeljenega "
"zaslona besedila</guimenuitem></menuchoice>. Nato lahko uporabite element "
"menija <menuchoice><guimenu>Mapa</guimenu><guimenuitem>Preklopi pogled</"
"guimenuitem></menuchoice>, da preklapljate med seznamom datotek in pogledom "
"besedilne razlike, ki nato zavzameta celoten zaslon."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1616
#, no-c-format
msgid "Comparing or Merging a Single File"
msgstr "Primerjava ali združevanje ene datoteke"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1617
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Probably you will prefer a simple double mouse click on a file in order to "
"compare it. Nevertheless there also exists an entry in the <guimenu>Folder</"
"guimenu> menu. You can also directly merge a single file by selecting it and "
"choosing <menuchoice><guimenu>Merge</guimenu><guimenuitem>Merge Current "
"File</guimenuitem></menuchoice> menu item. On saving the result, the status "
"will be set to done, and the file will not be merged again if a folder merge "
"is started."
msgstr ""
"Verjetno vam bo ljubši preprost dvojni klik na datoteko, da jo primerjate. "
"Kljub temu obstaja tudi vnos v meniju <guimenu>Mapa</guimenu>. Posamezno "
"datoteko lahko tudi neposredno združite tako, da jo izberete in izberete "
"menijsko postavko <menuchoice><guimenu>Združi</guimenu><guimenuitem>Združi "
"trenutno datoteko</guimenuitem></menuchoice>. Ko shranite rezultat, bo "
"status nastavljen na dokončano in datoteka ne bo ponovno združena, če se "
"začne združevanje map."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1624
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"But note that this status information will be lost when you rerun a folder "
"scan: <menuchoice><guimenu>Folder</guimenu><guimenuitem>Rescan</"
"guimenuitem></menuchoice>"
msgstr ""
"Vendar upoštevajte, da bodo te informacije o stanju izgubljene, ko znova "
"zaženete prečesavanje mape: <menuchoice><guimenu>Mapa</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Ponovno prečesavanje</guimenuitem></menuchoice>"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1629
#, no-c-format
msgid "Comparing or Merging Files with Different Names"
msgstr "Primerjava ali združevanje datotek z različnimi imeni"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1630
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Sometimes you need to compare or merge files with different names (&eg; the "
"current file and the backup in the same folder)."
msgstr ""
"Včasih morate primerjati ali združiti datoteke z različnimi imeni (&eg; "
"trenutno datoteko in varnostno kopijo v isti mapi)."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1633
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Select the exact file by clicking onto the icon in the column <guilabel>A</"
"guilabel>, <guilabel>B</guilabel> or <guilabel>C</guilabel>. The first file "
"selected thus will be marked with an <guilabel>A</guilabel>, the second and "
"third with <guilabel>B</guilabel> and <guilabel>C</guilabel> regardless on "
"what column they are in. Only up to three files can be chosen like this."
msgstr ""
"Izberite točno datoteko s klikom na ikono v stolpcu <guilabel>A</guilabel>, "
"<guilabel>B</guilabel> ali <guilabel>C</guilabel>. Tako izbrana prva "
"datoteka bo označena z <guilabel>A</guilabel>, druga in tretja pa z "
"<guilabel>B</guilabel> in <guilabel>C</guilabel> ne glede na to, v katerem "
"stolpcu sta. tako lahko izberete do tri datoteke."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1635
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Proceed by choosing <menuchoice><guimenu>Folder</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Compare Explicitly Selected Files</guimenuitem></"
"menuchoice> or <menuchoice><guimenu>Folder</guimenu><guimenuitem>Merge "
"Explicitly Selected Files</guimenuitem></menuchoice> menu item. For your "
"convenience these menu entries also appear as context menu when you right-"
"click the last selected file."
msgstr ""
"Nadaljujte z izbiro <menuchoice><guimenu>Mapa</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Primerjaj izrecno izbrane datoteke</guimenuitem></"
"menuchoice> ali <menuchoice><guimenu>Mapa</guimenu><guimenuitem>Združi "
"izrecno izbrane datoteke</guimenuitem></menuchoice> element menija. Za vaše "
"udobje se ti vnosi menija prikažejo tudi kot kontekstni meni, ko z desno "
"miškino tipko kliknete zadnjo izbrano datoteko."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1637
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The comparison or merge of a file will happen in the same window. If this "
"method is used for folders a new window will be opened."
msgstr ""
"Primerjava ali združitev datoteke se bo zgodila v istem oknu. Če ta način "
"uporabite za mape, se odpre novo okno."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1645
#, no-c-format
msgid "Miscellaneous Topics"
msgstr "Razne teme"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1647
#, no-c-format
msgid "Network transparency via KIO"
msgstr "Preglednost omrežja preko KIO"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1648
#, no-c-format
msgid "KIO-Slaves"
msgstr "KIO-Sužnji"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1649
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The KIO library from &frameworks; supports network transparency via KIO-"
"slaves. &kdiff3; uses this for reading input files and for scanning folders. "
"This means that you can specify files and folders on local and remote "
"resources via &URL;s."
msgstr ""
"Knjižnica KIO iz &frameworks; podpira preglednost omrežja prek podrejenih "
"KIO. &kdiff3; uporablja to za branje vhodnih datotek in za preiskovanje map. "
"To pomeni, da lahko določite datoteke in mape na lokalnih in oddaljenih "
"virih prek &URL;s."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1654
#, no-c-format
msgid "Example:"
msgstr "Primer:"

#. Tag: screen
#: index.docbook:1657
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<command>kdiff3</command> test.cpp  ftp://ftp.faraway.org/test.cpp\n"
"   <command>kdiff3</command> tar:/home/hacker/archive.tar.gz/folder ./folder"
msgstr ""
"<command>kdiff3</command> test.cpp ftp://ftp.faraway.org/test.cpp\n"
"<command>kdiff3</command> tar:/home/hacker/archive.tar.gz/folder ./folder"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1659
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The first line compares a local file with a file on an &FTP; server. The "
"second line compares a folder within an compressed archive with a local "
"folder."
msgstr ""
"Prva vrstica primerja lokalno datoteko z datoteko na &FTP; strežniku. Druga "
"vrstica primerja mapo znotraj stisnjenega arhiva z lokalno mapo."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1661
#, no-c-format
msgid "Other KIO-slaves that are interesting are:"
msgstr "Drugi KIO-sužnji, ki so zanimivi, so:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1665
#, no-c-format
msgid "Files from the WWW (http:),"
msgstr "Datoteke iz WWW (http:),"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1666
#, no-c-format
msgid "Files from the &FTP; (ftp:),"
msgstr "Datoteke iz &FTP; (ftp:),"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1667
#, no-c-format
msgid "Encrypted file transfer (fish:, sftp:),"
msgstr "Šifriran prenos datotek (fish:, sftp:),"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1668
#, no-c-format
msgid "&Windows; resources (smb:),"
msgstr "&Windows; viri (smb:),"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1669
#, no-c-format
msgid "Local files (file:),"
msgstr "Lokalne datoteke (datoteka:),"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1671
#, no-c-format
msgid "Other things that are possible, but probably less useful are:"
msgstr "Druge stvari, ki so možne, a verjetno manj uporabne, so:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1675
#, no-c-format
msgid "Man-pages (man:),"
msgstr "Man-strani (man:),"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1676
#, no-c-format
msgid "Info-pages (info:),"
msgstr "Info-strani (info:),"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1680
#, no-c-format
msgid "How To Write &URL;s"
msgstr "Kako napisati &URL;s"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1681
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"An &URL; has a different syntax compared with paths for local files and "
"folders. Some things should be considered:"
msgstr ""
"&URL; ima drugačno sintakso v primerjavi s potmi za lokalne datoteke in "
"mape. Nekaj stvari je treba upoštevati:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1686
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A path can be relative and can contain \".\" or \"..\". This is not possible "
"for &URL;s which are always absolute."
msgstr ""
"Pot je lahko relativna in lahko vsebuje \".\" ali \"..\". To ni mogoče za "
"&URL;, ki so vedno absolutni."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1689
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Special characters must be written with \"escaping\". (\"<literal>#</literal>"
"\" -&gt; \"<literal>%23</literal>\", space -&gt;\"<literal>%20</literal>\", "
"&etc;) E.g. a file with the name \"<literal>#</literal>foo<literal>#</"
"literal>\" would have the &URL; \"file:/<literal>%23</literal>foo<literal>"
"%23</literal>\"."
msgstr ""
"Posebni znaki morajo biti zapisani s \"pobegom\". (\"<literal>#</literal>\" -"
"&gt; \"<literal>%23</literal>\", presledek -&gt;\"<literal>%20</literal>\", "
"itd.) Npr. datoteka z imenom \"<literal>#</literal>foo<literal>#</literal>\" "
"bi imela &URL; \"datoteka:/<literal>%23</literal>foo<literal>%23</literal>\"."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1692
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When &URL;s don't work as expected, try to open them in &konqueror; first."
msgstr ""
"Ko &URL;-ji ne delujejo po pričakovanjih, jih poskusite najprej odpreti v "
"&konqueror;."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1699
#, no-c-format
msgid "Capabilities of KIO-Slaves"
msgstr "Zmogljivosti KIO-Slaves"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1700
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Network transparency has one drawback: Not all resources have the same "
"capabilities."
msgstr ""
"Preglednost omrežja ima eno pomanjkljivost: vsi viri nimajo enakih "
"zmogljivosti."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1702
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Sometimes this is due to the file system of the server, sometimes due to the "
"protocol. Here is a short list of restrictions:"
msgstr ""
"Včasih je to posledica datotečnega sistema strežnika, včasih zaradi "
"protokola. Tukaj je kratek seznam omejitev:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1707
#, no-c-format
msgid "Sometimes there is no support for links."
msgstr "Včasih ni podpore za povezave."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1709
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Or there is no way to distinguish if a link points to a file or a folder; "
"always assuming a file. (ftp:, sftp:)."
msgstr ""
"Ali pa ni mogoče razločiti, ali povezava kaže na datoteko ali mapo; vedno "
"predpostavlja datoteko. (ftp:, sftp:)."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1712
#, no-c-format
msgid "Can't always determine the filesize."
msgstr "Velikosti datoteke ni mogoče vedno določiti."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1714
#, no-c-format
msgid "Limited support for permissions."
msgstr "Omejena podpora za dovoljenja."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1716
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"No possibility to modify permissions or modification time, so permissions or "
"time of a copy will differ from the original. (See the <guilabel>Trust the "
"size (unsafe)</guilabel> option.) (To modify permissions or modification "
"time is only possible for local files.)"
msgstr ""
"Ni možnosti spreminjanja dovoljenj ali časa spreminjanja, zato se bodo "
"dovoljenja ali čas kopije razlikovali od izvirnika. (Glejte možnost "
"<guilabel>Zaupajte velikosti (nevarno)</guilabel>.) (Spreminjanje dovoljenj "
"ali časa spreminjanja je možno samo za lokalne datoteke.)"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1726
#, no-c-format
msgid "Using &kdiff3; as a &git; Diff and Merging Tool"
msgstr "Uporaba &kdiff3; kot &git; Orodje za razlikovanje in spajanje"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1727
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kdiff3; can be used as a <ulink url=\"https://git-scm.com/\">&git;</ulink> "
"diff and merge tool."
msgstr ""
"&kdiff3; se lahko uporablja kot <ulink url=\"https://git-scm.com/\">&git;</"
"ulink> orodje za razlikovanje in spajanje."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1730
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Just add the following lines into your <filename>gitconfig</filename> file."
msgstr ""
"Samo dodajte naslednje vrstice v datoteko <filename>gitconfig</filename>."

#. Tag: programlisting
#: index.docbook:1733
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"[diff]\n"
"        tool = kdiff3\n"
"[difftool \"kdiff3\"]\n"
"        path = &lt;path to kdiff3 binary in your system>\n"
"[difftool]\n"
"        prompt = false\n"
"        keepBackup = false\n"
"        trustExitCode = false\n"
"[merge]\n"
"        tool = kdiff3\n"
"[mergetool]\n"
"        prompt = false\n"
"        keepBackup = false\n"
"        keepTemporaries = false\n"
"[mergetool \"kdiff3\"]\n"
"        path = &lt;path to kdiff3 binary in your system>"
msgstr ""
"[diff]\n"
"        tool = kdiff3\n"
"[difftool \"kdiff3\"]\n"
"        path = &lt;path to kdiff3 binary in your system>\n"
"[difftool]\n"
"        prompt = false\n"
"        keepBackup = false\n"
"        trustExitCode = false\n"
"[merge]\n"
"        tool = kdiff3\n"
"[mergetool]\n"
"        prompt = false\n"
"        keepBackup = false\n"
"        keepTemporaries = false\n"
"[mergetool \"kdiff3\"]\n"
"        path = &lt;path to kdiff3 binary in your system>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1734
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Then to see the difference between two commits use <userinput>git difftool "
"<replaceable>first_hash</replaceable> <replaceable>second_hash</replaceable> "
"--tool=kdiff3 --cc <replaceable>some_file_in_the_git_tree</replaceable></"
"userinput>"
msgstr ""
"Če želite nato videti razliko med dvema objavama, uporabite <userinput>git "
"difftool <replaceable>first_hash</replaceable> <replaceable>second_hash</"
"replaceable> --tool=kdiff3 --cc <replaceable>some_file_in_the_git_tree</"
"replaceable></userinput>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1737
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To merge a branch with &kdiff3; use <userinput>git merge "
"<replaceable>branch_name</replaceable> &amp;&amp; git mergetool --"
"tool=kdiff3</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"Za združitev veje z &kdiff3; uporabite <userinput>git merge "
"<replaceable>branch_name</replaceable> &amp;&amp; git mergetool --"
"tool=kdiff3</userinput>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1740
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"After resolving merging conflicts in the <link linkend=\"synchronise_views"
"\">usual way</link> it is enough to commit the changes to do the job."
msgstr ""
"Po razrešitvi sporov pri združevanju na <link linkend=\"synchronise_views"
"\">običajen način</link> je dovolj, da odobrite spremembe, da opravite delo."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1747
#, no-c-format
msgid "Questions and Answers"
msgstr "Vprašanja in odgovori"

#. Tag: chapter
#: index.docbook:1747
#, no-c-format
msgid "&reporting.bugs; &updating.documentation;"
msgstr "&reporting.bugs; &updating.documentation;"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1754
#, no-c-format
msgid "Why is it called \"&kdiff3;\"?"
msgstr "Zakaj se imenuje \"&kdiff3;\"?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1756
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Tools named <application>KDiff</application> and <application>KDiff2</"
"application> (now called &kompare;) already exist. Also &kdiff3; should "
"suggest that it can merge like the <command>diff3</command> tool in the Diff-"
"Tool collection."
msgstr ""
"Orodja z imenom <application>KDiff</application> in <application>KDiff2</"
"application> (zdaj imenovana &kompare;) že obstajata. Tudi &kdiff3; bi "
"moralo predlagati, da se lahko združi kot orodje <command>diff3</command> v "
"zbirki Diff-Tool."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1760
#, no-c-format
msgid "Why did I release it under GPL?"
msgstr "Zakaj sem ga izdal pod GPL?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1762
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"I'm using GPL programs for a very long time now and learned very much by "
"having a look at many of the sources. Hence this is my \"Thank You\" to all "
"programmers that also did so or will do the same."
msgstr ""
"Programe GPL uporabljam že zelo dolgo in sem se veliko naučil, ko sem si "
"ogledal številne vire. Zato je to moja \"hvala\" vsem programerjem, ki so "
"prav tako storili ali bodo storili enako."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1768
#, no-c-format
msgid "Some buttons and functions are missing. What's wrong?"
msgstr "Nekateri gumbi in funkcije manjkajo. Kaj je narobe?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1770
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You compiled from source but you probably didn't specify the correct prefix "
"for the installation. By default <command>cmake</command> wants to install "
"in <filename class=\"directory\">/usr/local</filename> but then the user-"
"interface resource file (&ie; <filename>kdiff3ui.rc</filename>) can't be "
"found. The <filename>README</filename> file contains more information about "
"the correct prefix."
msgstr ""
"Prevedli ste iz izvorne kode, vendar verjetno niste navedli pravilne "
"predpone za namestitev. Privzeto <command>cmake</command> želi namestiti v "
"<filename class=\"directory\">/usr/local</filename>, nato pa datoteko virov "
"uporabniškega vmesnika (&ie; <filename>kdiff3ui.rc</filename >) ni mogoče "
"najti. Datoteka <filename>README</filename> vsebuje več informacij o "
"pravilni predponi."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1778
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Often lines that are similar but not identical appear next to each other but "
"sometimes not. Why?"
msgstr ""
"Pogosto se vrstice, ki so podobne, vendar ne enake, pojavijo ena poleg "
"druge, včasih pa tudi ne. Zakaj?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1781
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Lines where only the amount of white space characters is different are "
"treated as \"equal\" at first, while just one different non-white character "
"causes the lines to be \"different\". If similar lines appear next to each "
"other, this actually is coincidence but this fortunately is often the case. "
"See also <link linkend=\"manualdiffhelp\">Manual Diff Help</link>."
msgstr ""
"Vrstice, kjer je različna le količina presledkov, se najprej obravnavajo kot "
"\"enake\", medtem ko samo en drugačen nebel znak povzroči, da so vrstice "
"\"različne\". Če se podobne črte pojavljajo druga zraven druge, je to "
"pravzaprav naključje, vendar je na srečo pogosto tako. Glejte tudi <link "
"linkend=\"manualdiffhelp\">Pomoč za ročno razlikovanje</link>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1789
#, no-c-format
msgid "Why must all conflicts be solved before the merge result can be saved?"
msgstr ""
"Zakaj je treba rešiti vse spore, preden je mogoče shraniti rezultat spajanja?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1791
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For each equal or different section the editor in the merge result window "
"remembers where it begins or ends. This is needed so that conflicts can be "
"solved manually by simply selecting the source button (<guilabel>A</"
"guilabel>, <guilabel>B</guilabel> or <guilabel>C</guilabel>). This "
"information is lost while saving as text and it is too much effort to create "
"a special file format that supports saving and restoring all necessary "
"information."
msgstr ""
"Za vsak enak ali različen razdelek si urejevalnik v oknu rezultatov "
"združevanja zapomni, kje se začne ali konča. To je potrebno, da se spori "
"lahko rešijo ročno s preprosto izbiro gumba vira (<guilabel>A</guilabel>, "
"<guilabel>B</guilabel> ali <guilabel>C</guilabel>). Te informacije se med "
"shranjevanjem kot besedilo izgubijo in ustvarjanje posebnega formata "
"datoteke, ki podpira shranjevanje in obnavljanje vseh potrebnih informacij, "
"je preveč naporno."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1795
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"How can I synchronise the diff and merge views, so that all views show the "
"same text position?"
msgstr ""
"Kako lahko sinhroniziram pogled razlik in združevanja, tako da vsi pogledi "
"prikazujejo isti položaj besedila?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1797
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Click into the summary column left of the text. (<link linkend="
"\"synchronise_views\">See also here.</link>)"
msgstr ""
"Kliknite na stolpec s povzetkom levo od besedila. (<link linkend="
"\"synchronise_views\">Glejte tudi tukaj.</link>)"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1801
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Why does <userinput>git difftool --dir-diff</userinput> give \"Mix of links "
"and normal files error\" when using KDiff3 as the difftool?"
msgstr ""
"Zakaj <userinput>git difftool --dir-diff</userinput> pri uporabi KDiff3 kot "
"difftool prikaže \"Napaka mešanice povezav in običajnih datotek\"?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1803
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This is a side effect of git's internal workings. If you try to compare a "
"previous revision to the current work tree git will compare actually files "
"representing the past commit to symlinks pointing to the worktree. As of 1.9 "
"KDiff3 defaults to having <guilabel>Follow file links</guilabel> and "
"<guilabel>Follow folder links</guilabel> on. Prior to this they were off by "
"default. This did not matter when not doing if \"Full analysis\" was also "
"off. However, with <guilabel>Full analysis</guilabel> on KDiff3 would "
"initially attempt to compare the path pointed to by a link rather than "
"follow it. Prior to 1.8 the resulting error was ignored. However, 1.8 began "
"reporting the error."
msgstr ""
"To je stranski učinek notranjega delovanja gita. Če poskušate primerjati "
"prejšnjo revizijo s trenutnim delovnim drevesom, bo git dejansko primerjal "
"datoteke, ki predstavljajo preteklo objavo, s simbolnimi povezavami, ki "
"kažejo na delovno drevo. Od 1.9 dalje ima KDiff3 privzeto vključeno "
"<guilabel>Sledi povezavam datotek</guilabel> in <guilabel>Sledi povezavam "
"map</guilabel>. Pred tem so bili privzeto izklopljeni. To ni bilo pomembno, "
"če ne delate, če je bila tudi \"Popolna analiza\" izklopljena. Vendar bi s "
"<guilabel>Popolno analizo</guilabel> na KDiff3 sprva poskušal primerjati "
"pot, na katero kaže povezava, namesto da bi ji sledil. Pred 1.8 je bila "
"nastala napaka prezrta. Vendar je 1.8 začel poročati o napaki."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1810
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Why does the editor in the merge result window not have an \"undo\"-function?"
msgstr ""
"Zakaj urejevalnik v oknu z rezultati spajanja nima funkcije \"razveljavi\"?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1812
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This was too much effort until now. You can always restore a version from "
"one source (<guilabel>A</guilabel>, <guilabel>B</guilabel> or <guilabel>C</"
"guilabel>) by clicking the respective button. For big editing the use of "
"another editor is recommended anyway."
msgstr ""
"To je bil do sedaj preveč truda. Vedno lahko obnovite različico iz enega "
"vira (<guilabel>A</guilabel>, <guilabel>B</guilabel> ali <guilabel>C</"
"guilabel>), tako da kliknete ustrezni gumb. Za veliko urejanja je vseeno "
"priporočljiva uporaba drugega urejevalnika."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1816
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When I removed some text, then suddenly \"&lt;No src line&gt;\" appeared and "
"cannot be deleted. What does that mean and how can one remove this?"
msgstr ""
"Ko sem odstranil nekaj besedila, se je nenadoma pojavilo \"&lt;Ni izvorne "
"vrstice&gt;\" in ga ni mogoče izbrisati. Kaj to pomeni in kako to odstraniti?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1819
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For each equal or different section the editor in the merge result window "
"remembers where it begins or ends. \"&lt;No src line&gt;\" means that there "
"is nothing left in a section, not even a new line character. This can happen "
"either while merging automatically or by editing. This is no problem, since "
"this hint won't appear in the saved file. If you want the original source "
"back just select the section (click on the left summary column) and then "
"click the source button with the needed contents (<guilabel>A</guilabel>/"
"<guilabel>B</guilabel> or <guilabel>C</guilabel>)."
msgstr ""
"Za vsak enak ali različen razdelek si urejevalnik v oknu rezultatov spajanja "
"zapomni, kje se začne ali konča. \"&lt;Ni izvorne vrstice&gt;\" pomeni, da v "
"razdelku ni več ničesar, niti znaka za novo vrstico. To se lahko zgodi med "
"samodejnim združevanjem ali z urejanjem. To ni problem, saj se ta namig ne "
"bo pojavil v shranjeni datoteki. Če želite nazaj izvirni vir, preprosto "
"izberite razdelek (kliknite levi stolpec s povzetkom) in nato kliknite gumb "
"vira s potrebno vsebino (<guilabel>A</guilabel>/<guilabel>B</guilabel> ali "
"<guilabel >C</guilabel>)."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1830
#, no-c-format
msgid "Why doesn't &kdiff3; support syntax-highlighting?"
msgstr "Zakaj &kdiff3; ne podpira označevanje sintakse?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1832
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kdiff3; already uses many colors for difference highlighting. More "
"highlighting would be confusing. Use another editor for this."
msgstr ""
"&kdiff3; že uporablja veliko barv za poudarjanje razlik. Več poudarjanja bi "
"bilo zmedeno. Za to uporabite drug urejevalnik."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1837
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Can I use &kdiff3; to compare <application>LibreOffice</application>/"
"<trademark class=\"registered\">OpenOffice.org</trademark>, "
"<application>&Microsoft; Word</application>, <application>&Microsoft; Excel</"
"application>, &PDF;, &etc; files?"
msgstr ""
"Ali lahko uporabim &kdiff3; za primerjavo <application>LibreOffice</"
"application>/<trademark class=\"registered\">OpenOffice.org</trademark>, "
"<application>&Microsoft; Word</application>, <application>&Microsoft; Excel</"
"application>, &PDF;, &etc;. datotek?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1841
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Although &kdiff3; will analyse any kind of file the result will probably not "
"be very satisfactory for you."
msgstr ""
"Čeprav &kdiff3; bo analiziral katero koli vrsto datoteke, rezultat za vas "
"verjetno ne bo zelo zadovoljiv."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1844
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kdiff3; was made to compare pure text files. <application>LibreOffice</"
"application>/<trademark class=\"registered\"> OpenOffice.org</trademark>, "
"<application>&Microsoft; Word</application>, <application>&Microsoft; Excel</"
"application>, &etc; store much more information in the files (about fonts, "
"pictures, pages, colors, &etc;) which &kdiff3; doesn't know about. So "
"&kdiff3; will show you the contents of the file interpreted as pure text, "
"but this might be unreadable or at least it will look very odd."
msgstr ""
"&kdiff3; je bil narejen za primerjavo čistih besedilnih datotek. "
"<application>LibreOffice</application>/<trademark class=\"registered\"> "
"OpenOffice.org</trademark>, <application>&Microsoft; Word</application>, "
"<application>&Microsoft; Excel</application>> &etc;. shrani veliko več "
"informacij v datoteke (o pisavah, slikah, straneh, barvah &etc;), ki jih "
"&kdiff3; ne pozna. Torej &kdiff3; vam bo prikazal vsebino datoteke, "
"interpretirano kot čisto besedilo, vendar je to morda neberljivo ali pa bo "
"vsaj videti zelo čudno."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1852
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Since most programs nowadays store their contents in &XML; format, you might "
"be able to read it as pure text. So if the change was only small, &kdiff3; "
"still might help you."
msgstr ""
"Ker večina današnjih programov shranjuje svojo vsebino v &XML; formatu, ga "
"boste morda lahko prebrali kot čisto besedilo. Torej, če je bila sprememba "
"le majhna, vam &kdiff3; še vedno lahko pomaga."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1856
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The best solution if you only want to compare the text (without embedded "
"objects like pictures) is to use <menuchoice><guimenu>Edit</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Select All</guimenuitem></menuchoice> and "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>Edit</guimenu><guimenuitem>Copy</guimenuitem></"
"menuchoice> menu items in your program to copy the interesting text to the "
"clipboard and then in &kdiff3; paste the text into either diff input window. "
"(See also <link linkend=\"selections\">Select, Copy And Paste</link>.)"
msgstr ""
"Najboljša rešitev, če želite primerjati samo besedilo (brez vdelanih "
"predmetov, kot so slike), je uporaba <menuchoice><guimenu>Uredi</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Izberi vse</guimenuitem></menuchoice> in "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>Uredi</guimenu><guimenuitem>Kopiraj</guimenuitem></"
"menuchoice> menijske elemente v vašem programu, da kopirate zanimivo "
"besedilo v odložišče in nato v &kdiff3; prilepite besedilo v katero koli "
"okno za vnos razlike. (Glejte tudi <link linkend=\"selections\">Izberi, "
"kopiraj in prilepi</link>.)"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1860
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Where has the folder option <guimenuitem>List only deltas</guimenuitem> gone?"
msgstr ""
"Kam je izginila možnost mape <guimenuitem>Seznam samo razlik</guimenuitem>?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1862
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"There are now several <link linkend=\"selectingvisiblefiles\">\"Show\" "
"options</link> in the <guimenu>Folder</guimenu> menu. Disabling "
"<guimenuitem>Show Identical Files</guimenuitem> will achieve what enabling "
"<guimenuitem>List only deltas</guimenuitem> used to do."
msgstr ""
"Zdaj je na voljo več <link linkend=\"selectingvisiblefiles\">možnosti "
"»Pokaži«</link> v meniju <guimenu>Mapa</guimenu>. Če onemogočite "
"<guimenuitem>Pokaži enake datoteke</guimenuitem>, boste dosegli tisto, kar "
"je prej omogočalo <guimenuitem>Seznam samo razlik</guimenuitem>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1868
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"How can I make a big selection in the diff input window because scrolling "
"takes so long?"
msgstr ""
"Kako lahko naredim velik izbor v oknu za vnos razlike, ker drsenje traja "
"tako dolgo?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1871
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Start the selection as usual (click and hold the &LMB;). Then use the "
"navigation keys (&eg; &PgUp;, &PgDn;) while holding the &LMB; down. (See "
"also <link linkend=\"selections\">Select, Copy And Paste</link>.)"
msgstr ""
"Zaženite izbiro kot običajno (kliknite in držite &LMB;). Nato uporabite "
"navigacijske tipke (&eg; &PgUp;, &PgDn;), medtem ko držite &LMB; navzdol. "
"(Glejte tudi <link linkend=\"selections\">Izberi, kopiraj in prilepi</link>.)"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1875
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"There is so much information here, but your question is still not answered?"
msgstr "Tukaj je toliko informacij, a na vaše vprašanje še vedno ni odgovora?"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1877
#, no-c-format
msgid "Please send me your question. I appreciate every comment."
msgstr "Prosim, pošljite mi svoje vprašanje. Cenim vsak komentar."

